item_13370.Name: Astounding Chair

item_1338.Description: The giant stabbing part of a giant stabbing wasp.
item_1338.Name: Fae Wasp Stinger

item_13401.Description: A collection of 1000 dowels that are the right length for becoming arrows, if a fletcher prepared them.
item_13401.Name: Oak Dowels

item_13402.Description: A collection of 1000 dowels that are the right length for becoming arrows, if a fletcher prepared them.
item_13402.Name: Maple Dowels

item_13403.Description: A collection of 1000 dowels that are the right length for becoming arrows, if a fletcher prepared them.
item_13403.Name: Cedar Dowels

item_13404.Description: Holds 1000 dowels. Suitable for use by fletchers. The box can only be used once.
item_13404.Name: Empty Fletching Box

item_13405.Description: A collection of 1000 dowels that are the right length for becoming arrows, if a fletcher prepared them.
item_13405.Name: Spruce Dowels

item_1341.Description: Quite warm, and quite bright: whatever's inside is alive!
item_1341.Name: Phoenix Egg

item_1342.Description: Some extremely dedicated Winter Court fae replace their biological heart with one of these. Presumably it makes them more powerful...
item_1342.Name: Fairy Iceheart

item_1343.Description: An animal has left these bones behind after eating a meal.
item_1343.Name: Gnawed Bones

item_13431.Description: This small fire is warm enough to keep you from freezing to death, but not good enough for much else. Lasts 60 seconds once deployed.
item_13431.Name: Emergency Warmth Fire

item_13432.Description: A fire pit, good for cooking in the field or for keeping warm in the cold. Lasts 3 minutes once deployed.
item_13432.Name: Basic Campfire

item_1345.Description: The shell of a small sea snail.
item_1345.Name: Auger Shell

item_13452.Description: A small box for storing up to 4 items. Lasts for 5 minutes once deployed. (Each player that access the storage crate can store their own items. All storage crates allow access to the same items for that player.)
item_13452.Name: Shoddy Storage Crate

item_13455.Description: A box for storing up to 8 items. Lasts for 5 minutes once deployed. (Each player that access the storage crate can store their own items. All storage crates allow access to the same items for that player.)
item_13455.Name: Crude Storage Crate

item_13458.Description: A box for storing up to 12 items. Lasts for 5 minutes once deployed. (Each player that access the storage crate can store their own items. All storage crates allow access to the same items for that player.)
item_13458.Name: Decent Storage Crate

item_1346.Description: The shell of a departed bivalve. It's pretty.
item_1346.Name: Scallop Shell

item_13461.Description: A box for storing up to 16 items. Lasts for 5 minutes once deployed. (Each player that access the storage crate can store their own items. All storage crates allow access to the same items for that player.)
item_13461.Name: Nice Storage Crate

item_13463.Description: A box for storing up to 20 items. Lasts for 5 minutes once deployed. (Each player that access the storage crate can store their own items. All storage crates allow access to the same items for that player.)
item_13463.Name: Quality Storage Crate

item_13464.Description: A box for storing up to 24 items. Lasts for 5 minutes once deployed. (Each player that access the storage crate can store their own items. All storage crates allow access to the same items for that player.)
item_13464.Name: Great Storage Crate

item_13465.Description: A box for storing up to 28 items. Lasts for 5 minutes once deployed. (Each player that access the storage crate can store their own items. All storage crates allow access to the same items for that player.)
item_13465.Name: Amazing Storage Crate

item_1347.Description: The shell of a deceased snail. It's pretty.
item_1347.Name: Small Conch

item_1348.Description: The shell of a deceased snail. This is an especially large and pretty shell.
item_1348.Name: Large Conch

item_13481.Description: A small cask used in dairy and beer production.
item_13481.Name: Firkin

item_13482.Description: A mid-sized cask used for food and drink production.
item_13482.Name: Kilderkin

item_13483.Description: A large cask used for storing wet and dry goods.
item_13483.Name: Barrel

item_13484.Description: A large cask used for aging wine.
item_13484.Name: Hogshead

item_1350.Description: It's too waterlogged and slimy to be salvaged.
item_1350.Name: Moldy Old Boot

item_13501.Description: An elaborate contraption that can dispense free items. This model can dispense up to 10 of a single kind of item.
item_13501.Name: Simple Item Dispenser

item_13502.Description: An elaborate contraption that can dispense free items. This model can dispense up to 1000 of a single kind of item.
item_13502.Name: Large-Capacity Item Dispenser

item_13503.Description: An elaborate contraption that can dispense free items. This model can dispense up to 1000 of a single kind of item and has a place for a custom message that all visitors will see.
item_13503.Name: Fancy Item Dispenser

item_1351.Description: A handful of fragmented animal shells.
item_1351.Name: Shell Fragments

item_13513.Description: An elaborate contraption that can dispense items and collect currency. This model can sell up to 10 of a single kind of item.
item_13513.Name: Simple Item Vendor

item_13514.Description: An elaborate contraption that can dispense items and collect currency. This model can sell up to 1000 of a single kind of item.
item_13514.Name: Large-Capacity Item Vendor

item_13515.Description: An elaborate contraption that can dispense items and collect currency. This model can sell up to 1000 of a single kind of item and has a place for a custom message that all users will see.
item_13515.Name: Fancy Item Vendor

item_13516.Description: For Guide use only! This is a Fancy Item Vendor that only dispenses to Demo players.
item_13516.Name: Demo-Player Item Vendor

item_13521.Description:
An elaborate contraption that can dispense free raffle tickets and then deliver a reward to the raffle winner.

This model can dispense up to 10 free raffle tickets for a single item (or item stack).
item_13521.Name: Simple Free Item Raffler

item_13522.Description:
An elaborate contraption that can dispense free raffle tickets and then deliver a reward to the raffle winner.

This model can dispense up to 20 free raffle tickets for 1 or 2 items (or item stacks) and/or a small cash prize.
item_13522.Name: Modest Free Item Raffler

item_13523.Description:
An elaborate contraption that can dispense raffle tickets and then deliver a reward to the raffle winner.

This model can dispense up to 30 raffle tickets for up to 3 items (or item stacks) and/or a cash prize. The raffle tickets can be free or can cost Councils.
item_13523.Name: Standard Item Raffler

item_13524.Description:
An elaborate contraption that can dispense raffle tickets and then deliver a reward to the raffle winner.

This model can dispense up to 50 raffle tickets for up to 6 items (or item stacks) and/or a cash prize. The raffle tickets can be free or can cost Councils. This model has a place for an inscription that is displayed to each user.
item_13524.Name: Fancy Item Raffler

item_13525.Description:
An elaborate contraption that can dispense raffle tickets and then deliver a reward to the raffle winner.

This model can dispense up to 100 raffle tickets for up to 8 items (or item stacks) and/or a cash prize. The raffle tickets can be free or can cost Councils. This model has a place for an inscription that is displayed to each user, and a message that is shown only to the winner. This model can also be configured to have a time limit of 1-60 minutes.
item_13525.Name: Advanced Item Raffler

item_13526.Description:
An elaborate contraption that can dispense raffle tickets and then deliver a reward to the raffle winner.

This model can dispense up to 1000 raffle tickets for up to 10 items (or item stacks) and/or a cash prize. The raffle tickets can be free or can cost Councils. This model has a place for an inscription that is displayed to each user, and a message that is shown only to the winner. This model can also be configured to have a time limit of 1-90 minutes.
item_13526.Name: Ultra Item Raffler

item_13527.Description: For Guide use only! This is an Ultra Item Raffler that only allows Demo players to take tickets.
item_13527.Name: Demo-Player Raffler

item_13528.Description: A raffler with all standard options, plus the ability to attune the items to the winner. For admin use.
item_13528.Name: Admin Item Raffler

item_1354.Description: The shell of a small sea snail. Some say this species comes from the fae realm, but it doesn't seem particularly unusual.
item_1354.Name: Fae Auger Shell

item_13541.Description: A simple spring-activated trap that will stun whatever walks over it. One-use.
item_13541.Name: Paralyzing Rat Trap

item_1355.Description: A particularly flat species of sea urchin. These shells are used as currency by the Ranalon.
item_1355.Name: Sand Dollar

item_1358.Description: A lovely conch that has proven to be resilient and powerful. It's amazing for making magic weapons with!
item_1358.Name: Amazing Conch

item_1359.Description: A lovely conch that has proven to be resilient and powerful. It's perfect for making magic weapons with!
item_1359.Name: Perfect Conch

item_1360.Description: A tool used aboard Fae ships during the repair of hull damage. It's quite heavy!
item_1360.Name: Articulated Cutting Arm

item_1361.Description: This lightweight piece of... metal? Is used for... something? Anyway, it's green.
item_1361.Name: Accuracy Circuit

item_1362.Description: A few drops of residue from some type of cold elemental.
item_1362.Name: Frost Elemental Runoff

item_1363.Description: A crystallized honeycomb containing an audio message. Only fae seem to be able to access these documents, but in this case it's clearly humdrum day-to-day paperwork.
item_1363.Name: "Jumpdrive Diagnostic Results"

item_1364.Description: A crystallized honeycomb containing an audio message. Only fae seem to be able to access these documents, but in this case it's clearly humdrum day-to-day paperwork.
item_1364.Name: "Dimensional Scan Repair Log"

item_1365.Description: A crystallized honeycomb containing an audio message. Only fae seem to be able to access these documents, but in this case it's clearly humdrum day-to-day paperwork.
item_1365.Name: "Entropic Barrier Maintenance Requirements"

item_1366.Description: A small lump of gold with arrows carved into it. It seems to be a pawn for some sort of game.
item_1366.Name: Golden Zelta Token

item_1367.Description: A small shiny green rock with arrows carved into it. It seems to be a pawn for some sort of game.
item_1367.Name: Aventurine Zelta Token

item_1368.Description: It's a sealed pouch with a mineral inside.
item_1368.Name: Mortal-Realm Mineral Sample

item_1369.Description: It's a sealed pouch with something inside.
item_1369.Name: Mortal-Realm Flora Sample

item_14001.Description: A simple wooden key with a faint green magical glow.
item_14001.Name: Wooden Key

item_14002.Description: A key cut from magical ice. It won't melt until it is used in whatever strange door it's designed for.
item_14002.Name: Winter Nexus Key

item_14003.Description:
A brief note written in a lovely flowing script. It says,

"Do you remember when your helm was shattered? Probably not. You gave it to me to repair, but it was beyond my skill. I took it to Haetrix, who used inappropriately-strong magic, and now its reality is damaged. Anyway, if your helm disappears in a puff of logic, don't fret. I've locked it in a box for you near the Sun Vale mouth. Gut a troll to light the lamp light, rip the wings off a deviant fae for the second, and rip out the stomach of your least favorite ogre for the third.

- Trallix"
item_14003.Name: Note to Algid Overseer Winterhue

item_14004.Description: A key cut from magical ice.
item_14004.Name: Dementia Puck's Key

item_14005.Description: A key formed of dirt, held in place via magic.
item_14005.Name: Fae Animal Nexus Key

item_14006.Description: It's a piece of lacquered wood shaped like a long worm with a fanged mouth. Pretty impressive, really.
item_14006.Name: Gulagra's Sigil Key

item_14007.Description: It's a small parchment with a magical inscription. You can use this to get past a huge icy barrier beneath the ruined tower in Kur.
item_14007.Name: Ice Bypass Spell

item_14008.Description: A small metal key you found in a cave in Kur Mountains.
item_14008.Name: Wolf Loot Key

item_14009.Description: A metal key from Gravamux, a ghoul.
item_14009.Name: Gravamux's Key

item_14010.Description: A crystal used to unlock certain Crone Hegemony armory chests. This one is partially digested, but should still work.
item_14010.Name: Hegemonic Storage Key

item_14011.Description: An ancient stone key, worn by yetis as a good luck token.
item_14011.Name: Yeti Key

item_14012.Description:
A note in a jaggy, hurried handwriting. It says,

"Test is still underway. I have passed the Combat and Teleportation trials, but I can't figure out how to get into the locked chest with the altars around it. I used Divination, but the only answer I got was 'SEWN'.

I still have my secret weapon: a Potion of Brilliance. Will drink it if necessary, but leaving it here for now."
item_14012.Name: Journal Entry

item_14013.Description:
A metal key with a note attached. In flowery script it says,

"My dear Lawyr, I knew you could do it! Meet me on the mainland and I'll help you recover your destiny. - Yurra"
item_14013.Name: Chest Key

item_14015.Description: It's a parchment with strange symbols on it. Perhaps someone could explain its meaning to you.
item_14015.Name: Symbols of Darkness

item_14016.Description: A drop of blood that's been affected by the fae realm. Winterprize crystals are known to be sensitive to this sort of blood. Carrying it in large quantities is unwise, however, as it can corrupt the bearer. (You cannot carry more than 6 at once.)
item_14016.Name: Winter Fae Blood

item_14017.Description: Lets you leap high and control your fall. You also take no damage from falls, no matter how high. On the down side, you'll be too disoriented to effectively fight, and your attacks will deal very little damage.
EffectDescs: Boosts jumping abilities dramatically, and reduces all attacks by 90%, for 2 minutes
item_14017.Name: Superjump Potion

item_14018.Description: Lets you fly for 5 minutes (press the Move Up key to begin). Also grants immunity to falling damage. Only usable outdoors; entering a dungeon will cause the effect to immediately end.
item_14018.Name: Flight Potion

item_14019.Description: Lets you sprint very, very fast. (Hold down shift key to switch between sprinting and walking.) You also take no damage from falls. Lasts 2 minutes.
item_14019.Name: Super Speed Potion

item_14020.Description: A bulky wooden cup full of greenish energy. You can sip this in your dying moments in order to come back to life.
item_14020.Name: Chalice of Life

item_14021.Description: A bone key that fits in any of the special event loot chests in Serbule. (Look behind the inn.)
item_14021.Name: Event Loot Key (Universal)

item_14022.Description: A bone key that fits in the special chest in Serbule for level 10-20 loot. (Look behind the inn.)
item_14022.Name: Level 10-20 Event Loot Key

item_14023.Description: A bone key that fits in the special chest in Serbule for level 30 loot. (Look behind the inn.)
item_14023.Name: Level 30 Event Loot Key

item_14024.Description: A bone key that fits in the special chest in Serbule for level 40 loot. (Look behind the inn.)
item_14024.Name: Level 40 Event Loot Key

item_14025.Description: A bone key that fits in the special chest in Serbule for level 50 loot. (Look behind the inn.)
item_14025.Name: Level 50 Event Loot Key

item_14026.Description: A bone key that fits in the special chest in Serbule for level 60 loot. (Look behind the inn.)
item_14026.Name: Level 60 Event Loot Key

item_14027.Description: A transferrable day-pass to visit the parts of Rahu that are usually off-limits to tourists. While this permit lasts, the citizens of Rahu will not attack you and shopkeepers will generally be willing to deal with you. The pass becomes invalidated if you attack any Rahu citizen, and the plateau where the Onkara train is still off-limits.
EffectDescs: Grants access to back-areas of Rahu for 90 minutes
item_14027.Name: Rahu Visitor's Permit

item_14028.Description: A thin blanket embroidered with a depiction of a beaming sun. This style of blanket is often given out by followers of Arisetsu, the god of warmth and hope.
EffectDescs: Restores 20 Body Heat, Cures Hypothermia and Frostbite (one-time use)
item_14028.Name: Simple Arisetsu Blanket

item_14029.Description: A rotten urak egg. Completely valueless.
item_14029.Name: Unfertilized Dead Urak Egg

item_14030.Description: A Gazluk officer's key to one of the armory storage chests.
item_14030.Name: Gazluk Armory Key

item_14031.Description: The key to a goblin hoard chest, typically one of several keys needed to unlock it.
item_14031.Name: Gobkey Alpha

item_14032.Description: The key to a goblin hoard chest, typically one of several keys needed to unlock it.
item_14032.Name: Gobkey Beta

item_14033.Description: The key to a goblin hoard chest, typically one of several keys needed to unlock it.
item_14033.Name: Gobkey Gamma

item_14034.Description:
A handwritten note. It says,

"If you're reading this then I didn't make it out alive. Please help my friends, they're still trapped in this horrible cave. Look for the ever-burn campfire. We're camped around it because it keeps the spiders away somewhat.

We came for spider eggs, and the spiders seemed weak enough. But as we climbed higher into the caves to reach the egg-chambers, we found MUCH harder ones. Soum died when a spider exploded out of him... we all freaked out and ran... now we can't escape because of injuries. Help, please! And if you're here for spider eggs, turn back now. - Cole Fensmith"
item_14034.Name: Plea for Help

item_14035.Description: A bone key that fits in the special chest in Serbule for level 70 loot. (Look behind the inn.)
item_14035.Name: Level 70 Event Loot Key

item_14036.Description: This series of books by the goblin sage Muligu details each god that might be able to help you with a knowledge-related question.
item_14036.Name: "The Gods of Knowledge, Vol. 1"

item_14037.Description: This series of books by the goblin sage Muligu details each god that might be able to help you with a knowledge-related question.
item_14037.Name: "The Gods of Knowledge, Vol. 2"

item_14038.Description: This series of books by the goblin sage Muligu details each god that might be able to help you with a knowledge-related question.
item_14038.Name: "The Gods of Knowledge, Vol. 3"

item_14039.Description: This series of books by the goblin sage Muligu details each god that might be able to help you with a knowledge-related question.
item_14039.Name: "The Gods of Knowledge, Vol. 4"

item_14040.Description: The work of a master stoneshaper, this key is a miniature work of art. It may unlock something somewhere, but even if not, it's an interesting curio.
item_14040.Name: Ranalon Key

item_14043.Description: This ticket entitles the bearer to a free game of Monsters and Mantids at any table in the Red Wing Casino.
item_14043.Name: Monsters and Mantids Free-Play Ticket

item_14044.Description: This ticket entitles the bearer to a free game of Lootmaster Match-3 at the Red Wing Casino.
item_14044.Name: Lootmaster Free-Play Ticket

item_14045.Description: This ticket entitles the bearer to a free game of Cashfall Match-3 at the Red Wing Casino.
item_14045.Name: Cashfall Free-Play Ticket

item_14046.Description: A small runestone that's worth a small fortune at the Red Wing Casino. See Qatik to trade this for 5,000 Councils.
item_14046.Name: Black Windfall Stone

item_14047.Description: A small runestone that's worth a small fortune at the Red Wing Casino. See Qatik to trade this for 7,000 Councils.
item_14047.Name: Green Windfall Stone

item_14048.Description: A small runestone that's worth a small fortune at the Red Wing Casino. See Qatik to trade this for 10,000 Councils.
item_14048.Name: Blue Windfall Stone

item_14049.Description: A small runestone that's worth a small fortune at the Red Wing Casino. See Qatik to trade this for 15,000 Councils.
item_14049.Name: Red Windfall Stone

item_14050.Description: A small runestone that's worth a small fortune at the Red Wing Casino. See Qatik to trade this for 20,000 Councils.
item_14050.Name: Orange Windfall Stone

item_14051.Description: A small runestone that's worth a small fortune at the Red Wing Casino. See Qatik to trade this for 25,000 Councils.
item_14051.Name: Violet Windfall Stone

item_14052.Description: A small runestone that's worth a small fortune at the Red Wing Casino. See Qatik to trade this for 50,000 Councils.
item_14052.Name: Yellow Windfall Stone

item_14053.Description: This reddish token is made of very thin metal. There are tiny inscrutable symbols painted on the back side. (See Qatik at the Red Wing Casino to trade these tokens for prizes.)
item_14053.Name: Red Wing Token

item_14054.Description: A small plush bear. It's enchanted to give encouraging messages when you're sad.
item_14054.Name: Stuffed Toy Bear

item_14055.Description: See Qatik in the Red Wing Casino to trade this token in for a magical crown!
item_14055.Name: Crown Token

item_14056.Description: A lovely stuffed toy with joyous cymbal-clashing action. It can be deployed periodically to entertain others.
item_14056.Name: Cymbal Monkey

item_14057.Description: A tiny key made of jade.
item_14057.Name: Weird Key

item_14058.Description: Made of an unfamiliar metal, this key has weird lines etched all over it.
item_14058.Name: Alien Key

item_14059.Description: A weird symbol carved into a strange metal.
item_14059.Name: Ratkin Necromancer's Talisman

item_14060.Description: An old key encrusted in slime. Somehow it passed beyond the veil of death! But it's back now.
item_14060.Name: Velmer's Key

item_14061.Description: A small valuable item encased in protective goop. The goblin technique for removing the stuff requires special equipment. Perhaps there's another means to open it.
item_14061.Name: Goblands Transit Pod

item_14062.Description: A fancy key that can open any Minotaur Vault. For security reasons the key is destroyed upon use.
item_14062.Name: Minotaur Vault Master Key

item_14063.Description: A piece of paper that says "This document is worth 1 (one) Sir Johnson Buck, redeemable at participating commissaries. Sir Johnson retains the right to confiscate this document if he thinks you stole it." Beneath the impeccably-handwritten note is an illegible scrawl that you assume is Sir Johnson's signature.
item_14063.Name: Sir Johnson Buck

item_14064.Description: The first volume in a series of travelogues and interviews by the semi-famous mage Reginald.
item_14064.Name: The Sage's Lectern, Vol. 1

item_14065.Description: The second volume in a series of travelogues and interviews by the semi-famous mage Reginald.
item_14065.Name: The Sage's Lectern, Vol. 2

item_14066.Description: The title is dull, but the cover art suggests something... less dull. However, someone has torn out the front half of the book, leaving only appendices.
item_14066.Name: The Origin of 'Tast's Pack'

item_14067.Description: A bone key that fits in the special chest in Serbule for level 80 loot. (Look behind the inn.)
item_14067.Name: Level 80 Event Loot Key

item_14068.Description:
This token can be redeemed with -ADMIN- Jackencola for up to a level 80 max-enchanted ring, necklace or piece of armor of choice.
This token can only be redeemed by the account that won it. The prize is non-transferable.
item_14068.Name: MEGA Raffle Prize Token

item_14069.Description: This token is the special currency of the Crafter's Guild. It seems to have no real Council value to it, but the members of the Crafting Caravan value them for trade among fellow professionals.
item_14069.Name: Crafter's Guild Token

item_14070.Description: The strange substance in this bag can keep dying fairies from leaving this plane of existence. It costs 50 Fae Energy to use this item. It smells of honey. (This item is useless to non-fae.)
EffectDescs: Respawns you at this area's entrance (instead of the Fae Realm)
item_14070.Name: Fairy Soul Anchor

item_14071.Description:
This special mixture grants you the ability to carry more stuff at one time, which is essential when out traveling for a long period of time.
This effect does not stack with other inventory expansion potions from Orran and overrides all inventory Words of Power.
item_14071.Name: Orran's Inventory Expander Potion

item_14072.Description:
This special mixture grants you the ability to carry a lot more stuff at one time, which is essential when out traveling for a long period of time.
This effect does not stack with other inventory expansion potions from Orran and overrides all inventory Words of Power.
item_14072.Name: Orran's Super Inventory Expander Potion

item_14073.Description:
This special mixture grants you the ability to carry a whole lot more stuff at one time, which is essential when out traveling for a long period of time.
This effect does not stack with other inventory expansion potions from Orran and overrides all inventory Words of Power.
item_14073.Name: Orran's Ultra Inventory Expander Potion

item_14074.Description: A strange cube. It once held augmentation magic, but it's been damaged beyond repair. You might be able to salvage something from it... if you knew how to open it without shattering it.
item_14074.Name: Broken Augment

item_14076.Description: A token that is acquired as a reward for participating in a live event. This token can be redeemed for certain things across Alharth.
item_14076.Name: Live Event Token

item_14077.Description: Part of an abomination. It has an identification mark branded into it. Might be useful to impersonate an abomination... but mostly just junk.
item_14077.Name: Identification Gland

item_14078.Description: A beautiful collar with a unique identification number chiseled into the inside. As well as being made of silver, it might be useful for accessing certain supply crates.
item_14078.Name: Silver Hippogriff Collar

item_14081.Description: An exotic key. As a security mechanism, it self-destructs after a few days.
item_14081.Name: Transport Security Card

item_14082.Description: A special token from Raim to barter for a special advanced item.
item_14082.Name: Raim's Advanced Crafting Token

item_14083.Description: A special token from Moxie to barter for a special advanced item.
item_14083.Name: Moxie's Advanced Crafting Token

item_14084.Description: An old metal key from a dusty old chest you found under Hogan's Keep. Utterly unremarkable.
item_14084.Name: Dusty Key

item_14085.Description: A shiny metal key from a goblin jewelry chest that you found under Hogan's Keep. Very well polished.
item_14085.Name: Shiny Key

item_14086.Description: A scorched metal key you found in the belly of a fire spider under Hogan's Keep. This key has seen some hot action.
item_14086.Name: Scorched Key

item_14087.Description: An antique, encrusted metal key. Unfortunately it appears to be encrusted in bear shit.
item_14087.Name: Bear Key

item_14088.Description: The bleeding end clotted up fast, so this severed goblin thumb is a little less disgusting than it could be.
item_14088.Name: Minizhemu's Severed Finger

item_14090.Description: Teaches you how to summon a vendor fox from a box.
item_14090.Name: Event: Vendor Fox in a Box

item_14091.Description: A small handheld device with a large amethyst set in the center used to teleport the wielder to an attuned location. This device will self destruct when the charge has expired.
item_14091.Name: Personal Teleportation Device - Serbule

item_14092.Description: A small handheld device with a large amethyst set in the center used to teleport the wielder to an attuned location. This device will self destruct when the charge has expired.
item_14092.Name: Personal Teleportation Device - Eltibule

item_14093.Description: A small handheld device with a large amethyst set in the center used to teleport the wielder to an attuned location. This device will self destruct when the charge has expired.
item_14093.Name: Personal Teleportation Device - Kur Mountains

item_14094.Description: A small handheld device with a large amethyst set in the center used to teleport the wielder to an attuned location. This device will self destruct when the charge has expired.
EffectDescs: Teleports wielder to the Ilmari Desert
item_14094.Name: Personal Teleportation Device - Ilmari Desert

item_14095.Description: A small handheld device with a large amethyst set in the center used to teleport the wielder to an attuned location. This device will self destruct when the charge has expired.
item_14095.Name: Personal Teleportation Device - Sun Vale

item_14096.Description: A small handheld device with a large amethyst set in the center used to teleport the wielder to an attuned location. This device will self destruct when the charge has expired.
EffectDescs: Teleports wielder to New Prestonbule in Gazluk
item_14096.Name: Personal Teleportation Device - New Prestonbule

item_14097.Description: A small handheld device with a large amethyst set in the center used to teleport the wielder to an attuned location. This device will self destruct when the charge has expired.
EffectDescs: Teleports wielder to the Fae Realm
item_14097.Name: Personal Teleportation Device - Fae Realm

item_15301.Description: Powdered brains of psychic creatures. A choice drug for psychics.
EffectDescs: All Mentalism and Psychology attacks deal +7 damage for 15 minutes
After-effects reduce damage for a time but can be countered with more Cranium Powder
item_15301.Name: Cranium Powder

item_15302.Description: Powdered brains of psychic creatures. A choice drug for psychics. This batch is 99% pure frontal cortex.
EffectDescs: All Mentalism and Psychology attacks deal +15 damage for 20 minutes
After-effects reduce damage for a time but can be countered with more Cranium Powder
item_15302.Name: Pure Cranium Powder

item_15303.Description: Powdered brains of psychic creatures. A choice drug for psychics. This batch has been enhanced with secret chemicals.
EffectDescs: All Mentalism and Psychology attacks deal +23 damage for 30 minutes
After-effects reduce damage for a time but can be countered with more Cranium Powder
item_15303.Name: Enhanced Cranium Powder

item_15304.Description: A substance made of cranium powder, mixed with chemicals that alter its effect.
EffectDescs: Cures the symptoms of Cranium Powder abuse
item_15304.Name: Cranium Balm

item_15331.Description: The enchanted and ground-up pineal glands of intelligent creatures, in a sweet syrupy liquid.
EffectDescs: After-effects reduce Max Power and Power Regeneration for a time, but can be countered by drinking more Pineal Juice
item_15331.Name: Pineal Juice

item_15332.Description: The enchanted and ground-up pineal glands of intelligent creatures. No syrup added, just pure pineal juice.
EffectDescs: After-effects reduce Max Power and Power Regeneration for a time, but can be countered by drinking more Pineal Juice
item_15332.Name: Pure Pineal Juice

item_15333.Description: The enchanted and ground-up pineal glands of intelligent creatures, mixed with a secret catalyst for added effect.
EffectDescs: After-effects reduce Max Power and Power Regeneration for a time, but can be countered by drinking more Pineal Juice
item_15333.Name: Enhanced Pineal Juice

item_15334.Description: A lemony liquid designed to counter the effects of severe Pineal Juice abuse.
EffectDescs: Temporarily masks the side-effects of Pineal Juice abuse
item_15334.Name: Faux Pineal Juice

item_15341.Description: A packet of strange chemicals wrapped in a leaf. It's said that some sentient animals find this drug irresistible.
EffectDescs: All animal attacks deal +10 damage for 15 minutes and animals experience additional movement-related benefits depending upon their form
After-effects reduce damage for a time but can be countered with more Bounceweed
item_15341.Name: Bounceweed

item_15342.Description: A packet of strange chemicals wrapped in a leaf. It's said that some sentient animals find this drug irresistible.
EffectDescs: All animal attacks deal +20 damage for 15 minutes and animals experience additional movement-related benefits depending upon their form
After-effects reduce damage for a time but can be countered with more Bounceweed
item_15342.Name: Northern Bounceweed

item_15343.Description: A packet of strange chemicals wrapped in a leaf. It's said that some sentient animals find this drug irresistible.
EffectDescs: All animal attacks deal +30 damage for 15 minutes and animals experience additional movement-related benefits depending upon their form
After-effects reduce damage for a time but can be countered with more Bounceweed
item_15343.Name: Pure Bounceweed

item_15344.Description: A packet of strange chemicals wrapped in a leaf. It's said that some sentient animals find this drug irresistible.
EffectDescs: All animal attacks deal +40 damage for 15 minutes and animals experience additional movement-related benefits depending upon their form
After-effects reduce damage for a time but can be countered with more Bounceweed
item_15344.Name: Augmented Bounceweed

item_15345.Description: A packet of strange chemicals wrapped in a leaf. While it has minor benefits, its primary use is to cure Bounceweed hangovers. It can also temporarily relieve the symptoms of Bounceweed abuse. Calmweed is not addictive.
EffectDescs: For 60 minutes Max Power is raised by +3, all animal attacks deal +2 damage, and negative side-effects of Bounceweed use are masked
item_15345.Name: Calmweed

item_15346.Description:
A thin tube full of liquid. Apparently you jab it into your skin to use it -- a horrific idea that only a mantis could dream up.

Sharpen is supposedly not addictive.
EffectDescs: For 15 minutes, all non-basic attacks made with fists, feet, claws, teeth, or similar body parts deal +20 damage.
item_15346.Name: Sharpen

item_15347.Description:
A thin tube full of liquid. Apparently you jab it into your skin to use it -- a horrific idea that only a mantis could dream up.

Sharpen is supposedly not addictive, but higher-quality doses are only effective if the recipient has well-honed survival instincts.
EffectDescs: For 15 minutes, all non-basic attacks made with fists, feet, claws, teeth, or similar body parts deal +40 damage.
item_15347.Name: Super Sharpen

item_15348.Description:
A thin tube full of liquid. Apparently you jab it into your skin to use it -- a horrific idea that only a mantis could dream up.

Sharpen is supposedly not addictive, but higher-quality doses are only effective if the recipient has well-honed survival instincts.
EffectDescs: For 15 minutes, all non-basic attacks made with fists, feet, claws, teeth, or similar body parts deal +80 damage.
item_15348.Name: Ultra Sharpen

item_15349.Description:
A thin tube full of liquid. Apparently you jab it into your skin to use it -- a horrific idea that only a mantis could dream up.

Sharpen is supposedly not addictive, but higher-quality doses are only effective if the recipient has well-honed survival instincts.
EffectDescs: For 15 minutes, all non-basic attacks made with fists, feet, claws, teeth, or similar body parts deal +120 damage.
item_15349.Name: Perfect Sharpen

item_15351.Description: A small vial that reeks of urine, gore, and chemicals. Only rakshasa are able to stomach this substance, and even they find it revolting -- although many rakshasa claim the smell is also strangely exhilarating.
EffectDescs: For 15 minutes, melee attacks deal +25 damage and melee evasion is +5%. Then the drinker suffers withdrawal effects for 15 minutes.
item_15351.Name: Telka's Teeth ("Baby Tooth" Variety)

item_15352.Description: A small vial that reeks of urine, gore, and chemicals. Only rakshasa are able to stomach this substance, and even they find it revolting -- although many rakshasa claim the smell is also strangely exhilarating.
EffectDescs: For 20 minutes, melee attacks deal +50 damage, melee evasion is +10%, and XP is earned faster when in the right mindframe. Afterwards, the drinker suffers painful withdrawal effects for 20 minutes.
item_15352.Name: Telka's Teeth ("Molar" Variety)

item_15353.Description: A small vial that reeks of urine, gore, and chemicals. Only rakshasa are able to stomach this substance, and even they find it revolting -- although many rakshasa claim the smell is also strangely exhilarating.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, melee attacks deal +75 damage, melee evasion is +15%, and XP is earned faster when in the right mindframe. Afterwards, the drinker suffers agonizing withdrawal effects for 30 minutes.
item_15353.Name: Telka's Teeth ("Incisor" Variety)

item_15354.Description: A small vial that reeks of urine, gore, and chemicals. Only rakshasa are able to stomach this substance, and even they find it revolting -- although many rakshasa claim the smell is also strangely exhilarating.
EffectDescs: For 45 minutes, melee attacks deal +100 damage, melee evasion is +20%, and XP is earned faster when in the right mindframe. Afterwards, the drinker suffers excruciating withdrawal effects for 45 minutes.
item_15354.Name: Telka's Teeth ("Canine" Variety)

item_15801.Description: A sweet syrupy potion that warms the throat when drunk.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, gain +8 mitigation against Cold, Nature, Acid, and Poison damage, both direct and indirect.
item_15801.Name: Toxin Resistance Potion

item_15802.Description: It looks like milk, but stinks like mashed-up spider bits.
EffectDescs: Boosts direct and indirect poison mitigation by 3 and raises Max Health +15 for 60 minutes
item_15802.Name: Poison Protection Potion

item_15804.Description: Just pulped-up spider bits in a jar.
EffectDescs: For 60 minutes, your out-of-combat Sprint Speed is +1
item_15804.Name: Spider Speed Potion

item_15805.Description: Bits of ground-up stinger are floating in it.
EffectDescs: Boosts direct and indirect fire, cold, and electricity mitigation by 5 for 60 minutes
item_15805.Name: Energy Resistance Potion

item_15806.Description: It tastes like pureed salad. And since you use it by applying it to your skin, you too will smell like pureed salad.
EffectDescs: Boosts damage vs. creatures with the Fish anatomy type +10% for 60 minutes
item_15806.Name: Gillpuncher Ointment

item_15807.Description: A topical balm beloved by ranalon, who apply it to their skin continuously. Its effects are much weaker when applied to non-ranalon, but it is, at least, safe to use.
EffectDescs: For one hour, boosts Max Bodyheat +20 and Breath Restored (on land or partial water) +5/sec
item_15807.Name: Moistening Cream

EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Fire Magic attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15808.Name: Fire Magic Boost Potion 20%

EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Ice Magic attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15809.Name: Ice Magic Boost Potion 20%

item_15810.Description: An unpleasant substance that activates every area of your tongue at once.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Mentalism attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15810.Name: Mentalism Boost Potion 20%

item_15811.Description: A terrible-smelling liquid that actually only tastes unpleasant, not terrible.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Psychology attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15811.Name: Psychology Boost Potion 20%

item_15812.Description: It tastes like orange juice! Kind of!
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Priest attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15812.Name: Priest Boost Potion 20%

item_15813.Description: Tastes like furry eyeballs but it makes all your motions feel crisp and sharp.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Sword attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15813.Name: Sword Boost Potion 20%

item_15814.Description: It tastes crunchy and unpleasant. As a side-effect, it's extremely difficult to relax while under the effect of this potion.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Knife attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15814.Name: Knife Boost Potion 20%

item_15815.Description: You don't want to think about the taste... it's best to drink something strong afterwards.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Unarmed attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15815.Name: Unarmed Boost Potion 20%

item_15816.Description: Weirdly cold and soupy, but not unpleasant to taste.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Staff attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15816.Name: Staff Boost Potion 20%

item_15817.Description: Smells like entrails. Tastes like entrails... but with an extremely unpleasant crunch.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Hammer attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15817.Name: Hammer Boost Potion 20%

item_15818.Description: Smells foul but doesn't really taste bad (for an alchemy potion).
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Battle Chemistry attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15818.Name: Battle Chemistry Boost Potion 20%

item_15819.Description: Sniff that? Smells like feathers and hate. Definitely an archery potion.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Archery attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15819.Name: Archery Boost Potion 20%

EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Bard attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15820.Name: Bard Boost Potion 20%

EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Shield attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15821.Name: Shield Boost Potion 20%

item_15822.Description: This liquid is viscous and gross.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Animal Handling attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15822.Name: Animal Handling Boost Potion 20%

item_15823.Description: Smells of sulfur and tastes of hair. Typical alchemy nonsense.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Werewolf skill attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15823.Name: Werewolf Boost Potion 20%

item_15824.Description: Thick and crunchy, like any good potion.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Spider skill attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15824.Name: Spider Boost Potion 20%

item_15825.Description: Pigs drinking this are advised not to think about the ingredients lest they become depressed. And possibly very angry.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Pig skill attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15825.Name: Pig Boost Potion 20%

item_15826.Description: A little tastier than usual potions, perhaps. (But not good-tasting, to be clear.)
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Deer skill attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15826.Name: Deer Boost Potion 20%

item_15827.Description: Milky. Hmm. Turns out that's not really a good thing when it comes to describing potion taste.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Cow skill attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15827.Name: Cow Boost Potion 20%

EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Giant Bat skill attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15828.Name: Giant Bat Boost Potion 20%

item_15829.Description: It smells awful and it leaves your tongue completely numb. So that's something.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Rabbit skill attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15829.Name: Rabbit Boost Potion 20%

item_15830.Description: A vaguely meat-flavored swill made all the more horrid with the addition of lumps of fur.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your Warden skill attacks deal +20% base damage
item_15830.Name: Warden Boost Potion 20%

item_15841.Description: Named for the god of knowledge, this potion lets you see a few seconds into the future! It is permanent, however, and some scribes of Imatia have been driven insane by what they see.
EffectDescs:
You can perceive where new monsters will spawn. They will appear as purple energy for 3 seconds before they actually appear.

This effect does not wear off, but whenever you die there's a 5% chance that it will end.
item_15841.Name: Imatia's Sight Potion

item_15842.Description: This pleasant beverage helps you digest cheese.
EffectDescs: Regenerate +10 power every 5 seconds (both in and out of combat). Lasts 1 hour or until no cheese is in your system, whichever comes first.
item_15842.Name: Mild Ratkin Digestif

item_15843.Description: This tasty beverage helps you digest cheese.
EffectDescs: Regenerate +20 power every 5 seconds (both in and out of combat). Lasts 1 hour or until no cheese is in your system, whichever comes first.
item_15843.Name: Potent Ratkin Digestif

item_15844.Description: This delicious beverage helps you digest cheese.
EffectDescs: Regenerate +30 power every 5 seconds (both in and out of combat). Lasts 1 hour or until no cheese is in your system, whichever comes first.
item_15844.Name: Amazing Ratkin Digestif

item_15845.Description: An appetizer intended to be eaten before the cheese course.
EffectDescs: Causes cheese effects to last 20 minutes longer. (Must be drunk before cheese is eaten!)
item_15845.Name: Simple Ratkin Aparatif

item_15846.Description: An appetizer intended to be eaten before the cheese course.
EffectDescs: Causes cheese effects to last 40 minutes longer. (Must be drunk before cheese is eaten!)
item_15846.Name: Tasty Ratkin Aparatif

item_15847.Description: An appetizer intended to be eaten before the cheese course.
EffectDescs: Causes cheese effects to last 60 minutes longer. (Must be drunk before cheese is eaten!)
item_15847.Name: Delicious Ratkin Aparatif

item_15848.Description: An extremely secret formula used by ratkin sages to predict when and where rodents will appear.
EffectDescs:
You can perceive newly-spawned rodents and rodent-kin 10 seconds before they actually appear.

The effect does not wear off, but whenever you die there's a 5% chance that it will end.
item_15848.Name: Potion of Rat Detection

EffectDescs: Recovers 1 health per second for 30 seconds.
item_15849.Name: Potion of Least Regeneration

item_15850.Description: A delayed-action potion which is tricky to use in stressful situations, and also tastes like bile.
item_15850.Name: Potion of Casual Healing

item_15851.Description: This was obviously intended to be a Potion of Universal Resistance, but the ingredients were added in the wrong order, resulting in a revolting soup with an unpredictable effect.
EffectDescs: Boosts mitigation of a random damage-type by 5 for 60 minutes. The effect mimics other potions and does not stack with them. (For instance if this potion boosts Poison resistance, it does not stack with a Potion of Poison Resistance.)
item_15851.Name: Potion of Random Resistance

item_15852.Description: A thick black paste that requires an iron stomach to drink. If you can keep it down, the potion protects from all types of damage, and even better, it can be combined with potions that protect against specific damage types.
EffectDescs: Boosts mitigation of all damage-types 5 for 60 minutes. This effect stacks with potions that provide resistance to a specific damage-type.
item_15852.Name: Potion of Universal Resistance

item_15853.Description: A delayed-action potion which is tricky to use in stressful situations, and also tastes like wet cardboard.
item_15853.Name: Potion of Casual Armoring

item_15854.Description: The not-quite-dead remains of an ooze. It's mainly used as an ingredient in other potions, but it does have a healing effect when drunk -- assuming you have the gastronomic experience to tolerate the flavor without vomiting.
item_15854.Name: Magic Ooze Syrup

item_15855.Description:
This healing potion can be drunk many times. Just leave a drop in the bottom and it will refill right before your eyes! The secret? It's made with a still-living ooze. Unfortunately, the ooze is so thick that the average person can't manage to drink it. Also unfortunately, the ooze takes a few seconds to take effect.

This potion is best known as the favorite drink of Grita the Arbitrarily Murderous, the feared rakshasa pirate. She says the potion is light on the stomach, allowing her to drink far more of it than regular healing potions. But she's a pirate (and a rakshasa to boot), so most people take that with a grain of salt.
item_15855.Name: Infinite Potion of Healing

item_15856.Description: This potion alters your eyes so they work better when there's not much light. It's an ancient recipe that's quite effective, but the revolting taste has kept it from becoming too popular.
EffectDescs: For 60 minutes, you can see better in low-light environments.
item_15856.Name: Potion of Night Vision

item_15857.Description: Useful primarily to mages, this apple-flavored potion causes explosions to be a little more particular about what they hit.
EffectDescs: For 60 minutes, you gain +10% Burst Accuracy
item_15857.Name: Potion of Burst Accuracy

item_15858.Description: This potion helps you think like an animal. If you have an animal companion this lets you communicate a bit more efficiently.
EffectDescs: For 60 minutes, all Animal Handling abilities cost 10% less Power to use.
item_15858.Name: Potion of Swift Animal Handling

item_15859.Description: Most people can't tell that this does anything at all. But it does have magic. Just not very good magic.
EffectDescs: For 60 minutes, any Minor Healing abilities used on you restore +1 Health
item_15859.Name: Potion of Extremely Minor Healing Receptiveness

item_15860.Description: This potion increases the size of your stomach by a very small amount. (This is usually not something to get too excited about.)
EffectDescs: For 60 minutes, you gain +10 Max Metabolism
item_15860.Name: Minor Stomach Expander Potion

item_15861.Description: A flask of flammable liquid. It doesn't deal much damage, but any flame will keep trolls from regenerating, and this flame lasts a long time.
EffectDescs: If used immediately before an attack, the attack will cause the target(s) to be covered in mild but long-burning flame.
item_15861.Name: Trollbane Oil

item_15862.Description: Blessed by a high priest of Au-Shin, this tube of liquid glows like a light.
EffectDescs: Boosts Max Health by 300% for 15 minutes. Must be an animal.
item_15862.Name: Warden Strength Drink

item_15863.Description: This clear liquid has bubbles in it that never seem to pop.
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, you lose Breath Meter half as quickly while underwater.
item_15863.Name: Water Breathing Potion

item_15864.Description: A slimy gunk that lets you move like an eel. (Swimming buff does not stack with other swimming-buff potions.)
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your underwater fast-swim speed is +6 and you gain +6 mitigation against Electricity
item_15864.Name: Eel Potion

item_15865.Description: Stinky sludge that lets you move like a shark. (Swimming buff does not stack with other swimming-buff potions.)
EffectDescs: For 30 minutes, your underwater fast-swim speed is +7 and your Max Breath is +10
item_15865.Name: Shark Potion

item_15866.Description:
A dollop of cold, fruit-flavored magical liquid that will change your wing-stype permanently. This item can melt.

NOTE: this changes an aspect of your character's appearance PERMANENTLY. Think before you drink!
EffectDescs: For fairies: randomly chooses a new wing shape and color from among a few possible styles.
item_15866.Name: Fae Wing-Change Potion (Types A&B)

item_15867.Description:
A dollop of cold, fruit-flavored magical liquid that will change your hairstyle permanently. This item can melt.

NOTE: this changes an aspect of your character's appearance PERMANENTLY. Think before you drink!
EffectDescs: For races with multiple hair styles: randomly chooses a new hair style. (Hair color is unchanged.)
item_15867.Name: Fae Hair Style Potion

item_15868.Description:
A dollop of cold, fruit-flavored magical liquid that will change your hair color permanently. This item can melt.

NOTE: this changes an aspect of your character's appearance PERMANENTLY. Think before you drink!
EffectDescs: For races with multiple hair colors: randomly chooses a new hair color. (Hair style is unchanged.)
item_15868.Name: Fae Hair Color Potion

item_15869.Description:
A dollop of cold, fruit-flavored magical liquid that will change your beard style permanently. This item can melt.

NOTE: this changes an aspect of your character's appearance PERMANENTLY. Think before you drink!
EffectDescs: For race/sex combinations with multiple beard styles: randomly chooses a new beard style. (Beard color is unchanged.)
item_15869.Name: Fae Beard Style Potion

item_15870.Description:
A dollop of cold, fruit-flavored magical liquid that will change your beard color permanently. This item can melt.

NOTE: this changes an aspect of your character's appearance PERMANENTLY. Think before you drink!
EffectDescs: For race/sex combinations with multiple beard colors: randomly chooses a new beard color. (Beard style is unchanged.)
item_15870.Name: Fae Beard Color Potion

item_15871.Description:
A dollop of cold, fruit-flavored magical liquid that will change your skin or fur color permanently. This item can melt.

NOTE: this changes an aspect of your character's appearance PERMANENTLY. Think before you drink!
EffectDescs: For races with multiple skintones: randomly chooses a new skintone.
item_15871.Name: Fae Skin Color Potion

item_15872.Description: A blend of fairy wings and secret ingredients that are quite difficult to digest due to their repulsiveness. It is banned in half of the fairy courts, and readily available in the other half.
EffectDescs: For fairies: restores up to 10 fae energy, but cannot not raise fae energy above 20.
item_15872.Name: Thin Fae Energy Potion

item_15873.Description: A blend of fairy wings and secret ingredients that are quite difficult to digest due to their repulsiveness. It is banned in half of the fairy courts, and readily available in the other half.
EffectDescs: For fairies: restores up to 20 fae energy, but cannot not raise fae energy above 20.
item_15873.Name: Thick Fae Energy Potion

item_15874.Description:
A dollop of cold, fruit-flavored magical liquid that will change your wing-style permanently. This item can melt.

NOTE: this changes an aspect of your character's appearance PERMANENTLY. Think before you drink!
EffectDescs: For fairies: randomly chooses a new wing shape and color from among a few possible styles.
item_15874.Name: Fae Wing-Change Potion (Types C&D)

item_15875.Description:
A dollop of cold, fruit-flavored magical liquid that will change your wing-style permanently. This item can melt.

NOTE: this changes an aspect of your character's appearance PERMANENTLY. Think before you drink!
EffectDescs: For fairies: randomly chooses a new wing shape and color from among a few possible styles.
item_15875.Name: Fae Wing-Change Potion (Types E&F)

item_15876.Description:
A dollop of cold, fruit-flavored magical liquid that will change your wing-style permanently. This item can melt.

NOTE: this changes an aspect of your character's appearance PERMANENTLY. Think before you drink!
EffectDescs: For fairies: randomly chooses a new wing shape and color from among a few possible styles.
item_15876.Name: Fae Wing-Change Potion (Types G&H)

item_15877.Description:
A dollop of cold, fruit-flavored magical liquid that will change your wing-style permanently. This item can melt.

NOTE: this changes an aspect of your character's appearance PERMANENTLY. Think before you drink!
EffectDescs: For fairies: randomly chooses a new wing color (of a certain style).
item_15877.Name: Fae Wing-Change Potion (Type I)

item_15878.Description: A lotion created by Moxie of the Crafting Caravan in order to make long distance fluttering less stressful when applied directly to the wings. Unfortunately, this formula only works on Fae.
EffectDescs: For fairies: Decreases flight power costs in and out of combat while gaining +1 flight speed for 2 hours.
item_15878.Name: Moxie's Flutter Butter

item_15879.Description:
A lotion created by Moxie of the Crafting Caravan in order to make long distance flight less stressful when applied directly to the wings. Unfortunately, this formula only works on druidic bird forms.
WARNING: Leaving bird form will cancel the effects of this lotion!
EffectDescs: For druidic bird forms: Decreases flight power costs in and out of combat while gaining +1 flight speed for 2 hours.
item_15879.Name: Moxie's Birdie Butter

item_15880.Description:
A lotion created by Moxie of the Crafting Caravan in order to make long distance flight less stressful when applied directly to the wings. Unfortunately, this formula only works on giant bats. Also, since giant bat wings are so large, the bottle contains fewer doses than the other butters, but it's more effective, too.
WARNING: Leaving giant bat form will cancel the effects of this lotion!
EffectDescs: For giant bats: Decreases flight power costs in and out of combat while gaining +2 flight speed for 2 hours.
item_15880.Name: Moxie's Bat Butter

item_15881.Description: A blend of fairy wings and secret ingredients that are quite difficult to digest due to their repulsiveness. It is banned in half of the fairy courts, and readily available in the other half.
EffectDescs: For fairies: restores up to 30 fae energy, but cannot not raise fae energy above 30.
item_15881.Name: Gooey Fae Energy Potion

item_15882.Description: A blend of fairy wings and secret ingredients that are quite difficult to digest due to their repulsiveness. It is banned in half of the fairy courts, and readily available in the other half.
EffectDescs: For fairies: restores up to 40 fae energy, but cannot not raise fae energy above 40.
item_15882.Name: Foamy Fae Energy Potion

item_15883.Description: A small metal cylinder with liquid sealed inside. There's a pull-tab on top to open it. The cylinder bears an image of a smiling Spring fairy. If you stare for a moment, she seems to mouth the cryptic words "Rez and Shine, You Live Again! Original Honey Flavor!"
EffectDescs: For fairies: raises Max Health +40. Restores 5 fae energy, but cannot not raise fae energy above 50.
item_15883.Name: Rez and Shine

item_15884.Description: A time-bending drink that allows one to perceive fairies before they exist.
EffectDescs:
You can perceive newly-spawned fairies and fae creatures 10 seconds before they actually appear.

The effect does not wear off, but whenever you die there's a 5% chance that it will end.
item_15884.Name: Potion of Fae Sight

item_15885.Description: A syrup of exotic tree seeds that will better attune your senses to the plant realm.
EffectDescs:
You can perceive newly-spawned plant creatures 10 seconds before they actually appear.

The effect does not wear off, but whenever you die there's a 5% chance that it will end.
item_15885.Name: Potion of Plantsight

item_16003.Description: A large block of animal fat.
item_16003.Name: Typical Animal Fat

item_16004.Description: A large unbroken block of high-quality animal fat.
item_16004.Name: Smooth Animal Fat

item_16022.Description: A useful form of rendered fat.
item_16022.Name: Crude Tallow

item_16023.Description: Rendered fat that's good for most of your everyday utility-fat needs.
item_16023.Name: Nice Tallow

item_16041.Description: A bit of string that will (technically) burn.
item_16041.Name: Shoddy Wick

item_16042.Description: Wax-coated string for use in a candle.
item_16042.Name: Crude Wick

item_16043.Description: Braided string that will burn clean. For use in a fancy candle.
item_16043.Name: Nice Wick

item_16101.Description:
A tiny short-lived light used for decoration.

Tealights are non-interactible. They last for 5 minutes. You can deploy up to 5 tealights at a time.
item_16101.Name: Tealight

item_16103.Description: A lump of wax that can be affixed to the head to provide light. Don't worry: it only looks dangerous because of how dangerous it is.
EffectDescs: Causes your head to emit light for 15 minutes. May inflict mild scalding.
item_16103.Name: Head Candle

item_16161.Description:
A musty outdoor scent that makes you want to go outdoors and hit stuff.

This candle lasts for 5 minutes and any number of people can appreciate it. You can only deploy 1 candle at a time.
EffectDescs: Boosts Crushing Damage +1% for 90 minutes. (You can only gain one candle buff at a time.)
item_16161.Name: Shoddy Brisk Candle

item_16162.Description:
A gripping outdoor scent that will make you excited to grip things.

This candle lasts for 5 minutes and any number of people can appreciate it. You can only deploy 1 candle at a time.
EffectDescs: Boosts Crushing Damage +2% for 90 minutes. (You can only gain one candle buff at a time.)
item_16162.Name: Rough Brisk Candle

item_16163.Description:
A no-nonsense outdoor scent that makes you want to go out and crush things.

This candle lasts for 5 minutes and any number of people can appreciate it. You can only deploy 1 candle at a time.
EffectDescs: Boosts Crushing Damage +3% for 90 minutes. (You can only gain one candle buff at a time.)
item_16163.Name: Crude Brisk Candle

item_16164.Description:
A feral assault on the nose that enhances your need to fight!

This candle lasts for 5 minutes and any number of people can appreciate it. You can only deploy 1 candle at a time.
EffectDescs: Boosts Crushing Damage +4% for 90 minutes. (You can only gain one candle buff at a time.)
item_16164.Name: Decent Brisk Candle

item_16165.Description:
An eye-watering odor that urges you to go get physically violent.

This candle lasts for 5 minutes and any number of people can appreciate it. You can only deploy 1 candle at a time.
EffectDescs: Boosts Crushing Damage +5% for 90 minutes. (You can only gain one candle buff at a time.)
item_16165.Name: Nice Brisk Candle

item_16166.Description:
Somewhere between a foul odor and a pleasant one, this amps your adrenal system for fighting.

This candle lasts for 5 minutes and any number of people can appreciate it. You can only deploy 1 candle at a time.
EffectDescs: Boosts Crushing Damage +6% for 90 minutes. (You can only gain one candle buff at a time.)
item_16166.Name: Quality Brisk Candle

item_16167.Description:
An almost-malignant odor that sends your body into a ferocious snarl.

This candle lasts for 5 minutes and any number of people can appreciate it. You can only deploy 1 candle at a time.
EffectDescs: Boosts Crushing Damage +7% for 90 minutes. (You can only gain one candle buff at a time.)
item_16167.Name: Great Brisk Candle

item_16168.Description:
A viceral odor experience that causes you to clench your fists in exuberance.

This candle lasts for 5 minutes and any number of people can appreciate it. You can only deploy 1 candle at a time.
EffectDescs: Boosts Crushing Damage +8% for 90 minutes. (You can only gain one candle buff at a time.)
item_16168.Name: Amazing Brisk Candle

item_16176.Description:
All the smells of a scrub tree in a swamp to help you get into a natural mindset.

This candle lasts for 5 minutes and any number of people can appreciate it. You can only deploy 1 candle at a time.
EffectDescs: Boosts Nature Damage +1% for 90 minutes. (You can only gain one candle buff at a time.)
item_16176.Name: Shoddy Woodland Candle

item_16177.Description:
The smell of bark and pollen isn't pleasant, but it turns your thoughts to nature.

This candle lasts for 5 minutes and any number of people can appreciate it. You can only deploy 1 candle at a time.
EffectDescs: Boosts Nature Damage +2% for 90 minutes. (You can only gain one candle buff at a time.)
item_16177.Name: Rough Woodland Candle

item_16178.Description:
A not-quite-pleasant pine candle that focuses your instincts toward nature.

This candle lasts for 5 minutes and any number of people can appreciate it. You can only deploy 1 candle at a time.
