A dull yellow-green stone. Used in magic, it can pierce the barrier between life and death.

Associated Primary Skill: Necromancy
item_18042.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have Necromancy enchantments.
item_18042.Name: Serpentine

item_18043.Description: A scintillating gemstone. Used in magic, it can protect against death.
item_18043.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have random enchantments.
item_18043.Name: Diamond

item_18044.Description: A bright blue stone, almost teal in color. In magic, it is associated with beaches and waves.
item_18044.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have skill-agnostic enchantments.
item_18044.Name: Turquoise

item_18045.Description: A beautiful blue stone. In magic it is associated with flight and the sky.
item_18045.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have skill-agnostic enchantments.
item_18045.Name: Sapphire

item_18046.Description: This green crystal is a type of beryl. Used in magic, it is associated with perfection, richness, and deities.
item_18046.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have skill-agnostic enchantments.
item_18046.Name: Emerald

item_18047.Description: This is an orange variety of beryl. Used in magic, it is associated with tailoring. It is the favored color of goblins.
item_18047.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have skill-agnostic enchantments.
item_18047.Name: Morganite

item_18048.Description:
This pale yellow crystal is extremely reflective from certain angles. In magic, it is associated with growth.

When used in Augment Extraction, Sunstone can extract powers that have no specific skill association.
item_18048.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have skill-agnostic enchantments.
item_18048.Name: Sunstone

item_18049.Description: This beautiful golden rock has deep striations. In magic, it is associated with animals, hunting, and livestock.
item_18049.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have skill-agnostic enchantments.
item_18049.Name: Tiger's Eye

item_18050.Description: This greenish stone seems to have many other colors embedded in it. While some -- especially orcs -- find it beautiful, others find it disconcerting or even ugly. In magic it is associated with curses and the evil eye.
item_18050.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have skill-agnostic enchantments.
item_18050.Name: Opal

item_18051.Description:
A clear variety of beryl. It is not particularly powerful in magic, but it can be used as a sort of energy dampener.

When used in Augment Extraction, Goshenite can extract powers that have no specific skill association.
item_18051.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have skill-agnostic enchantments.
item_18051.Name: Goshenite

item_18052.Description: This white gem with purple streaks is exceptionally strong and makes very resilient jewelry. In magic, it is likewise associated with toughness.
item_18052.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have skill-agnostic enchantments.
item_18052.Name: Danburite

item_18053.Description: Deep crimson in color, this valuable gem is used in magic to ensure good fortune.
item_18053.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have skill-agnostic enchantments.
item_18053.Name: Ruby

item_18054.Description:
A deep blue gem evocative of dark stormy oceans or winter skies. In magic it enhances musical skill.

Associated Primary Skill: Bard
item_18054.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have Bard enchantments.
item_18054.Name: Azurite

item_18055.Description: A beautiful orb that grew inside an oyster or other mollusc. While geologists don't consider this a gem, jewelers do. It can be used in magic to convey water-related benefits.
item_18055.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have skill-agnostic enchantments.
item_18055.Name: Pearl

item_18056.Description: An incredibly rare form of pearl. It can be used in very-high-end jewelrymaking, and alchemists prize it above all other gems. Geologists, for their part, don't even consider it a gem at all.
item_18056.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have skill-agnostic enchantments.
item_18056.Name: Black Pearl

item_18181.Description: A magical diamond that is flowing with fae power.
item_18181.Name: Winterprize

item_18182.Description: A magically enhanced piece of fluorite.
item_18182.Name: Vervadium

item_18183.Description: A large pretty piece of pulsing crystal. It's pleasantly warm to the touch.
item_18183.Name: Glowy Yellow Crystal

item_18184.Description: Supposedly taken from the dwarven queen Carlosta, this ruby is quite valuable, but otherwise unremarkable.
item_18184.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have random enchantments.
item_18184.Name: Carlosta Ruby

item_18185.Description: This piece of warm, pulsing crystal has been coated in some sort of powder, making it safe to touch.
item_18185.Name: Coated Glowy Yellow Crystal

item_18186.Description: A warm crystal that seems to constantly grow and shrink.
item_18186.Name: Semi-Real Hassium

item_18201.Description: A pretty gem with dark green bands, it's well known for aiding magical communication. This particular gem has been infused with a rune that attunes it to cattle when used in crafting.
item_18201.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have Cow enchantments.
item_18201.Name: Cow Malachite

item_18202.Description: A pretty gem with dark green bands, it's well known for aiding magical communication. This particular gem has been infused with a rune that attunes it to the needs of deer when used in crafting.
item_18202.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have Deer enchantments.
item_18202.Name: Deer Malachite

item_18203.Description: A pretty gem with dark green bands, it's well known for aiding magical communication. This particular gem has been infused with a rune that attunes it to pigs when used in crafting.
item_18203.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have Pig enchantments.
item_18203.Name: Pig Malachite

item_18204.Description: A pretty gem with dark green bands, it's well known for aiding magical communication. This particular gem has been infused with a rune that attunes it to spiders when used in crafting.
item_18204.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have Spider enchantments.
item_18204.Name: Spider Malachite

item_18205.Description: A dark red stone, known for its curative properties. This particular stone has been attuned to the First Aid skill if used in crafting.
item_18205.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have First Aid enchantments.
item_18205.Name: First Aid Garnet

item_18206.Description: A small crystal made up of black and white bands. Used in magic, it guards against physical dangers. This particular onyx has been attuned to Armor Patching when used in crafting.
item_18206.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have Armor Patching enchantments.
item_18206.Name: Armor Patching Onyx

item_18207.Description: A pretty gem with dark green bands, it's well known for aiding magical communication. This particular gem has been infused with a rune that attunes it to bats when used in crafting.
item_18207.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have Giant Bat enchantments.
item_18207.Name: Bat Malachite

item_18208.Description: A pretty gem with dark green bands, it's well known for aiding magical communication. This particular gem has been infused with a rune that attunes it to rabbits when used in crafting.
item_18208.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have Rabbit enchantments.
item_18208.Name: Rabbit Malachite

item_18209.Description: A small yellow topaz. An incredibly versatile magical stone. This particular piece has been infused with a rune that attunes it to Fairy Magic, giving crafted items a chance to include one or more Fairy Magic powers (with the rest being Mentalism powers).
item_18209.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have a chance to include Fairy Magic enchantments (in addition to, or instead of, Mentalism enchantments).
item_18209.Name: Fairy Magic Topaz

item_18210.Description: A soft blue rock. It's useful in curatives and curse removal potions. This particular gem has been infused with a rune that attunes it to foxes when used in crafting.
item_18210.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have Spirit Fox enchantments.
item_18210.Name: Spirit Fox Lapis

item_18301.Description: This small gem is brownish orange. It has been tuned as an amplifier for certain tailoring recipes.
item_18301.Name: Maximized Sardonyx

item_18302.Description: A small crystal made up of black and white bands. This particular gem has been tuned to act as an amplifier for certain leatherworking recipes.
item_18302.Name: Maximized Onyx

item_18303.Description: A small black stone. It has been tuned as an amplifier for certain toolcrafting recipes.
item_18303.Name: Maximized Obsidian

item_18304.Description: A blue-green stone. It has been tuned as an amplifier for certain armorsmithing recipes.
item_18304.Name: Maximized Aquamarine

item_18332.Description:
A massive yellow topaz. An incredibly versatile magical stone.

Associated Primary Skill: Mentalism
item_18332.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in equipment-crafting recipes to create items that have Mentalism enchantments.
item_18332.Name: Massive Topaz

item_19001.Description: Rita asked you to deliver this soap to Helena, who lives in the ruins of Castle Eltibule.
item_19001.Name: Herbal Soap

item_19002.Description: This bean has little prongs growing out of it that kind of look like horns.
item_19002.Name: Demon Bean

item_19003.Description: A rooty vegetable heart. Would probably be great in a salad.
item_19003.Name: Salmpo Heart

item_19005.Description: A small sack of foul-smelling white dust. Echur instructed you not to eat it, but that shouldn't be a problem.
item_19005.Name: Unrefined Cranium Powder

item_19006.Description: A handful of odorous twinkling flowers. Cute, but a little too gimmicky.
item_19006.Name: Flitterbies

item_19007.Description: A pack full of extremely small woman's clothing, plus blankets and some costume jewelry.
item_19007.Name: Sarina's Backpack

item_19008.Description: A grisly paw hacked off of The Mauler.
item_19008.Name: The Mauler's Claw

item_19010.Description: Mu asked you to deliver this to a Myconian named Poe.
item_19010.Name: Mu's Message Spore

item_19012.Description: This bundle of sporelings should be delivered to a myconian named Yoy.
item_19012.Name: Backup Sporelings

item_19013.Description: It's a partially-acid-melted shield without any straps to keep it on.
item_19013.Name: Melted and Broken Shield

item_19014.Description: It's a note to Landri the Cold, an elf in Kur Mountains. It reads, "You have not met me, and I cannot reveal myself, but I am a fellow theoretician, and I beg your help. I believe I can tap a portal to other planes of existence, and the plane of ice is very accessible here. I intend to use the Galkun technique to open the wormhole, and power it via ordinary ice lichen." (The note goes on for some length, in increasing technical detail, before ending with a perfunctory request for verification of the plan.)
item_19014.Name: Letter to Landri the Cold

item_19015.Description: A lead cup with a hefty weight and some cheap jewels on it. As you hold it, it grows unnaturally warm to the touch.
item_19015.Name: Necromancer's Goblet

item_19016.Description: A chunk of a weird giant mushroom. It reeks of death, and you're pretty sure it has no practical use.
item_19016.Name: Giant Mushroom Sample

item_19017.Description: A small poorly-made tiara, sized for a large rat or smallish dog. It seems utterly non-magical.
item_19017.Name: Squeaky's Tiara

item_19018.Description: It's an official letter from Praetor Ballard, demanding that a Human named Charles Thompson leave Serbule's surroundings forever... or face death.
item_19018.Name: Praetor's Orders

item_19020.Description: A sack of millet from a strange plant.
item_19020.Name: Gratflower Millet

item_19021.Description: A rakshasa's tail ring. It's not magical. It is inscribed, "to Sinda, the explorer supreme."
item_19021.Name: Sinda's Tail Ring

item_19022.Description: A sage's personal diary. It doesn't contain any useful lore or anything, it's just ramblings about his personal life.
item_19022.Name: Journal of Sir Villas Wake

item_19023.Description: A lovely navel ring with a tourmaline in it, apparently designed to calm intense anger.
item_19023.Name: Oritania's Navel Ring

item_19024.Description: The skull of a dead necromancer.
item_19024.Name: Lomas's Skull

item_19025.Description: A large gear that came out of a very large golem. It's bent and has no obvious purpose.
item_19025.Name: Cranial Gear

item_19026.Description: A small piece of bone inscribed with a dwarven rune for eternal sleep. It doesn't look very useful to you.
item_19026.Name: Preservative Rune

item_19027.Description: The skull of a ghoul that invaded from a realm of evil.
item_19027.Name: Skull of Maligno

item_19028.Description: A prism that has been inscribed with weird symbols. You don't think it would be useful for regular prism-related activities.
item_19028.Name: Archaic Prism

item_19029.Description: It's an old note. "Relamir: if you read this, get out of here! The frog men came again... and they killed the guests and staff. There's nobody left but me, and I'm leaving. Fuck this island, fuck this whole inn idea, fuck money, fuck the ocean, fuck everything. I'll pay you the money I owe you within a decade, I promise. - Roolaustus"
item_19029.Name: Old Owner's Note

item_19030.Description:
It's very light, and very cold, and very fragile.

(Note: if this item is held by someone not on the appropriate quest, it will quickly evaporate.)
item_19030.Name: Lydia's Soul

item_19031.Description:
A ring that can be used to 'sign' messaging stones as Lord Eltibule.

(Note: if this item is held by someone not on the appropriate quest, it will crumble to dust.)
item_19031.Name: Eltibule's Signet Ring

item_19032.Description: It's labeled 'bear repellent.' It smells spicy. You opt not to taste it.
item_19032.Name: Bear Repellent

item_19033.Description: A stinky flower. It's not going to be useful in bouquets, that's for sure.
item_19033.Name: Rotflower

item_19034.Description: A letter written by Sirine. You're supposed to give it to Yetta in Eltibule.
item_19034.Name: Letter to Yetta

item_19035.Description:
"Payment: 3 RTC
To: Tal-Saka (outcast rakshasa)
Reason: assistance in interpreting notes about Transmutation."

It's been formally approved by a Lt. Flakis.
item_19035.Name: Invoice for Tal-Saka

item_19037.Description: It's a large, gaudy belt buckle with a hand-painted scene of a man chopping lumber.
item_19037.Name: Paul's Lucky Buckle

item_19038.Description: A bottle with five small areas to hold dirt.
item_19038.Name: Soil Sample Container

item_19039.Description: It's an old worn shovel with a small handle. It doesn't seem very special to you.
item_19039.Name: "Spadey"

item_19040.Description: A brooch with an emerald inlaid in the middle. It's too dinged up to be valuable, but it's still pretty.
item_19040.Name: Emerald Brooch

item_19041.Description: A delicate glass star painted red and gold.
item_19041.Name: Stolen Tree Star

item_19042.Description: A tuft of fur from a manticore 'mane'.
item_19042.Name: Manticore Mane

item_19043.Description: A hacked-off piece of a rakshasa's ear.
item_19043.Name: Rakshasa Ear

item_19044.Description: A chapter from an adventure novel.
item_19044.Name: 'Leeka and the Blade Trials' Chapter 1

item_19045.Description: A chapter from an adventure novel.
item_19045.Name: 'Leeka and the Blade Trials' Chapter 2

item_19046.Description: A chapter from an adventure novel.
item_19046.Name: 'Leeka and the Blade Trials' Chapter 3

item_19047.Description: A chapter from an adventure novel.
item_19047.Name: 'Leeka and the Blade Trials' Chapter 4

item_19048.Description: A chapter from an adventure novel.
item_19048.Name: 'Leeka and the Blade Trials' Chapter 5

item_19049.Description: A chapter from an adventure novel.
item_19049.Name: 'Leeka and the Blade Trials' Chapter 6

item_19050.Description: Bits of ground up hippo hair. Very itchy.
item_19050.Name: Itching Powder

item_19051.Description: It doesn't seem to do anything, but it's definitely magical. Huh.
item_19051.Name: Spoon of Necromancy

item_19052.Description: These were probably decent tassels at some point -- for what, it's impossible to say -- but now they're covered in blood and pus and other fluids.
item_19052.Name: Tassels of Gulagra

item_19053.Description: A translucent handkerchief from a ghost. It should have turned into ectoplasm when separated from the ghost, but somehow it hasn't. Eerie.
item_19053.Name: Ghostly Handkerchief

item_19055.Description: A drop of blood from a gnasher.
item_19055.Name: Bloodsoaker's Blood

item_19056.Description: The mandibles from a particularly nasty insect.
item_19056.Name: Chitterface's Mandibles

item_19057.Description: The teeth of a very mean bear.
item_19057.Name: Grottofang's Teeth

item_19058.Description: A pebble found on a yeti.
item_19058.Name: Urraghur's Lucky Rock

item_19059.Description: It says, "Karnag, your family loves you. Please don't do this to yourself! There must be another way. You will miss your son's first words..." the rest is scribbled out except a bit at the bottom written in a different style, "Karnag Has Graduated Wizard School! Signed my mother."
item_19059.Name: Karnag's Imaginary Diploma

item_19060.Description: It's covered in gibberish -- there are words, but they don't seem to make sentences.
item_19060.Name: Elerimon's Notes

item_19063.Description: The perfumed note says, "W: My love for you grows each night I spend alone. I long to touch you. Your beard, your lips, your... tee hee... meet me tonight behind the kennels. I cannot survive another night without your touch! And don't worry -- the messenger is safe. - E"
item_19063.Name: Note to Willem

item_19064.Description: It's a tooth from a huge Tor-Urak.
item_19064.Name: Fluffy's Tooth

item_19065.Description: A drop of magical darkness, trapped in a vial.
item_19065.Name: Mote of Darkness

item_19066.Description: A keg of Troll's Lip, one of the cheapest and vilest beers in all the Council Lands.
item_19066.Name: Troll's Lip Beer Keg

item_19067.Description: The heart of a desert-living drakeworm.
item_19067.Name: Vurrkan's Heart

item_19068.Description: A delicate flower that seems simultaneously warm and cold.
item_19068.Name: Coldkiss Flower

item_19069.Description: An ordinary Council that's had weird little marks etched into it.
item_19069.Name: Cursed Coin

item_19070.Description: A magical bottle that analyzes water. Use it while standing in the center of a pool of water.
item_19070.Name: Water Sample Analyzer

item_19071.Description: Full of anatomical drawings of rat-people, and musings in arcane Goblinese.
item_19071.Name: Bogaku's Sixteenth Notebook

item_19072.Description: Looks like meat. Gross meat, but ... just meat.
item_19072.Name: Escaped-Snail Meat

item_19073.Description: An organ cut out of a large scorpion.
item_19073.Name: Scorpion Poison Gland

item_19074.Description: A gross dead scorpion. It's very heavy.
item_19074.Name: Decently-Scary Scorpion Corpse

item_19075.Description: It says, "I hereby acknowledge that Vangreef's debt to me is paid." It has an elven signature symbol and the letters "SS". Then at the bottom is another note by the author: "Don't waste that spell, Vangreef. Even if you could afford a second casting, I can't recast it until the moon waxes anew. Be smart and fast or your whole gang WILL die down there. And nobody will be able to rescue you."
item_19075.Name: Spell Receipt

item_19076.Description: The shell of a dead scorpion. It's very smelly.
item_19076.Name: Scorpion Carapace

item_19077.Description: A small vial that reeks of urine and other unpleasant chemicals. This is an unadulterated "pure" dose of the drug, straight from the alchemists' workbench.
item_19077.Name: Telka's Teeth (Clean Sample)

item_19078.Description: A sticky blob of "silk" from a sand worm. It's not what you'd call silky.
item_19078.Name: Sand Worm Silk

item_19079.Description: It seems like an ordinary giant spider leg.
item_19079.Name: Tornado Spider Leg

item_19080.Description: A plate-like protrusion from a carnivine.
item_19080.Name: Carnivine Tooth

item_19081.Description: A thorny protrusion from a spriggan weed or plant.
item_19081.Name: Spriggan Weed Tooth

item_19082.Description: A freeze-dried beetle of some sort.
item_19082.Name: Candied Ice Beetle

item_19084.Description: The horn of a fae rhino.
item_19084.Name: Chipped Fae Rhino Horn

item_19085.Description: A hot piece of magical crystal.
item_19085.Name: Fiery Sound Crystal

item_19086.Description: A cold piece of magical crystal.
item_19086.Name: Icy Sound Crystal

item_19087.Description: A warm piece of magical crystal.
item_19087.Name: Natural Sound Crystal

item_19088.Description: An old book written by an elf about how to use dwarven engineering in elven designs.
item_19088.Name: Dwarven Circuit Principles and Applications for Elven Dweomers, 5th Edition

item_19089.Description: A care package including some clover, salt licks, sealed documents, and a strange device you don't recognize.
item_19089.Name: Care Package for Suspicious Cow

item_19090.Description: A care package including mushroom substrate, a bag of beads, and several paper notes.
item_19090.Name: Care Package for Norbert

item_19091.Description: A care package including sacks of Councils, odd-colored dyes, and a note.
item_19091.Name: Care Package for Lumpfuzz

item_19092.Description: A care package consisting entirely of mushrooms.
item_19092.Name: Care Package for Trekker

item_19093.Description: The beak of a very large turkey.
item_19093.Name: Gobblejack's Beak

item_19094.Description: A butterfly that's been captured alive. It doesn't look happy... but it's alive!
item_19094.Name: Stunned Rose-Mourning Butterfly

item_19095.Description: A net designed to catch and contain Rose-mourning butterflies. (Keep this in your inventory when harvesting the butterflies to capture them alive.)
item_19095.Name: Rose-Mourning Butterfly Net

item_19096.Description: These extra-large flower seeds are coated in sticky honey, which is in turn coated in pollen.
item_19096.Name: Honeyed Seeds

item_19098.Description: A shark fin, freshly hacked off.
item_19098.Name: Sacrificial Shark Fin

item_19099.Description: A lump from a very large ooze.
item_19099.Name: Sacrificial Ooze

item_19100.Description: The heart of a massive snail.
item_19100.Name: Sacrificial Snail Meat

item_19101.Description: The lung of a newly-sacrificied mega scray. (NOTE: not yet implemented; does nothing!)
item_19101.Name: Sacrificial Lung

item_19102.Description: A special pemphredo eye adjusted to receive messages from a nearby source, instead of a distant one.
item_19102.Name: Asterion's Eye

item_19103.Description: These pages of parchment are covered in symbols that make no sense to you.
item_19103.Name: Claudia's Notes

item_19201.Description: A map that supposedly leads to a "war cache", an underground bunker from before the Sand War.
item_19201.Name: Ilmari War Cache Map

item_19202.Description: A map that supposedly leads to a "war cache", an underground bunker from before the Sand War.
item_19202.Name: Ilmari War Cache Map

item_19301.Description: A bar of magic-amplifying Xedrite metal. Some unknown metallurgy has been performed on it.
item_19301.Name: Weaponized Xedrite

item_19302.Description: A bar of magic-amplifying Xedrite metal. Some unknown metallurgy has been performed on it.
item_19302.Name: Weaponized Xedrite

item_21555.Description: A coarse variety of whisky that's commonly drunk in the dwarven military.
item_21555.Name: Burn-Throat

item_21556.Description: Fermented cactus juice with a complex taste. This batch is pretty vile, but barely drinkable.
item_21556.Name: Dhakmar's Shoddy Tequila

item_21557.Description: This is some of the worst gin ever. But it is technically not fatal to drink.
item_21557.Name: Dhakmar's Terrible Gin

item_21558.Description: A favorite of conscripted trolls. The name 'bourbon' is a misnomer since no corn is used. You don't want to know what is used.
item_21558.Name: Bootleg Troll Bourbon

item_21561.Description: Someone has mixed good egg nog with cheap vodka. (This mixed drink is treated as a beer/wine.)
item_21561.Name: Spiked Egg Nog

item_21562.Description: A mantis invention: watered-down gin, fruit-flavored rum, and 'secret flavorings' which are probably just mint. A casino favorite! ... because it's usually free. (This mixed drink is treated as a beer/wine.)
item_21562.Name: Psychic Cricket

item_21708.Description: This bourbon needs to be stored in a cave for three hours before it can be made drinkable. (You do not need to remain in the cave or online the whole time.)

item_21751.Name: Aged Potato Vodka

item_21801.Description: A very rough alcoholic beverage. Some say you grow to like the taste, but others say that's just your tastebuds dying from the pain.
item_21801.Name: Potato Vodka

item_21802.Description: Apple brandy, with a distinctive apple taste and a strong kick. A longtime favorite of rural humans.
item_21802.Name: Applejack

item_21803.Description: A sweet, relatively palatable variety of vodka. Although it's a traditional dwarven drink, it long ago fell out of favor, and these days dwarves only use it for cooking.
item_21803.Name: Beet Vodka

item_21804.Description: Sweet and strong, with the distinctive odor of molasses. In far-off lands, ranalon produce and drink rum in tremendous quantities, but it's less common -- and less delicious -- in Alharth.
item_21804.Name: Pale Rum

item_21805.Description: A simple variety of whisky made from barley. It's drinkable and has a tolerable flavor.
item_21805.Name: Whisky

item_21806.Description: Fermented cactus juice with a complex taste. This variety has been aged to make it more drinkable. (It's "more" drinkable, but still not "very" drinkable -- it's an acquired taste.) The stereotypical drink of rakshasa desert bandits.
item_21806.Name: Tequila

item_21807.Description: Pleasant, slightly citrusy, but with a distinctive bitterness too. It's said to be the favorite hard liquor of elves, but since elves mostly drink wine, that's not much praise.
item_21807.Name: Dry Gin

item_21808.Description: Made from fermented corn mash, this is very mellow and drinkable. This is the favored drink of Councilwoman Sereel "The Steel" Avenbule. She holds a bourbon competition each year in Vidaria.
item_21808.Name: Bourbon

item_21851.Description: Although there might be delicious varieties of strawberry wine out there somewhere, this is not it: the strawberry flavor is undermined by a grassy taste.
item_21851.Name: Strawberry Wine

item_21852.Description: A drinkable wine, but with a slightly musky taste and odor. This is definitely not the kind of wine that elves drink in Verta! But it's not horrible.
item_21852.Name: Concord Wine

item_21853.Description: With notes of citrus and sweetness, this is a decent table wine.
item_21853.Name: Orange Wine

item_21854.Description: Given that it was made from carrots, this wine is... surprisingly good!
item_21854.Name: Carrot Wine

item_21855.Description: A buttery, banana-flavored wine that's quite a mouthful.
item_21855.Name: Banana Wine

item_21857.Description: A very dry wine that's quite drinkable.
item_21857.Name: Rice Wine

item_21858.Description: A dry wine. It has a slightly piney smell, but the aroma is not pleasant.
item_21858.Name: Juniper Wine

item_22001.Description: A chunk of ore that could be used to make silver equipment and jewelry. It can also be used in formulas that augment jewelry.
item_22001.Name: Silver Ore

item_22002.Description: A chunk of fool's gold. It has many alchemical uses, and is great for making costume jewelry. It is often used in formulas that augment jewelry.
item_22002.Name: Pyrite

item_22003.Description: A chunk of ore that could be used to make gold equipment and jewelry. It is also used in formulas that augment jewelry.
item_22003.Name: Gold Ore

item_22004.Description: A chunk of dense (yet brittle) iridium. It's used in the creation of acid-proof armor and strange robotic constructs. It can also be used to augment jewelry.
item_22004.Name: Iridium

item_22005.Description: A tiny bit of unrefined ore. You'd need a bunch of these to make anything useful from them.
item_22005.Name: Gold Nugget

item_22006.Description: A chunk of weird ore. It's a potent conductor of certain magics and is used in specialized armor and weapons.
item_22006.Name: Paladium

item_22007.Description: A chunk of brittle ore. It is extremely hard to smith, but alchemists have found some uses for it.
item_22007.Name: Tungsten

item_22008.Description: A chunk of soft metal. While it's not particularly strong, it's very easy for smiths to work with, so it has uses in specialized armors and weapons. Fletchers use it to create dense arrows.
item_22008.Name: Copper Ore

item_22009.Description: A soft strange metal, quite magical, and very poisonous. It has many uses.
item_22009.Name: Cinnabar

item_22010.Description: A chunk of pointy ore. Its most common use is by blacksmiths, who can add fireproofing to armor with it.
item_22010.Name: Stibnite

item_22011.Description: A chunk of weird ore that can conduct powerful magics, but requires extreme skill to craft with.
item_22011.Name: Rhodium

item_22012.Description: A chunk of metal with magic-amplification properties. It is used as a form of currency among some goblins due to hyper-inflation of goblin paper money.
item_22012.Name: Xedrite

item_22013.Description: A small lump of metal said to form in areas of high latent magic. It can be combined with other ores for advanced smithing, and alchemists have their own strange uses for it.
item_22013.Name: Molybdenum

item_22501.Description: A small metal band used in making casks.
item_22501.Name: Quarter Hoop

item_22502.Description: A metal band used in making casks.
item_22502.Name: Medium Hoop

item_22503.Description: A large metal band used in making casks.
item_22503.Name: Bilge Hoop

item_22504.Description: Metal pins used mainly in armorsmithing.
item_22504.Name: Rivets

item_22505.Description: A metal clamp used by toolmakers and weaponsmiths.
item_22505.Name: Vise

item_22506.Description: A small thin piece of metal covered in a grid of holes. It is used by flower arrangers.
item_22506.Name: Thin Mesh Grate

item_22507.Description: A piece of metal covered in a grid of holes. It is used by flower arrangers.
item_22507.Name: Mesh Grate

item_22508.Description: A piece of metal that's especially strong.
item_22508.Name: Orcish Steel

item_23201.Name: Goblin Orders

item_23202.Description: This is a work-order from a goblin chieftan to a goblin mason guild detailing a home expansion. It's terribly interesting.
item_23202.Name: Translated Builder Instructions

item_23203.Description: This is an old battle plan for some intra-goblin skirmish. It might be worth something to somebody... but probably not much in any case.
item_23203.Name: Translated Battle Plan

item_23204.Description: This is sloppily transliterated goblin poetry. It scans poorly, the similes make no sense after translation, and the topic of the poem is toenails. But it is poetry, technically.
item_23204.Name: Translated Goblin Poetry

item_23301.Description: A simple scroll written in both Orcish and Human. The Human title is "Demands of the Deceased".
item_23301.Name: "Demands of The Deceased"

item_23302.Description: A simple scroll with both Orcish and Human words on it.
item_23302.Name: Orcish Language Reference

item_23303.Description: A simple scroll written in Orcish, with images of sword techniques.
item_23303.Name: Orcish Scroll About Swords

item_23304.Description: A simple book in Orcish. It has lots of pictures of weapons.
item_23304.Name: Orcish Book On Weapons

item_23305.Description: A simple book in Orcish. It seems to contain many prayers or chants, plus woodcut images of orcish armies killing people.
item_23305.Name: Orcish Book With Prayers

item_23306.Description: A simple book in Orcish. It looks like it might be a fiction novel -- very rare among orcs!
item_23306.Name: Orcish Novel

item_23308.Description: A book written in Orcish. It has many pictures of spears, polearms, and swords.
item_23308.Name: Orcish Weaponry Treatise

item_23310.Description: A scroll in Orcish. It seems to be about orcish wizards.
item_23310.Name: Orcish Scroll About Thaumaturges

item_23311.Description: A book written in Orcish. It's clearly a guide to first aid.
item_23311.Name: Orcish Field Medicine Guide

item_23312.Description: A book written in Orcish. The woodcuts appear to depict the other major races such as humans, elves, and dwarves.
item_23312.Name: Orcish Race Guide

item_23313.Description: A scroll in Orcish. There is one picture depicting a human wizard.
item_23313.Name: Orcish Scroll About Magic

item_23315.Description: A book written in Orcish. It seems to show techniques for the knife.
item_23315.Name: Orcish Book On Knife Tricks

item_23316.Description: A book written in Orcish. From the diagrams, it seems to be about magic.
item_23316.Name: Orcish Book About Thaumaturgy

item_23317.Description: A book written in Orcish. In the title, you recognize the orcish word for Gotkul, a famous orc general that commands a massive army in the Crone Hegemony.
item_23317.Name: Orcish Book About Gotkul

item_23318.Description: A book written in Orcish. It seems to be about war machines.
item_23318.Name: Orcish Book About Trebuchets

item_23319.Description: A book written in Orcish. Judging by the pictures, it seems to be about Tast, the god of war and armies.
item_23319.Name: Orcish Book About Tast

item_23321.Description: A book written in Orcish. It's very long and there are very few pictures.
item_23321.Name: Orcish Treatise

item_23322.Description: A book with Orcish phrases translated into several languages.
item_23322.Name: Orcish Military Phrasebook

item_23323.Description: A book written in Orcish. The occasional diagrams and woodcut illustrations suggest that it's about orcish mages that perform weird rituals.
item_23323.Name: Orcish Book About Weird Mages

item_2528.Description: Teaches you how to make a potion that lets your sprint faster. Only werewolves can use this recipe (it requires drops of distilled wolf urine), but anyone can drink the resulting potion.
item_2528.Name: Alchemy: Wolfen Speed Potion

item_2529.Description: Teaches you how to make a potion that lets your sprint faster. Only werewolves can use this recipe (it requires drops of distilled wolf urine), but anyone can drink the resulting potion.
item_2529.Name: Alchemy: Concentrated Wolfen Speed Potion

item_2530.Description: A ponderous volume wherein an anonymous rakshasa mage explores the idea that the 'old' rakshasa form is somehow still locked within each 'new' rakshasa body. The author posits that certain potions might do the trick, and then explores numerous alchemical hypotheses, none of which pan out too well, but one complex recipe catches your eye.
item_2530.Name: On Becoming Great Again

item_2531.Description: Teaches you an odd recipe for a potion that keeps dirt off of you. (Why you wouldn't just bathe more often is anyone's guess.)
item_2531.Name: Alchemy: Dirt Shield Potion

item_2532.Description: Teaches you various recipes for special inks.
item_2532.Name: Alchemy: Inks for Special Occasions Pt 4

item_2533.Description: Teaches you a method for teleporting back to your guild's home location. (Currently all guilds' home locations are Rahu, but that will eventually be configurable.) Costs 2 Guild Credits to cast.
item_2533.Name: Teleportation: Return to Guild Hall

item_2534.Description: Bring a seemingly-dead ally back to life. The ally will return with half of their Max Health. Consumes 3 Guild Credits.
item_2534.Name: First Aid: Resuscitate 2 (Guild)

item_2535.Description: Bring a seemingly-dead ally back to life. The ally will return with half of their Max Health. Consumes 1 Guild Credit. You must be Hardcore to use this ability.
item_2535.Name: First Aid: Resuscitate 2 (Hardcore, Guild)

item_2536.Description: Bring a seemingly-dead ally back to life. The ally will return with half of their Max Health. Consumes 2 Guild Credits. You must be in a long-term animal form to use this ability.
item_2536.Name: First Aid: Resuscitate 2 (Animal, Guild)

item_2537.Description: Teaches you the technique for creating mercury, a curious liquid with many uses.

item_3501.Description: Contains formulae for insanely dangerous run-speed acceleration potions.
item_3501.Name: Alchemy: Ignite The Fire In Your Legs!

item_3502.Description: Explains a technique for hyper-accelerating your organs well beyond their natural limits.
item_3502.Name: Alchemy: Overclock Your Heart and Mind

item_3503.Description: Safe, mild recipes for increasing your Max Power. "Great for beginners!"
item_3503.Name: Alchemy: Safe Brain Boosts For Beginners

item_3504.Description: An introductory text. Most techniques are just tutorials, but the recipe for causing fruit to rot has a few uses. And it's good practice!
item_3504.Name: Alchemy: So You Want To Be An Alchemist

item_3505.Description: Teaches you to make simple acids from exotic metals, or from organic items you may already have in your home. Great for cleaning! Too mild for use in combat.
item_3505.Name: Alchemy: The Hows and Whys of Acid

item_3506.Description: Teaches you how to make and apply poison to a small knife.
item_3506.Name: Alchemy: Weak Poison For Knives

item_3507.Description: Teaches you how to make and apply poison to a small knife.
item_3507.Name: Alchemy: Modest Poison For Knives

item_3508.Description: Teaches you how to make and apply poison to a small knife.
item_3508.Name: Alchemy: Dangerous Poison For Knives

item_3509.Description: Teaches you how to make and apply poison to a small knife.
item_3509.Name: Alchemy: Potent Poison For Knives

item_3510.Description: Teaches you how to make and apply poison to a small knife.
item_3510.Name: Alchemy: Deadly Poison For Knives

item_3511.Description: Teaches you several ways to make advanced acids with many uses in crafting. Not quite useful in combat.
item_3511.Name: Alchemy: Potent Acids: Facts and Myths

item_3516.Description: Teaches you various recipes for special inks.
item_3516.Name: Alchemy: Inks for Special Occasions Pt 1

item_3517.Description: Teaches you various recipes for special inks.
item_3517.Name: Alchemy: Inks for Special Occasions Pt 2

item_3518.Description: Teaches you various recipes for special inks.
item_3518.Name: Alchemy: Inks for Special Occasions Pt 3

item_3519.Description: Teaches you how to create a potion that burns enemies that attack you.
item_3519.Name: Alchemy: Behold the Fire Shield

item_3520.Description: Teaches you how to create a potion that gives you insanely potent jumping power.
item_3520.Name: Alchemy: Why Not Leap Into the Sky?

item_3521.Description: Teaches you how to make Make-Me-Strong Juice, an overly-cutesy name for a potion that boosts max health.
item_3521.Name: Alchemy: Better Pick-Me-Ups

item_3522.Description: Teaches werewolves how to make a special compound from their saliva.
item_3522.Name: Lycanthropic Alchemy: Sanguinizer

item_3523.Description: Teaches werewolves how to make a special compound from their saliva.
item_3523.Name: Lycanthropic Alchemy: Blood Seeker Ointment

item_3524.Description: Teaches you how to read the phase of the moon.
item_3524.Name: Phases of the Moon

item_3525.Description: An orcish Hal-Ku story (which are non-fiction accounts of orcs torturing other people to death). Recounts every minute of a six-week torture session, wherein the orcish author slowly killed a human alchemist. Much of the book is padded with grotesque anecdotes, but one useful recipe is hidden in the appendix.
item_3525.Name: The Alchemist's Screams

item_3526.Description: Teaches you how to make a hallucinogenic cauldron.
item_3526.Name: Alchemy: Cauldron of Vile Thoughts

item_3527.Description: Teaches you how to create a potion that increases the time you can stay underwater.
item_3527.Name: Alchemy: Water Lung Potion

item_3528.Description: Teaches you how to create a potion that accelerates your swimming speed.
item_3528.Name: Alchemy: Swimming Potion

item_3529.Description: Teaches you how to create a potion that dramatically boosts your Max Bodyheat.
item_3529.Name: Alchemy: Orcish Thickskin Potion

item_3530.Description: Teaches you a hypothetical recipe designed by a Gazluk sage.
item_3530.Name: Alchemy: Kraken Power Potion

item_3531.Description: Teaches you how to create a potion that grants fire, cold, and electricity resistance.
item_3531.Name: Alchemy: Energy Resistance Potion

item_3532.Description: Teaches you how to make a potion that boosts all your attacks +10% against creatures of the Fish anatomy type (which also includes frogs and snails).
item_3532.Name: Alchemy: Gillpuncher Ointment

item_3533.Description: Teaches you how to make a potion to perceive monsters before they appear.
item_3533.Name: Alchemy: Imatia's Sight Potion

item_3534.Description: Teaches you how to make a healing potion that can be drunk many times.
item_3534.Name: Alchemy: Infinite Potion of Healing

item_3535.Description: Teaches you how to make a poison cure.
item_3535.Name: Alchemy: Strong Antivenom

item_3536.Description: Teaches you how to make a flammable oil that can be applied to weapons.
item_3536.Name: Alchemy: Trollbane Oil

item_3537.Description: Teaches you how to turn a bunch of gold nuggets into a more useful chunk of gold.
item_3537.Name: Blacksmithing: Combining Gold Nuggets

item_3538.Description: Teaches you how to make a potion that helps fairies recoup their energy.
item_3538.Name: Alchemy: Gooey Fae Energy Potion

item_3539.Description: Teaches you how to make a potion that helps fairies recoup their energy.
item_3539.Name: Alchemy: Foamy Fae Energy Potion

item_3540.Description: Teaches you how to make a pathology toolkit from advanced materials.
item_3540.Name: Toolcrafting: Carbon-Form Scrutinizer Array

item_3541.Description: Teaches you to make a magic ring from otherworldly material.
item_3541.Name: Jewelry Crafting: Position Inferencing Ring

item_40002.Description: Sturdy and fashionable, if not especially protective.
item_40002.Name: Basic Boots

item_40003.Description: These have been perfectly worn in! Nice. But still very smelly.
item_40003.Name: Comfortable Ancient Shoes

item_40005.Description: These boots have been hand-painted, but are still pretty ugly.
item_40005.Name: Sturdy Boots

item_40006.Description: These were worn by a dainty goblin.
item_40006.Name: Goblin Slippers

item_40007.Description: These were worn by a tough goblin.
item_40007.Name: Goblin Stompers

item_4001.Description: A simple autopsy kit for beginning pathologists. (Keep it in your inventory and you'll be given the option to autopsy corpses.)
item_4001.Name: Autopsy Kit

item_40010.Description: When you put these slippers on, your whole body feels lighter.
item_40010.Name: Featherweights

item_40011.Description: These boots have been dyed red and given a preposterous name.
item_40011.Name: Hateboots

item_40013.Description: Strong general-purpose footwear, with metal outside for protection, wool inside for insulation.
item_40013.Name: Ruggedized Boots

item_40015.Description: Handmade by a fairy, these make you especially light on your feet.
item_40015.Name: Flower Dainties

item_40017.Description: Horseshoes, but fitted for a cow's hooves.
item_40017.Name: Cow Shoes

item_40018.Description: Horseshoes, but fitted for a pig's hooves.
item_40018.Name: Pig Shoes

item_40019.Description: A pair of simple boots. Echur says that they help one connect with the world around them, whatever that means.
item_40019.Name: Echur's Boots

item_4002.Description: A fancy autopsy kit for advanced pathologists. (+3 to your effective skill when autopsying a corpse.)
item_4002.Name: Forensic Inspection Kit

item_40020.Description: Horseshoes, but fitted for a deer's hooves.
item_40020.Name: Deer Shoes

item_40021.Description: These boots are abysmal, leaky, and humiliating to wear.
item_40021.Name: Shoddy Leather Boots

item_40022.Description: Well, they're hand-made shoes. Not everything that's hand-made is good quality, though, it turns out.
item_40022.Name: Rough Leather Boots

item_40023.Description: Hideous foot wrappings covered in excess leather to provide protection - but not comfort. Expect gigantic blisters.
item_40023.Name: Crude Leather Boots

item_40024.Description: The sort of boots you might imagine if you tried to visualize leather boots in your head. Fairly generic.
item_40024.Name: Decent Leather Boots

item_40025.Description: Boots with a fair amount of reinforcement in the heel, and padding to prevent blisters. Still not elegant, but fairly effective in combat.
item_40025.Name: Nice Leather Boots

item_40026.Description: These boots are pretty nice to wear, and seem like they'll last a long time, too.
item_40026.Name: Quality Leather Boots

item_40027.Description: These are so soft to touch that you almost feel criminal wearing them out into the mud and gore.
item_40027.Name: Great Leather Boots

item_40028.Description: These boots breathe better than most leather garments, so your feet don't get quite as stinky. Plus, they have double-reinforced laces!
item_40028.Name: Amazing Leather Boots

item_40029.Description: This shoe has been heavily over-engineered, with secret cushions and odd snaps to ensure a perfect fit for any foot size.
item_40029.Name: Astounding Leather Boots

item_4003.Description: A fancier autopsy kit for advanced pathologists. (+5 to your effective skill when autopsying a corpse.)
item_4003.Name: Forensic Analysis Kit

item_4004.Description: An autopsy kit made of ice and fairy dust. (Keep it in your inventory and you'll be given the option to autopsy corpses.)
item_4004.Name: Enchanted Autopsy Kit

item_40041.Description: Farmers typically don't feel compelled to shod a cow. But some cows are more violent and adventurous than others.
item_40041.Name: Shoddy Cow Shoes

item_40042.Description: Your violent cow will be made all the more violent by these uncomfortable shoes!
item_40042.Name: Rough Cow Shoes

item_40043.Description: A crude cow will love these crude shoes.

item_4005.Name: Carbon-form Scrutinizer Array

item_40061.Description: Deer seem to get along fine in nature without having metal hammered into their hooves, but not all deer are content with the life of a passive ungulate.
item_40061.Name: Shoddy Deer Shoes

item_40062.Description: The nails are too long for the deer's small hooves, causing considerable pain while wearing.
item_40062.Name: Rough Deer Shoes

item_40071.Description: If a cow needed to be shod for some reason, it is surely not with these wooden, splinter-laced bits of junk.
item_40071.Name: Shoddy Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40072.Description: Basically just chunks of wood nailed to a cow's feet. Which makes them sound more comfortable than they really are.
item_40072.Name: Rough Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40073.Description: Not generally considered a good choice, shodding a cow with bits of wood. These crude shoes are... crude.
item_40073.Name: Crude Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40074.Description: If all you're looking for is some horseshoe-shaped pieces of wood to nail to your cow's feet, you're in luck.
item_40074.Name: Decent Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40075.Description: Elegantly whittled and reinforced wooden shoes. They can easily withstand the weight of an angry heiffer.

item_40076.Description: Made by someone with decent working knowledge of wood, these seem fairly comfortable if you have hooves for feet.
item_40076.Name: Quality Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40077.Description: You'd almost think these were metal, that's how great these bits of wood are!
item_40077.Name: Great Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40078.Description: These wooden footguards are a work of art. Avant garde art, where you nail wood to cows' feet.
item_40078.Name: Amazing Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40085.Name: Nice Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40086.Description: Made by someone with decent working knowledge of wood, these seem fairly comfortable if you have hooves for feet.

item_40087.Description: You'd almost think these were metal, that's how great these bits of wood are!
item_40087.Name: Great Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40088.Description: These wooden footguards are a work of art. Avant garde art, where you nail wood to the feet of an unsuspecting ungulate.
item_40088.Name: Amazing Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40101.Description: Special deer-fitted horseshoes made of an otherworldly metal.
item_40101.Name: Shadow Trotters

item_40102.Description: Thick layers of hide and fur make these boots quite warm.
item_40102.Name: Insulated Boots

item_40103.Description: Although they're leather instead of metal, these insulated boots are made for protection, not grace or mobility.
item_40103.Name: Orcish Rugged Boots

item_40104.Description: It's hard to imagine, but once these boots were the height of fashion.
item_40104.Name: Discarded Boots

item_40105.Description: These fancy boots have been digested by a slime creature, leaving mostly just metal behind. Don't worry about them being uncomfortable, though: there's tons of ooze in there to keep your feet cozy.
item_40105.Name: Slimy Shoes

item_40106.Description: These boots have clearly been the birthing spot for baby spiders in the past. You can clean them off, but can you ever really get the image out of your head?
item_40106.Name: Web-Encrusted Shoes

item_40107.Description: A werewolf wore these boots while transforming a few too many times. The armor quality is totally shot, but it still has some value.
item_40107.Name: Ruined Shifter's Boots

item_40109.Description: Profoundly uncomfortable and rather awkward to move in, but very stylish.
item_40109.Name: Elven Plate Boots

item_40110.Description: Made of a bizarre metal, these uncomfortable boots seem to clench your feet with malice.
item_40110.Name: Boots of the Winter Court

item_40111.Description: Common apparel from the Serbule Revolt, 1500 years ago. These boots are so over-engineered that they look brand new. But the smell is pretty bad.
item_40111.Name: Dwarven Soldier Boots

item_40112.Description: The evil creature Ciervos wore these for thousands of years. Must be lucky! Hmm, but he died wearing them. Maybe they're unlucky...
item_40112.Name: Ciervos's Anklets

item_40113.Description: Makeshift fae armor crafted from repurposed Winter Court armor. It doesn't have quite the style or powers of Summer Court armor, but it's not bad.
item_40113.Name: Boots of the Summer Court

item_40114.Description: Designed by a spiteful necromancer bent on conquering a city, these cloth foot coverings seethe with hatred. And it turns out that pure hatred is pretty warm, providing mild protection against the cold.
item_40114.Name: Booties of Hateful Comeuppance

item_40115.Description: When thousands of Rakshasa warriors arrived on Alharth, they wore boots like these, designed to accommodate all environments. The secret to their crafting is lost to the Rakshasa living here now.
item_40115.Name: Ravana Soldier Boots

item_40116.Description: Popular with elven messengers, these elegant cloth footwraps make your feet move much faster! But they don't protect your feet very well, so you'll need significant endurance to tolerate the numerous stubbed toes and sprained ankles.
item_40116.Name: Windstep Shoes

item_40117.Description: Sturdy and fashionable, if not especially protective.
item_40117.Name: Basic Boots

item_40118.Description: These boots have been hand-painted, but are still pretty ugly.
item_40118.Name: Sturdy Boots

item_40120.Description: A bit of leaves, a bit of bark, and a lot of magic.
item_40120.Name: Spring Fairy Shoes

item_40121.Description: Part of the ancient uniform of Dwarven Stalwarts, the elite warriors entrusted with protecting the most important Dwarven secrets. Quality-wise, they're very protective, but very uncomfortable.
item_40121.Name: Stalwart Boots

item_40122.Description: A pair of old cloth shoes that are much, much tougher than they look.
item_40122.Name: Tough Old Shoes

item_40123.Description: These are shoddy boots that have had sections of their protective armor removed to make them a little more agile. The holes let moisture in, and they quickly stink beyond fathoming.
item_40123.Name: Crude Evasion Boots

item_40124.Description: Reasonable boots that have been oiled and softened to let the wearer dash and dart about. Kinda comfortable, but not really.
item_40124.Name: Decent Evasion Boots

item_40125.Description: Someone with competence put together these nimble leather boots. Only a small amount of protection is lost in exchange for nimble dodging ability.
item_40125.Name: Nice Evasion Boots

item_40126.Description: Quality stuff! These are the sort of evasion boots you'd see in a storefront window, if there was a store specifically for evasion boots, which there is not.
item_40126.Name: Quality Evasion Boots

item_40127.Description: Great stuff! These are the sort of evasion boots you'd see in a storefront window, if there was a store specifically for evasion boots, which there is not.

item_40128.Description: Amazing stuff! These are the sort of evasion boots you'd see in a storefront window, if there was a store specifically for evasion boots, which there is not.

item_40129.Description: Astounding stuff! These are the sort of evasion boots you'd see in a storefront window, if there was a store specifically for evasion boots, which there is not.
item_40129.Name: Astounding Evasion Boots

item_40301.Description: Worn leather boots with metal meticulously inserted into them. Whoever made these lacked skill in leatherworking, but made up for it with time and attention to detail.
item_40301.Name: Desert Vagabond Boots

item_40302.Description: This is the latest masterpiece of rakshasa leatherworking, designed to replace the old Ravana armor they can no longer create. In many ways, this surpasses anything from their homeworld, a testament to rakshasa skill... and the toughness of beasts in Alharth.
item_40302.Name: Rakshasian Elite Boots

item_40303.Description: Thick matted hair combined with spider silk. These feel great. No, really. They don't look great, but they feel great.
item_40303.Name: Yeti Stockings

item_40304.Description: Sturdy and fashionable, if not especially protective.
item_40304.Name: Basic Boots

item_40305.Description: Thick layers of hide and fur make these boots quite warm.
item_40305.Name: Insulated Boots

item_40306.Description: The isolated elf colony of Sedgewick Forest prefers armor of this type because it reminds them of their home in Verta. It's been explained to them that nobody in Verta dresses this way anymore, but they don't seem to care.
item_40306.Name: Thentree Boots

item_40307.Description: Made of a bizarre metal, these uncomfortable boots seem to clench your feet with malice.
item_40307.Name: Great Boots of the Winter Court

item_40308.Description: Used by the typical troops of the Crone Hegemony.
item_40308.Name: Peltast Boots

item_40309.Description: The evil necromancer/mentalist wore these comfy booties whenever he destroyed towns or villages.
item_40309.Name: Mortimer's Booties

item_40310.Description: "To my lover, may she run back to me soon. - Raul"
item_40310.Name: Hooves of the Inamorata

item_40311.Description: Made of insanely strong scorpion and beetle carapace plates riveted together, these boots will keep your feet safe from everything except blisters. It's a pity carapace plates aren't more comfortable...
EffectDescs: You reflect 4% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_40311.Name: Scorpiclaw Boots

item_40312.Description: The customized scorpiclaw boots of the dread Onkara general. They fit a little better than normal.
EffectDescs: You reflect 4% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_40312.Name: General Pask's Boots

item_40313.Description: Budget-conscious goblins love these boots, which look as sturdy as regular goblin boots, but a fraction of the cost!
item_40313.Name: Cheap Goblin Boots

item_40315.Description: The rightly-feared orcish Misery Troopers from the Snowblood Army wear these near-indestructible boots. Well-maintained and polished.
item_40315.Name: Snowblood Misery Trooper Boots

item_40316.Description: Worn by orcish mages after they've been promoted to 'Magic Trooper', which is the highest rank that most can expect to reach, given mages' glass ceiling in orcish society.
item_40316.Name: Orcish Magic Trooper Boots

item_40317.Description: Named after a legendary werewolf who supposedly designed this style of footwear, these shoes fall off cleanly when a lycanthrope transforms, avoiding embarrassing trip-and-fall accidents in the heat of battle. A symbol of Arisetsu is carefully embroidered into the left shoe.
item_40317.Name: Lyramis Shoes

item_40318.Description: This red-tinted armor is worn by Gazluk City's front-line soldiers, known as "Death Troopers". Their armor enhances their strength and melee prowess.
item_40318.Name: Death Trooper Boots

item_40319.Description: This blue-tinted armor is worn by Gazluk City's support soldiers, known as "Misery Troopers". Their armor is strong while also providing survival protection in harsh weather.
item_40319.Name: Misery Trooper Boots

item_40320.Description: This green-tinted armor is worn by Gazluk City's gadgeteers and tacticians, known as "Treachery Troopers". Their armor protects them from battlefield conditions and enhances their tricky combat techniques.
item_40320.Name: Treachery Trooper Boots

item_40321.Description: This gold-tinted armor is worn by the highest battlefield officers in Gazluk City's army. It is versatile and strong, like its wearer.
item_40321.Name: Gazluk Officer Boots

item_40322.Description: This cloth armor is worn by the few Gazluk wizards who have become officers. It is designed to aid powerful spellcasters.
item_40322.Name: War-Wizard Officer Shoes

item_40323.Description: The terrifying orcish cult known as the Mutterers wear these garments.
item_40323.Name: Mutterer Necromancer Shoes

item_40324.Description: The terrifying orcish cult known as the Mutterers wear these garments.
item_40324.Name: Mutterer Cabalist Shoes

item_40325.Description: Originally gifted to ratkin guerillas by the Crone Hegemony, these magic boots have been re-soled and re-leathered several times in the intervening years.
item_40325.Name: Ratkin Revolutionist Boots

item_40326.Description: The product of a short-lived treaty with the Orcs of Gazluk, these orcish-style boots are comfortable and keep the feet dry in any environment. The boots were stored in a military warehouse for decades, which gives them a musty odor, but they are in great shape.
item_40326.Name: Council Pathfinder Boots

item_40327.Description: Made of a bizarre metal, these uncomfortable boots seem to clench your feet with malice.
item_40327.Name: Winter Court Battle-Boots

item_40328.Description: Made of a bizarre glowing metal, these uncomfortable boots seem to clench your feet with malice.
item_40328.Name: Winter Court Murder-Boots

item_40329.Description: These old boots have been resoled with a mysterious metal, and the most recent owner has etched eerie symbols into them.
item_40329.Name: Symbol-Etched Boots

item_40330.Description: Made of giant seashells. It's more comfortable than it looks. (Includes random level 35 enchantments.)
item_40330.Name: Seashell Boots

item_40331.Description: Made of giant seashells. It's more comfortable than it looks. (Includes random level 40 enchantments.)
item_40331.Name: Fancy Seashell Boots

item_40332.Description: Made of giant seashells. It's more comfortable than it looks. (Includes random level 45 enchantments.)
item_40332.Name: Extra-Fancy Seashell Boots

item_40334.Description: Skintight shoes worn by ranalon. Their creation method is a mystery to outsiders.
item_40334.Name: Kelp Shoes

item_40335.Description: Skintight shoes worn by ranalon. Their creation method is a mystery to outsiders.
item_40335.Name: Tough Kelp Shoes

item_40336.Description: These fancy boots have been digested by a slime creature, leaving mostly just metal behind. Don't worry about them being uncomfortable, though: there's tons of ooze in there to keep your feet cozy.
item_40336.Name: Slimy Shoes

item_40337.Description: Worn by fae officers aboard their strange ships. Made of an unrecognizable material.
item_40337.Name: Fae Navy Shoes

item_40338.Description: The goblin chief Rubgag used these magic slippers to win dancing competitions (which was definitely cheating, or "Chiefing", as he called it.).
item_40338.Name: Rubgag's Dancing Shoes

item_40339.Description: This style of plate boot is named after the elven knight Niph. As the story goes, Niph fought off an army of undead alone, somehow running "faster than death itself."
item_40339.Name: Niphian Boots

item_40404.Description: Soft, astonishingly flexible, and resistant to murder.
EffectDescs: Every 30 seconds, automatically Evade the first Burst attack aimed at you
item_40404.Name: Decent Nimble Shoes

item_40405.Description: Soft, astonishingly flexible, and resistant to murder.
EffectDescs: Every 30 seconds, automatically Evade the first Burst attack aimed at you
item_40405.Name: Nice Nimble Shoes

item_40406.Description: Soft, astonishingly flexible, and resistant to murder.
EffectDescs: Every 30 seconds, automatically Evade the first Burst attack aimed at you
item_40406.Name: Quality Nimble Shoes

item_40407.Description: Soft, astonishingly flexible, and resistant to murder.
EffectDescs: Every 30 seconds, automatically Evade the first Burst attack aimed at you
item_40407.Name: Great Nimble Shoes

item_40408.Description: Soft, astonishingly flexible, and resistant to murder.
EffectDescs: Every 25 seconds, automatically Evade the first Burst attack aimed at you
item_40408.Name: Amazing Nimble Shoes

item_40409.Description: Soft, astonishingly flexible, and resistant to murder.
EffectDescs: Every 25 seconds, automatically Evade the first Burst attack aimed at you
item_40409.Name: Astounding Nimble Shoes

item_40420.Description: Popular with elven messengers, these elegant cloth footwraps make your feet move much faster! But they don't protect your feet very well, so you'll need significant endurance to tolerate the numerous stubbed toes and sprained ankles. This pair was enhanced by Raim of the Crafting Caravan.
item_40420.Name: Enhanced Windstep Shoes

item_41001.Description: These have been in the muck for ages...
item_41001.Name: Moldy Ancient Pants

item_41002.Description: Nice greaves. Vaguely stylish yet vaguely protective.
item_41002.Name: Basic Pants

item_41003.Description: Sure they're gross, but they're already worn in, and the caked-on dirt provides extra resilience.
item_41003.Name: Comfortable Ancient Pants

item_41004.Description: Comfy, invigorating, and magically protective. They smell like lilac and pimentos for some reason.
item_41004.Name: Rita's Lucky Underpants

item_41005.Description: Gold! With little white frill things. Reasonably protective, too.
item_41005.Name: Sturdy Pants

item_41006.Description: A protective garment that also keeps you light on your feet. The goblin smell, unfortunately, doesn't wash out.
item_41006.Name: Goblin Skirt

item_41007.Description: Strong pants made of leather. You don't want to think about what creature the leather may have come from.
item_41007.Name: Goblin Leggings

item_41008.Description: Made from the skin of abominations, these pants seem to constantly fondle your legs as you wear them. It's really quite disturbing, but the armor is tough...
item_41008.Name: Nightmare Pants

item_41009.Description: The "quality" in the title refers to the defensive merits, not the fashion statement.
item_41009.Name: Quality Pants

item_41011.Description: Crafted by elves who were too homesick to get out of bed, the Pants of the Yearning Sea are sorrow incarnate. But these sure are comfy. Plus, the tears that dripped onto the fabric have made it extra bouncy!
item_41011.Name: Pants of the Yearning Sea

item_41012.Description: Once worn by Makopa the semi-legendary goblin boss.
item_41012.Name: Makopa's Pants

item_41013.Description: They're supernaturally slimming! Plus they have a hidden dimensional pocket inside that can fit a few extra items.
item_41013.Name: Rita's Disturbing Dimensional Panties

item_41014.Description: Created by an alchemist/farmer to protect her legs in the fields, these pants are great at keeping nature off of you. Too bad about the odor...
item_41014.Name: Ivyn's Family Pants

item_41015.Description: Full of wool! Way too much wool. You'd get heatstroke if it was too hot!
item_41015.Name: Ukorga's Experimental Pants

item_41016.Description: These once-amazing pants aren't amazing anymore. They're torn and mangled. But there's still some armor on them... could be worse! A hand-sewn tag inside says "To General Lawyr, may you remember me always, your Kello."
item_41016.Name: General Lawyr's Pants

item_41020.Description: Apparently Rita gave these to Sir Coth, who has since discarded them.
item_41020.Name: Sir Coth's Discarded Gift

item_41021.Description: Somebody has worn these undergarments previously without washing them. Hopefully that person was you. But you're not sure. Anyway, they reek, plus they provide no armor.
item_41021.Name: Crude Underwear

item_41022.Description: Someone was buried in these, apparently. They're caked with dust, but don't seem the worse for wear.
item_41022.Name: Ancient Slacks

item_41023.Description: Any beauty these leggings once possessed has long faded. But they still have an inner beauty, right?
item_41023.Name: Long-Lost Leggings

item_41024.Description: There's a big hole in these, but a decade of spiderweb build-up kind of seals the hole. Kind of.
item_41024.Name: Web-Encrusted Pants

item_41025.Description: These cotton undergarments are possibly the least interesting piece of clothing possible.
item_41025.Name: Cotton Long Underwear

item_41026.Description: These are just cotton underclothes, but they're really well made!
item_41026.Name: Long Stockings

item_41027.Description: Leather armor with a thin layer of strong metal inside.
item_41027.Name: Orcish Greaves

item_41028.Description: During the Elf-Dwarf wars, Dwarven mages created leather-evaporation magic, rendering elves' usual armor obsolete. These ceremonial plate leggings were hurried into battle. Although they're impressively protective, they're still pretty uncomfortable.
item_41028.Name: Elven Plate Leggings

item_41029.Description: The metal is always freezing cold, but you'll soon become numb to such trivial irritations.
item_41029.Name: Greaves of the Winter Court

item_41030.Description: It's been about 15 centuries since the Serbule Revolt, but these dwarven leggings don't seem a day over 450. Their preservative magic is quite strong.
item_41030.Name: Dwarven Soldier Leggings

item_41031.Description: Made from repurposed Winter Court armor in an imperfect process. This somehow conveys the warmth of summer while still being quite cold to the touch.
item_41031.Name: Greaves of the Summer Court

item_41032.Description: Designed by a spiteful necromancer bent on conquering a city, these airy pants seethe with hatred. And it turns out that pure hatred is pretty warm, providing mild protection against the cold.
item_41032.Name: Pants of Hateful Comeuppance

item_41033.Description: When thousands of Rakshasa warriors arrived on Alharth, they wore suits of armor like this, designed to accommodate all environments. The secret to their crafting is lost to the Rakshasa living here now.
item_41033.Name: Ravana Soldier Leggings

item_41034.Description: This kilt is part of the uniform of the dwarven Idealist's Guild. Members produce a substance they call "optimism", which is sold in the form of addictive crystals.
item_41034.Name: Idealist's Skirts

item_41035.Description: Nice greaves. Vaguely stylish yet vaguely protective.
item_41035.Name: Basic Pants

item_41036.Description: Gold! With little white frill things. Reasonably protective, too.
item_41036.Name: Sturdy Pants

item_41037.Description: The "quality" in the title refers to the defensive merits, not the fashion statement.
item_41037.Name: Quality Pants

item_41038.Description: Kind of revealing. But very comfortable.
item_41038.Name: Spring Fairy Leggings

item_41039.Description: Dwarven Stalwarts wore leg armor like this a thousand years ago, and then handed down for centuries after the Stalwarts were no more, because these pants are great at absorbing punishment.
item_41039.Name: Stalwart Leggings

item_41040.Description: The metal is always freezing cold, but you'll soon become numb to such trivial irritations.
item_41040.Name: Great Greaves of the Winter Court

item_41041.Description: With horrid stitching and gigantic holes, these smelly pants are just plain sad.
item_41041.Name: Shoddy Leather Leggings

item_41042.Description: Sewn by an amateur, with low-quality materials and a lack of fashion sense.
item_41042.Name: Rough Leather Leggings

item_41043.Description: With an eye toward performance over elegance, these leather pants will protect you from monsters, but not from chafing.
item_41043.Name: Crude Leather Leggings

item_41044.Description: Thanks to a modicum of padding inside, wearing these pants will only leave you severely chafed, instead of incapacitated.
item_41044.Name: Decent Leather Leggings

item_41045.Description: Someone with a basic sense of style has fashioned these leather pants. Unfortunately the protective reinforcement ruins the look, but it could be worse.
item_41045.Name: Nice Leather Leggings

item_41047.Description: Astonishingly, these leather pants don't chafe! This is some high-grade magic right here. Or just great tailoring.
item_41047.Name: Great Leather Leggings

item_41048.Description: These beautiful leather pants are so soft, you just want to pet them. Don't let anybody see you doing that.
item_41048.Name: Amazing Leather Leggings

item_41049.Description: You get the feeling that, even when they were brand new, these pants already had that great worn-in feeling. The padding is strong but not bulky and the leather smell is intoxicating.
item_41049.Name: Astounding Leather Leggings

item_41051.Description: Someone was buried in these, apparently. They're caked with dust, but don't seem the worse for wear.
item_41051.Name: Ancient Slacks

item_41063.Description: A sub-par pair of leather leggings has been chopped inexpertly to make it more evasive. The result is humiliating in most respects.
item_41063.Name: Crude Evasion Leggings

item_41064.Description: These leather pants have had the joints replaced with super-soft leather. The stitching is poor, though, and the pants are drafty. Drafty pants!
item_41064.Name: Decent Evasion Leggings

item_41065.Description: These leather pants are so soft. They're nice for dodging arrows and the like.
item_41065.Name: Nice Evasion Leggings

item_41066.Description: Stylish, highly mobile, and almost-but-not-quite comfortable leather pants.
item_41066.Name: Quality Evasion Leggings

item_41067.Description: Stylish, highly mobile, and comfortable leather pants.
item_41067.Name: Great Evasion Leggings

item_41068.Description: Stylish, highly mobile, and comfortable leather pants.
item_41068.Name: Amazing Evasion Leggings

item_41069.Description: Stylish, highly mobile, and comfortable leather pants.
item_41069.Name: Astounding Evasion Leggings

item_41084.Description: Extra insulated to protect against winds.
item_41084.Name: Decent Winter Leggings

item_41085.Description: Cozy and warm, with lots of fur trim.
item_41085.Name: Nice Winter Leggings

item_41086.Description: Professional-looking winter pants with heavy insulation.
item_41086.Name: Quality Winter Leggings

item_41087.Description: Professional-looking winter pants with heavy insulation.
item_41087.Name: Great Winter Leggings

item_41088.Description: Professional-looking winter pants with heavy insulation.
item_41088.Name: Amazing Winter Leggings

item_41089.Description: Professional-looking winter pants with heavy insulation.
item_41089.Name: Astounding Winter Leggings

item_41101.Description: A barbaric act of cruelty to cotton.
item_41101.Name: Shoddy Cloth Pants

item_41102.Description: The quadruple-thick stitching screams "overcompensating" and the pattern is frankly horrendous. But it'd be good for sewer-delving or something.
item_41102.Name: Rough Cloth Pants

item_41103.Description: A rustic farmer might consider these pants barely adequate. Might.
item_41103.Name: Crude Cloth Pants

item_41104.Description: The premier choice for those who work the land daily. Strong stitching, and none of that annoying "attractiveness" to get in the way.
item_41104.Name: Decent Cloth Pants

item_41105.Description: Not bad. You wouldn't even be embarrassed to be seen in these nice pants. Unless you were seen by someone you wanted to impress.
item_41105.Name: Nice Cloth Pants

item_41106.Description: Good thread count. Sturdy crotch support. A little stiff, but to be expected for such a resilient pair of pants.
item_41106.Name: Quality Cloth Pants

item_41107.Description: Very soft to the touch, but resistant to damage.
item_41107.Name: Great Cloth Pants

item_41108.Description: Very soft to the touch, but resistant to damage.
item_41108.Name: Amazing Cloth Pants

item_41109.Description: Very soft to the touch, but resistant to damage.
item_41109.Name: Astounding Cloth Pants

item_4111.Description: A potent acid for removing inscriptions on items.
item_4111.Name: Ink Remover

item_41151.Description: Someone has awkwardly painted these sub-par pants. Well, woodland animals aren't super smart, so maybe that'll do.
item_41151.Name: Camouflaged Crude Pants

item_41152.Description: Decent pants that blend into the surroundings.
item_41152.Name: Camouflaged Decent Pants

item_41153.Description: This is a great camouflage job! The pants, well, they're not bad per se...
item_41153.Name: Camouflaged Nice Pants

item_41154.Description: Don't drop these in the forest or you'll never find them again.
item_41154.Name: Camouflaged Quality Pants

item_41155.Description: These look like really soft plants. Wait, those are soft pants. That's great camo.
item_41155.Name: Camouflaged Great Pants

item_41156.Description: These look like really soft plants. Wait, those are soft pants. That's great camo.
item_41156.Name: Camouflaged Amazing Pants

item_41157.Description: These look like really soft plants. Wait, those are soft pants. That's great camo.
item_41157.Name: Camouflaged Astounding Pants

item_41171.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. The sinews were not properly cured and stink beyond comprehension.
item_41171.Name: Decent Snail Greaves

item_41172.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. Only somewhat stinky.
item_41172.Name: Nice Snail Greaves

item_41173.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_41173.Name: Quality Snail Greaves

item_41174.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_41174.Name: Great Snail Greaves

item_41175.Description: Made of snail shells, sinew, and teeth.
item_41175.Name: Amazing Snail Greaves

item_41201.Name: Nice Spring Fairy Leggings

item_41202.Description: Kind of revealing. But very comfortable.

item_41204.Name: Amazing Spring Fairy Leggings

item_41205.Name: Astounding Spring Fairy Leggings

item_4121.Description: An empty book. Experts at Calligraphy can write in it at a Writing Table.
item_4121.Name: Blank Book

item_41221.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the lower legs and haunches of a wolf.
item_41221.Name: Shoddy Werewolf Hindguard
