item_41227.Name: Great Werewolf Hindguard

item_41228.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the lower legs and haunches of a wolf.
item_41228.Name: Amazing Werewolf Hindguard

item_4123.Description: Used by calligraphers when extremely fine detail must be inked.
item_4123.Name: Inkstone

item_41246.Description: These pants are made of leather that's incredibly soft, yet strong. Although it has an inner lining to prevent chafing, that lining is made of silk, and silk chafes pretty badly too. But you get used to it.
item_41246.Name: Quality Bard Leggings

item_41247.Description: These pants are made of leather that's incredibly soft, yet strong. Although it has an inner lining to prevent chafing, that lining is made of silk, and silk chafes pretty badly too. But you get used to it.
item_41247.Name: Great Bard Leggings

item_41248.Description: These pants are made of leather that's incredibly soft, yet strong. Although it has an inner lining to prevent chafing, that lining is made of silk, and silk chafes pretty badly too. But you get used to it.
item_41248.Name: Amazing Bard Leggings

item_41249.Description: These pants are made of leather that's incredibly soft, yet strong. Although it has an inner lining to prevent chafing, that lining is made of silk, and silk chafes pretty badly too. But you get used to it.
item_41249.Name: Astounding Bard Leggings

item_41264.Description: Made of ultra-strong cloth, this garment makes it easy to dodge attacks.
EffectDescs: Every 30 seconds, automatically Evade the first Ranged attack aimed at you
item_41264.Name: Decent Nimble Pants

item_41265.Description: Made of ultra-strong cloth, this garment makes it easy to dodge attacks.
EffectDescs: Every 30 seconds, automatically Evade the first Ranged attack aimed at you
item_41265.Name: Nice Nimble Pants

item_41266.Description: Made of ultra-strong cloth, this garment makes it easy to dodge attacks.
EffectDescs: Every 30 seconds, automatically Evade the first Ranged attack aimed at you
item_41266.Name: Quality Nimble Pants

item_41267.Description: Made of ultra-strong cloth, this garment makes it easy to dodge attacks.
EffectDescs: Every 25 seconds, automatically Evade the first Ranged attack aimed at you
item_41267.Name: Great Nimble Pants

item_41268.Description: Made of ultra-strong cloth, this garment makes it easy to dodge attacks.
EffectDescs: Every 25 seconds, automatically Evade the first Ranged attack aimed at you
item_41268.Name: Amazing Nimble Pants

item_41269.Description: Made of ultra-strong cloth, this garment makes it easy to dodge attacks.
EffectDescs: Every 25 seconds, automatically Evade the first Ranged attack aimed at you
item_41269.Name: Astounding Nimble Pants

item_41281.Description: Some sort of hempen material stuffed with strange leaves. Itchy.
item_41281.Name: Quality Ri-Shin Pants

item_41282.Description: Stuffed with silky leaves and bits of straw. Not comfortable, but great protection!
item_41282.Name: Great Ri-Shin Pants

item_41283.Description: You would never realize these pants were crafted by treants... if indeed they were crafted by treants. (Followers of Ri-Shin constantly lie about how many things are crafted by treants. Most likely, it was elves.)
item_41283.Name: Amazing Ri-Shin Pants

item_41284.Description: A pant-shaped conglomeration of plant material. Sometimes a bit of moss is exposed, but they mostly work great.
item_41284.Name: Astounding Ri-Shin Pants

item_41301.Description: Worn leather pants with metal meticulously inserted into them. Whoever made these lacked skill in leatherworking, but made up for it with time and attention to detail.
item_41301.Name: Desert Vagabond Pants

item_41302.Description: This is the latest masterpiece of rakshasa leatherworking, designed to replace the old Ravana armor they can no longer create. In many ways, this surpasses anything from their homeworld, a testament to rakshasa skill... and the toughness of beasts in Alharth.
item_41302.Name: Rakshasian Elite Leggings

item_41303.Description: Thick matted hair combined with spider silk. These feel great. No, really. They don't look great, but they feel great.
item_41303.Name: Yeti Leggings

item_41304.Description: Nice greaves. Vaguely stylish yet vaguely protective.
item_41304.Name: Basic Pants

item_41305.Description: The isolated elf colony of Sedgewick Forest prefers armor of this type because it reminds them of their home in Verta. It's been explained to them that nobody in Verta dresses this way anymore, but they don't seem to care. An outdated version of the Symbol of Arisetsu can be found on the front.
item_41305.Name: Thentree Skirt

item_41306.Description: A protective garment that also keeps you light on your feet. The goblin smell, unfortunately, doesn't wash out.
item_41306.Name: Goblin Kilt

item_41307.Description: Used by the typical troops of the Crone Hegemony.
item_41307.Name: Peltast Kilt

item_41308.Description: Not really that comfortable unless you're in a blizzard, but then they are really cozy.
item_41308.Name: Insulated Pants

item_41309.Description: It's amazing that these awkwardly-riveted pieces of scorpion and beetle carapace give you any mobility at all. But they do! Just don't sit down too quickly, and you'll be fine.
EffectDescs: You reflect 5% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_41309.Name: Scorpiclaw Leggings

item_41310.Description: The terrifying Onkara lord wore these pants all the time. Like, nonstop. But they don't smell. Eerie.
EffectDescs: You reflect 5% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_41310.Name: General Pask's Leggings

item_41311.Description: The stitching on these leather pants is awful. And the quality of the leather sub-par. But goblins forced to buy their own armor often choose these for cost reasons.
item_41311.Name: Cheap Goblin Leggings

item_41312.Description: It's unclear what sort of leather was used in these greaves, but it's not cow leather. Something thicker.
item_41312.Name: Orcish Military Greaves

item_41313.Description: Worn by the elite Snowblood orcs that take care of problematic situations in battle. They're hard to maintain, but impressively protective.
item_41313.Name: Snowblood Misery Trooper Leggings

item_41314.Description: Worn by orcish mages after they've been promoted to 'Magic Trooper', which is the highest rank they can expect to reach, given mages' glass ceiling in orcish society.
item_41314.Name: Orcish Magic Trooper Pants

item_41315.Description: The brutish barbarians known as the 'McNasty clan' are known for their fearlessness almost as much as for their malodorous grooming habits. These crude metal pants are certainly not clean. But they are strong.
item_41315.Name: McNasty Pants

item_41316.Description: This red-tinted armor is worn by Gazluk City's front-line soldiers, known as "Death Troopers". Their armor enhances their strength and melee prowess.
item_41316.Name: Death Trooper Leggings

item_41317.Description: This blue-tinted armor is worn by Gazluk City's support soldiers, known as "Misery Troopers". Their armor is strong while also providing survival protection in harsh weather.
item_41317.Name: Misery Trooper Leggings

item_41318.Description: This green-tinted armor is worn by Gazluk City's gadgeteers and tacticians, known as "Treachery Troopers". Their armor protects them from battlefield conditions and enhances their tricky combat techniques.
item_41318.Name: Treachery Trooper Leggings

item_41319.Description: This gold-tinted armor is worn by the highest battlefield officers in Gazluk City's army. It is versatile and strong, like its wearer.
item_41319.Name: Gazluk Officer Leggings

item_41320.Description: This cloth armor is worn by the few Gazluk wizards who have become officers. It is designed to aid powerful spellcasters.
item_41320.Name: War-Wizard Officer Pants

item_41321.Description: The terrifying orcish cult known as the Mutterers wear these garments.
item_41321.Name: Mutterer Necromancer Pants

item_41322.Description: The terrifying orcish cult known as the Mutterers wear these garments.
item_41322.Name: Mutterer Cabalist Pants

item_41323.Description: While not exactly beautiful, it's definitely elegant and comfortable. The early work of an up-and-coming master tailor, perhaps.
item_41323.Name: Elegant Cotton Skirt

item_41324.Description: About a million of these enchanted pants were made by the Crone Hegemony for ratkin revolutionaries who said they were going to overthrow their gob-land masters. Ultimately the revolutionaries freed themselves and their friends, then called it quits and traded their armor away.
item_41324.Name: Ratkin Revolutionist Leggings

item_41325.Description: Designed to be worn by either orcs or humans, these pants feature several cinch-points to make them comfortable for any leg girth. With clever manipulation of these belts you store a few small items in them... although that wouldn't be very comfortable.
item_41325.Name: Council Pathfinder Leggings

item_41326.Description: Extraordinarily light armor that is very cold to the touch.
item_41326.Name: Winter Court Battle-Greaves

item_41327.Description: When you don this strange glowing metal suit, you can feel your sense of empathy and community diminish. All the better to kill without remorse!
item_41327.Name: Winter Court Murder-Greaves

item_41328.Description: The leather in these pants has been been partially transformed into wood bark, which is is profoundly uncomfortable.
item_41328.Name: Birch Pants

item_41329.Description: Made of giant seashells stitched together with seaweed rope. Surprisingly, they don't stink. (Includes random level 35 enchantments.)
item_41329.Name: Seashell Leggings

item_41330.Description: Made of giant seashells stitched together with seaweed rope. Surprisingly, they don't stink. (Includes random level 40 enchantments.)
item_41330.Name: Fancy Seashell Leggings

item_41331.Description: Made of giant seashells stitched together with seaweed rope. Surprisingly, they don't stink. (Includes random level 45 enchantments.)
item_41331.Name: Extra-Fancy Seashell Leggings

item_41333.Description: Skintight tights worn by ranalon. Their creation method is a mystery to outsiders.
item_41333.Name: Kelp Leggings

item_41334.Description: Skintight tights worn by ranalon. Their creation method is a mystery to outsiders.
item_41334.Name: Tough Kelp Leggings

item_41335.Description: A system of belts and harnesses worn around the hips and legs. Keeps equipment close at hand!
item_41335.Name: Fae Navy Harness

item_41336.Description: A customized system of harnesses worn around the hips and legs. Armor-enhancing nanodispensers are hidden behind the knee guards.
item_41336.Name: Captain Evergloam's Harness

item_42002.Description: Pretty shoddy workmanship... but hey, it's armor.
item_42002.Name: Basic Breastplate

item_42003.Description: This is the grossest possible thing. But all the blood smears make it harder for monsters to tell where to stab you.
item_42003.Name: Comfortable Ancient Shirt

item_42005.Description: This simple platemail has sufficient protection, but it could do with more padding. Very uncomfortable!
item_42005.Name: Sturdy Shirt

item_42006.Description: Strong enough for a Human, but made for a Goblin. By slaves who toil in very poor working conditions.
item_42006.Name: Goblin Breastplate

item_42007.Description: This is good armor, but rather uncomfortable if you have chest hair... lots of pinching.
item_42007.Name: Goblin Chain Shirt

item_42009.Description: Strong armor with a strong statement to make: "I like red!"
item_42009.Name: Quality Breastplate

item_4201.Description: For healing minor injuries. Used by First Aid abilities.
item_4201.Name: Simple First Aid Kit

item_42010.Description: The breastplate features a perfectly preserved Giant Snail shell.
item_42010.Name: Snail Plate Armor

item_42011.Description: Sacrificing armor for killing power, these robes are popular with wizards. A Necromancy Gem is woven into the chest.
item_42011.Name: Robes of Malediction

item_42012.Description: Imbued with potent magic, the ever-patching shirt is constantly fixing itself.
item_42012.Name: Everpatching Shirt

item_42013.Description: The best armor ever! Oh, except it rusts easily, squeaks a lot, is hot in the summer and cold in the winter, very uncomfortable, and particularly prone to lightning damage. And also it's not the best armor in terms of armor capacity. But ... but it's not bad.
item_42013.Name: Knight's Armor

item_42014.Description: It was in the bedding of Old Fangsworth's lair.
item_42014.Name: Tiger-Urine-Encrusted Shirt

item_42015.Description: Lawara the amnesiac was wearing this when she first awoke. It clearly used to be something special, but now it's barely holding together.
item_42015.Name: Lawara's Mangled Platemail

item_42017.Description: Another piece of once-ceremonial armor that was retrofitted for combat during the Elf-Dwarf wars. The suit has since become a favorite of elven warriors thanks to its handy odor-repulsion magic. And also, of course, its insane amount of protection.
item_42017.Name: Elven Ceremonial Suit

item_4202.Description: For healing moderate injuries. Used by First Aid 2 (and other abilities).
item_4202.Name: Basic First Aid Kit

item_42023.Description: Woven with fairy magic, this lovely shirt regenerates its leaves continuously. Unfortunately it is extremely itchy to wear. But noone said safety and comfort had to go hand in hand, so stop complaining.
item_42023.Name: Leafy Shirt

item_42027.Description: This gross shirt smells of urine. It provides no armor protection, and it's also very itchy.
item_42027.Name: Crude Undershirt

item_42028.Description: This simple platemail has sufficient protection, but it could do with more padding. Very uncomfortable!
item_42028.Name: Sturdy Shirt

item_42029.Description: Simple in design, but heavy on the armor plating.
item_42029.Name: Extra-Sturdy Shirt

item_4203.Description: For healing serious injuries. Used by First Aid 3 (and other abilities).
item_4203.Name: Good First Aid Kit

item_42030.Description: Rust damage has taken a heavy toll on this breastplate. It's still functional, but you'll probably get rust stains all over yourself.
item_42030.Name: Corroded Breastplate

item_42031.Description: Somehow this breastplate got stuck onto a spider via sticky web! What are the odds? Unfortunately, spider acid has filled it with holes, but what a great story!
item_42031.Name: Spider-Worn Coat

item_42032.Description: This breastplate is very old, and a sequence of enchantments has been laid atop it to protect it from the elements. An active symbol of Arisetsu is barely visible under layers of rust and paint.
item_42032.Name: Hunter's Breastplate

item_42033.Description: It's cotton! Breathable, pleasant, cotton. Yep. Cotton.
item_42033.Name: Cotton Undershirt

item_42034.Description: Inlaid with beautiful silver filigree, this cozy shirt looks gorgeous. A universal holy symbol is embroidered inside, allowing priests of Arisetsu, Saledar, or Kirad to enforce their wills.
item_42034.Name: Silver-Threaded Shirt

item_42035.Description: This tough leather armor is interwoven with magical threads that supposedly keep psionic attacks at bay.
item_42035.Name: Orcish Coat

item_42036.Description: When you don this strange metal suit, you can feel your sense of empathy and community diminish. All the better to kill without remorse!
item_42036.Name: Coat of the Winter Court

item_42037.Description: When the dwarves were holed up under Serbule so many centuries ago, they didn't have a lot to do but make really resilient armor. The resiliency magic bleeds over to the wearer.
item_42037.Name: Dwarven Soldier Breastplate

item_42038.Description: Makeshift Summer armor. It grants empathy to the wearer, though only those who are attuned to such things will notice.
item_42038.Name: Coat of the Summer Court

item_42039.Description: Designed by a spiteful necromancer bent on conquering a city, these robes seethe with hatred. And it turns out that pure hatred is pretty warm, providing mild protection against the cold.
item_42039.Name: Robes of Hateful Comeuppance

item_4204.Description: For healing debilitating injuries. Used by First Aid 4 (and other abilities).
item_4204.Name: Expert's First Aid Kit

item_42040.Description: When thousands of Rakshasa warriors arrived on Alharth, they wore suits of armor like this, designed to accommodate all environments. The secret to their crafting is lost to the Rakshasa living here now.
item_42040.Name: Ravana Soldier Coat

item_42041.Description: The rings of this chain suit are ridiculously thick, resulting in a very protective garment that is pretty ugly -- and very conductive of cold and electricity.
item_42041.Name: Thickened Chainmail Shirt

item_42042.Description: Pretty shoddy workmanship... but hey, it's armor.
item_42042.Name: Basic Breastplate

item_42043.Description: This simple platemail has sufficient protection, but it could do with more padding. Very uncomfortable!
item_42043.Name: Sturdy Shirt

item_42044.Description: Strong armor with a strong statement to make: "I like red!"
item_42044.Name: Quality Breastplate

item_42045.Description: Itchy and viney, but the magic is impressively resilient.
item_42045.Name: Spring Fairy Top

item_42046.Description: This thick and ungainly thing was the preferred armor of the ancient Dwarven Stalwarts. It's easy to see why: this armor is very... stalwart.
item_42046.Name: Stalwart Breastplate

item_42047.Description: A strange mechanism that can augment an arthropod's venomous attack capabilities. (Only wearable by spiders.)
item_42047.Name: Harness of Poisons

item_42048.Description: Cozy and warm, with lots of fur trim.
item_42048.Name: Syndra's Winter Coat

item_42049.Description: Worn leather with metal meticulously inserted into it. Whoever made this lacked skill in leatherworking, but made up for it with time and attention to detail.
item_42049.Name: Desert Vagabond Shirt

item_4205.Description: For healing devastating injuries. Used by First Aid 5 (and other abilities).
item_4205.Name: Master First Aid Kit

item_42050.Description: This is the latest masterpiece of rakshasa leatherworking, designed to replace the old Ravana armor they can no longer create. In many ways, this surpasses anything from their homeworld, a testament to rakshasa skill... and the toughness of beasts in Alharth.
item_42050.Name: Rakshasian Elite Coat

item_42051.Description: Thick matted hair combined with spider silk. It's kind of sticky, making it a little too form-fitting. It's surprisingly durable, though!
item_42051.Name: Yeti Jacket

item_42052.Description: Pretty shoddy workmanship... but hey, it's armor.
item_42052.Name: Basic Breastplate

item_42053.Description: The isolated elf colony of Sedgewick Forest prefers armor of this type because it reminds them of their home in Verta. It's been explained to them that nobody in Verta dresses this way anymore, but they don't seem to care. A symbol of Arisetsu is painted onto the front.
item_42053.Name: Thentree Harness

item_42054.Description: When you don this strange metal suit, you can feel your sense of empathy and community diminish. All the better to kill without remorse!
item_42054.Name: Great Coat of the Winter Court

item_42055.Description: Used by the typical troops of the Crone Hegemony.
item_42055.Name: Peltast Coat

item_42056.Description: It's gotten a bit frayed from use, but it's still thick and warm.
item_42056.Name: Insulated Coat

item_42057.Description: Made of giant beetle and scorpion carapace, this stifling, awkward, and heavy coat rewards those who have the fortitude to endure wearing it.
EffectDescs: You reflect 5% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_42057.Name: Scorpiclaw Suit

item_42058.Description: The general seems to have customized this Scorpiclaw suit to his own strange needs: there's a hidden compartment inside.
EffectDescs: You reflect 5% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_42058.Name: General Pask's Armor

item_42059.Description: The preferred armor of goblin tribes on serious budget crunches.
item_42059.Name: Cheap Goblin Chain Shirt

item_4206.Description: For healing heinous injuries. Used by First Aid 6 and 7 (and other abilities).
item_4206.Name: Amazing First Aid Kit

item_42060.Description: Sewn by an expert tailor in Rahu, this gown is lovely, but apparently not lovely enough, since it was discarded.

item_42061.Description: It's seen years of freezing cold weather, digging in the dirt, and horrific violence. It's surprisingly clean for all that.
item_42061.Name: Orcish Military Coat

item_42062.Description: This armor is feared in any land where orcs are known.
item_42062.Name: Snowblood Misery Trooper Armor

item_42063.Description: Worn by orcish mages after they've been promoted to 'Magic Trooper', which is the highest rank they can expect to reach, given mages' glass ceiling in orcish society.
item_42063.Name: Orcish Magic Trooper Coat

item_42064.Description: For the mage who needs to clear a sewer in the morning and dance at a ball in the evening.
item_42064.Name: Suave Mage Shirt

item_42065.Description: This red-tinted armor is worn by Gazluk City's front-line soldiers, known as "Death Troopers". Their armor enhances their strength and melee prowess.
item_42065.Name: Death Trooper Armor

item_42066.Description: This blue-tinted armor is worn by Gazluk City's support soldiers, known as "Misery Troopers". Their armor is strong while also providing survival protection in harsh weather.
item_42066.Name: Misery Trooper Armor

item_42067.Description: This green-tinted armor is worn by Gazluk City's gadgeteers and tacticians, known as "Treachery Troopers". Their armor protects them from battlefield conditions and enhances their tricky combat techniques.
item_42067.Name: Treachery Trooper Armor

item_42068.Description: This gold-tinted armor is worn by the highest battlefield officers in Gazluk City's army. It is versatile and strong, like its wearer.
item_42068.Name: Gazluk Officer Armor

item_42069.Description: This cloth armor is worn by the few Gazluk wizards who have become officers. It is designed to aid powerful spellcasters.
item_42069.Name: War-Wizard Officer Coat

item_4207.Description: For healing devastating injuries. Used by First Aid 5 (and other abilities).

item_42070.Description: The terrifying orcish cult known as the Mutterers wear these garments. This piece is fitted with a Necromancy Gem.
item_42070.Name: Mutterer Necromancer Coat

item_42071.Description: The terrifying orcish cult known as the Mutterers wear these garments.
item_42071.Name: Mutterer Cabalist Coat

item_42073.Description: These coats were a gift from the Crone Hegemony to Gob-land guerillas who were trying to free enslaved ratkin. Since the Hegemony is not against slavery in general, it's generally assumed they were just trying to stir up disharmony in the Gob-lands... but perhaps there was an ulterior motive. Anyway, they're still in pretty good shape a decade later.
item_42073.Name: Ratkin Revolutionist Coat

item_42074.Description: Created by the orcs of Gazluk as part of a short-lived coalition with the neighboring Council Lands. The "Pathfinders of Kur" initiative would have been a mixed-race team of orcs and humans that patrolled and mapped the vast mountain range. Unfortunately one of the human diplomats to Kur drunkenly revealed that the Council cared little about Kur itself, but mostly wanted this opportunity to work cooperatively with the orcs and perhaps build comeraderie. The orcs perceived it as "manipulative human trickery", killed the diplomat, and called the alliance off. But the armor had already been delivered. It's pretty good.
item_42074.Name: Council Pathfinder Armor

item_42075.Description: Extraordinarily light armor that is very cold to the touch.
item_42075.Name: Winter Court Battle-Coat

item_42076.Description: When you don this strange glowing metal suit, you can feel your sense of empathy and community diminish. All the better to kill without remorse!
item_42076.Name: Winter Court Murder-Coat

item_42077.Description: Expertly made out of a barghest, or something similar.

item_42078.Description: These massive seashells have been reinforced with a thin layer of wood, making for uncomfortable but effective armor. (Includes random level 35 enchantments.)

item_42079.Description: These massive seashells have been reinforced with a thin layer of wood, making for uncomfortable but effective armor. (Includes random level 40 enchantments.)

item_43007.Description: Who doesn't love steel plate armor on your hands? Well... besides wizards?

item_43014.Description: Thick smelly gloves that have been through a few fights
item_43014.Name: Goblin Gloves

item_43015.Description: Light, delicate gloves that seem far more fragile than they really are.

item_43017.Description: Insulated gloves for the most demanding of environments.
item_43017.Name: Temperature Control Gloves

item_43018.Description: Well, there's no name inscribed on them or anything. But you could give them a name if you wanted! The symbol of some god is etched on the inside.

item_4302.Description: For repairing moderate armor damage. Used by Armor Patching abilities.

item_43024.Description: These still get insanely hot and sweaty when worn, but at least they're kind of fashionable. Kind of.
item_43024.Name: Decent Leather Gloves

item_43025.Description: Made of reasonable materials, these gloves are nice. Just nice.
item_43025.Name: Nice Leather Gloves

item_43026.Description: These gloves were made by someone with a keen sense of anatomy, allowing a full range of motion.
item_43026.Name: Quality Leather Gloves

item_43027.Description: Pleasant to wear and reasonably protective.

item_43028.Description: These soft elegant gloves have custom gripping surfaces to make sure you never slip up in combat.

item_43068.Description: These were designed for the ratkin by the Crone Hegemony. The crones underestimated how long ratkin fingernails grow, and these gloves are now pretty holey. Still good for punching though.
item_43068.Name: Ratkin Revolutionist Gloves

item_43069.Description: While decades old, these gloves have never been worn in combat. They were crafted for "all-weather exploration", but to the orcs that made them, that mostly meant "cold-weather exploration".
item_43069.Name: Council Pathfinder Gloves

item_4307.Description: For repairing devastating armor damage. Used by Armor Patching abilities.
item_4307.Name: Astounding Armor Patch Kit

item_43070.Description: These freezing-cold gloves are hard to don, but once worn, they reveal themselves to be remarkably dextrous.
item_43070.Name: Winter Court Battle-Gauntlets

item_43071.Description: These glowing metal gloves are hard to don, but once worn, they reveal themselves to be remarkably dextrous.
item_43071.Name: Winter Court Murder-Gauntlets

item_43072.Description: Inlaid with intricate patterns that are incredibly precise. The palms have tiny quick-access pockets, too!
item_43072.Name: Felmer's Famous Fingerfangles

item_43073.Description: These gloves are made of woven fishgut and then adorned with strong shells. Odd, but wearable. Includes a built-in utility knife for opening oysters. (Includes random level 35 enchantments.)
item_43073.Name: Seashell Gloves

item_43074.Description: These gloves are made of woven fishgut and then adorned with strong shells. Odd, but wearable. Includes a built-in utility knife for opening oysters. (Includes random level 40 enchantments.)
item_43074.Name: Fancy Seashell Gloves

item_43075.Description: These gloves are made of woven fishgut and then adorned with strong shells. Odd, but wearable. Includes a built-in utility knife for opening oysters. (Includes random level 45 enchantments.)
item_43075.Name: Extra-Fancy Seashell Gloves

item_43077.Description: Tight dried-kelp gloves worn by ranalon. They're a little itchy.
item_43077.Name: Kelp Gloves

item_43078.Description: Tight dried-kelp gloves worn by ranalon. They're a little itchy.
item_43078.Name: Tough Kelp Gloves

item_43079.Description: Protects your hands so well that you can even punch harder than before.
item_43079.Name: Goblin Fist Wraps

item_43080.Description: Part of the uniform worn on fae ships. The stretchy gloves seem especially designed for precision work.
item_43080.Name: Fae Navy Gloves

item_43101.Description: Warm and cozy without getting in the way of violence.
item_43101.Name: Ukorga's Furry Fistwraps

item_43102.Description: An attempt at perfect harmony: metal outside, wool inside. Unfortunately, the gloves get really sweaty and are prone to fungal infestation. Ew.
item_43102.Name: Ruggedized Gloves

item_43103.Description: The goblin-trained bear Graz was outfitted with these after he killed one too many overzealous goblin mages. (Only animals can wear these.)
item_43103.Name: Graz's Shackles

item_43104.Description: The legacy is one of rusting quietly in a cave for hundreds of years. A faded symbol of Arisetsu makes the gloves slightly warm to the touch.
item_43104.Name: Legacy Gloves

item_43105.Description: Decades of spiderwebs have made the joints hard to open and close. It's hard to make magical gestures while wearing them, but on the bright side, they're silky smooth inside.
item_43105.Name: Webbed-Up Gloves

item_43106.Description: Lost in a cave and worn by generations of insane werewolves, these well-made gauntlets have become infused with lycanthropic power.
item_43106.Name: Claws of the Undone Beast

item_43108.Description: These were once used in ceremonies, not combat, but they turned out to work pretty well there too, as long as you're not trying to do anything too terribly dextrous.
item_43108.Name: Elven Gauntlets

item_43109.Description: Designed by a spiteful necromancer bent on conquering a city, these cloth gloves seethe with hatred. And it turns out that pure hatred is pretty warm, providing mild protection against the cold.
item_43109.Name: Gloves of Hateful Comeuppance

item_43110.Description: When thousands of Rakshasa warriors arrived on Alharth, they wore suits of armor like this, designed to accommodate all environments. The secret to their crafting is lost to the Rakshasa living here now.
item_43110.Name: Ravana Soldier Gloves

item_43111.Description: Thick smelly gloves that the goblin Jumjab augmented. A Necromancy gem has been embedded into the right palm.
item_43111.Name: Jumjab's Necrogloves

item_43112.Description: Worn leather with metal meticulously inserted into it. Whoever made this lacked skill in leatherworking, but made up for it with time and attention to detail.
item_43112.Name: Desert Vagabond Gloves

item_43113.Description: This is the latest masterpiece of rakshasa leatherworking, designed to replace the old Ravana armor they can no longer create. In many ways, this surpasses anything from their homeworld, a testament to rakshasa skill... and the toughness of beasts in Alharth.
item_43113.Name: Rakshasian Elite Gloves

item_43115.Description: Thick matted hair combined with spider silk. These feel great. No, really. They don't look great, but they feel great. An ancient holy symbol has been inscribed inside.
item_43115.Name: Yeti Gloves

item_43116.Description: Wow, off-red utility gloves. Nice. I guess.
item_43116.Name: Basic Gloves

item_43117.Description: Warmth is the key goal here. They're a little clumsy, but not enough to complain about.
item_43117.Name: Insulated Gloves

item_43118.Description: Made of immaculately-carved pieces of giant insect carapace, these are a work of mechanical art. Heavy and prone to painful pinching, they are tolerable only to hardened warriors.
EffectDescs: You reflect 4% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_43118.Name: Scorpiclaw Gauntlets

item_43119.Description: These scorpiclaw gauntlets were personally adjusted by the revered general. They are denser and yet more agile than one would expect.
EffectDescs: You reflect 4% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_43119.Name: General Pask's Gloves

item_43120.Description: Worn to high-society functions by the elite of Rahu, these lovely gloves are also fairly comfortable.
item_43120.Name: Rahu Society Gloves

item_43121.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. The sinews were not properly cured and stink beyond comprehension.
item_43121.Name: Decent Snail Gauntlets

item_43122.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. Only somewhat stinky.
item_43122.Name: Nice Snail Gauntlets

item_43123.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_43123.Name: Quality Snail Gauntlets

item_43124.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_43124.Name: Great Snail Gauntlets

item_43125.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_43125.Name: Amazing Snail Gauntlets

item_43141.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43141.Name: Shoddy Werewolf Foreguards

item_43142.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43142.Name: Rough Werewolf Foreguards

item_43143.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43143.Name: Crude Werewolf Foreguards

item_43144.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43144.Name: Decent Werewolf Foreguards

item_43145.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43145.Name: Nice Werewolf Foreguards

item_43146.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43146.Name: Quality Werewolf Foreguards

item_43147.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43147.Name: Great Werewolf Foreguards

item_43148.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43148.Name: Amazing Werewolf Foreguards

item_43163.Description: Thickened cloth gloves with resilience but no panache.
item_43163.Name: Crude Cloth Gloves

item_43164.Description: Cloth gloves that fit well and don't look too ridiculous.
item_43164.Name: Decent Cloth Gloves

item_43165.Description: Gloves that combine comfort, safety, and fashion.
item_43165.Name: Nice Cloth Gloves

item_43166.Description: Gloves that combine comfort, safety, and fashion.
item_43166.Name: Quality Cloth Gloves

item_43167.Description: Gloves that combine comfort, safety, and fashion.
item_43167.Name: Great Cloth Gloves

item_43168.Description: Gloves that combine comfort, safety, and fashion.
item_43168.Name: Amazing Cloth Gloves

item_43169.Description: Gloves that combine comfort, safety, and fashion.
item_43169.Name: Astounding Cloth Gloves

item_43184.Description: Extra insulated to protect against winds.
item_43184.Name: Decent Winter Gloves

item_43185.Description: Cozy and warm, with lots of fur trim.
item_43185.Name: Nice Winter Gloves

item_43186.Description: Professional-looking winter gloves with heavy insulation.
item_43186.Name: Quality Winter Gloves

item_43201.Description: Leather gloves that are supple enough to play instruments with, yet protective enough to battle horrible beasts.
item_43201.Name: Quality Bard Gloves

item_43202.Description: Leather gloves that are supple enough to play instruments with, yet protective enough to battle horrible beasts.
item_43202.Name: Great Bard Gloves

item_43203.Description: Leather gloves that are supple enough to play instruments with, yet protective enough to battle horrible beasts.
item_43203.Name: Amazing Bard Gloves

item_43204.Description: Leather gloves that are supple enough to play instruments with, yet protective enough to battle horrible beasts.
item_43204.Name: Astounding Bard Gloves

item_4321.Description: Used in the most primitive of smithing recipes.
item_4321.Name: Simple Metal Slab

item_43221.Description: Soft, warm, and comfortable, without interfering with movement.
item_43221.Name: Decent Nimble Gloves

item_43222.Description: Soft, warm, and comfortable, without interfering with movement.
item_43222.Name: Nice Nimble Gloves

item_43223.Description: Soft, warm, and comfortable, without interfering with movement.
item_43223.Name: Quality Nimble Gloves

item_43224.Description: Soft, warm, and comfortable, without interfering with movement.
item_43224.Name: Great Nimble Gloves

item_43225.Description: Soft, warm, and comfortable, without interfering with movement.
item_43225.Name: Amazing Nimble Gloves

item_43226.Description: Soft, warm, and comfortable, without interfering with movement.
item_43226.Name: Astounding Nimble Gloves

item_4341.Description: A specially-shaped piece of hardened metal. This is used in the making of plate mail armor.
item_4341.Name: Simple Armor Stake

item_4342.Description: A specially-shaped piece of hardened metal. This is used in the making of plate mail armor.
item_4342.Name: Basic Armor Stake

item_4343.Description: A specially-shaped piece of hardened metal. This is used in the making of plate mail armor.
item_4343.Name: Good Armor Stake

item_4344.Description: A specially-shaped piece of hardened metal. This is used in the making of plate mail armor.
item_4344.Name: Expert-Quality Armor Stake

item_4345.Description: A specially-shaped piece of hardened metal. This is used in the making of plate mail armor.
item_4345.Name: Masterwork Armor Stake

item_4346.Description: A specially-shaped piece of hardened metal. This is used in the making of plate mail armor.
item_4346.Name: Amazing Armor Stake

item_44003.Description: A thick layer of mold lines the inside, helping to seal the helmet to your head.
item_44003.Name: Comfortable Ancient Helm

item_44008.Description: The finest in slave-made head protection.
item_44008.Name: Goblin Helmet

item_4401.Description: A simple skinning knife for beginning skinners. (Keep it in your inventory and you'll be given the option to skin the corpses of some enemies.)
item_4401.Name: Simple Skinning Knife

item_44011.Description: Named by a bard who was having a bad day, this jaunty hat is actually pretty despair-free. A symbol of Arisetsu was added as a tassle by a later owner.
item_44011.Name: Jaunty Hat of Despair

item_44012.Description: Knights love this sort of thing. Hope they don't go out in a thunderstorm though...
item_44012.Name: Knight's Helm

item_44014.Description: A fairly basic helmet with some unnecessary stylistic flourishes.
item_44014.Name: Flanged Helm

item_44015.Description: Truth in advertising: this is not a pretty helmet. It has other charms, though, such as a deep-seated aroma of spoiled cheese.
item_44015.Name: Ugly Helm

item_44016.Description: This hat was stuck to a spider for years. There's so much webbing that you can't get all of it off, and it'll keep falling in your face while you try to murder things.
item_44016.Name: Web-Coated Hat

item_44017.Description: A cotton hat that's good in the cold.
item_44017.Name: Cotton Balaclava

item_44018.Description: A horrific cotton cap. High quality in every way, but just... ugly.
item_44018.Name: Thimble Pete's Awful Cap

item_44019.Description: For orcs that rely on speed and stealth to survive, this leather helmet is the standard. It's not really the best possible cap, but standards usually aren't.
item_44019.Name: Orcish Cap

item_4402.Description: A basic skinning knife for novice skinners. (+2 to your effective skill when skinning.)
item_4402.Name: Basic Skinning Knife

item_44020.Description: Ceremonial armor refitted for battlefield use, this helm looks sharp -- and can make the wearer look sharp, too, provided they know how to wear it with style.
item_44020.Name: Elven Officer's Helm

item_44021.Description: While vaguely protective, this lopsided helmet is so unbalancing that you're almost better off just going into combat without a helm at all.
item_44021.Name: Shoddy Leather Helmet

item_44022.Description: Designed to protect from concussions and minor scrapes, this helmet has the serious drawbacks of reduced visibility, unpleasant odor, and terrible craftsmanship.
item_44022.Name: Rough Leather Helmet

item_44023.Description: While the craftsmanship is adequate, the materials are not, and this helmet looks more like a dead beaver than a helm.
item_44023.Name: Crude Leather Helmet

item_44024.Description: A well-made helmet that will keep you alive in combat. But you'll sweat profusely in it, and you don't want to know what it's going to do to your hair.
item_44024.Name: Decent Leather Helmet

item_44025.Description: A comfy helmet that is almost (but not quite) attractive, too!
item_44025.Name: Nice Leather Helmet

item_44026.Description: Good materials and great craftsmanship combine in a helmet that breathes easy and protects from nearly any injury.
item_44026.Name: Quality Leather Helmet

item_44027.Description: A helmet that's stylish and also functional! Great.
item_44027.Name: Great Leather Helmet

item_44028.Description: This helmet goes beyond mere adequacy. It says "adequate isn't enough!" It takes it one step farther, all the way to more-than-adequate.
item_44028.Name: Amazing Leather Helmet

item_44029.Description: A hat you wouldn't be embarrassed being seen in, and so light and protective! Anti-odor components keep it smelling fresh all day, too.
item_44029.Name: Astounding Leather Helmet

item_4403.Description: A quality skinning knife for experienced skinners. (+4 to your effective skill when skinning.)
item_4403.Name: Good Skinning Knife

item_44031.Description: Named by a bard who was having a bad day, this jaunty hat is actually pretty despair-free. A symbol of Arisetsu was added as a tassle by a later owner.
item_44031.Name: Jaunty Hat of Despair

item_4404.Description: A great skinning knife for expert skinners. (+6 to your effective skill when skinning.)
item_4404.Name: Expert's Skinning Knife

item_44046.Description: A jaunty cap with a crowd-pleasing feather. Carefully sculpted to look great, yet give maximum visibility so you aren't caught off-guard.
item_44046.Name: Quality Bard Cap

item_44047.Description: A jaunty cap with a crowd-pleasing feather. Carefully sculpted to look great, yet give maximum visibility so you aren't caught off-guard.
item_44047.Name: Great Bard Cap

item_44048.Description: A jaunty cap with a crowd-pleasing feather. Carefully sculpted to look great, yet give maximum visibility so you aren't caught off-guard.
item_44048.Name: Amazing Bard Cap

item_44049.Description: A jaunty cap with a crowd-pleasing feather. Carefully sculpted to look great, yet give maximum visibility so you aren't caught off-guard.
item_44049.Name: Astounding Bard Cap

item_4405.Description: A perfect skinning knife for master skinners. (+8 to your effective skill when skinning.)
item_4405.Name: Master Skinning Knife

item_4406.Description: A perfect skinning knife for master skinners. (+10 to your effective skill when skinning.)
item_4406.Name: Amazing Skinning Knife

item_44201.Description: This bizarre helmet affects the mind of the wearer ever so slightly. Just a touch.
item_44201.Name: Helm of the Winter Court

item_44202.Description: "Coif of Calamities" is inscribed inside, in tiny lettering. It doesn't seem very calamitous, though. Maybe it was some sort of ancient marketing campaign.
item_44202.Name: Coif of Calamities

item_44203.Description: The damaged remains of an intellect-enhancement helmet.
item_44203.Name: Intellect Augmentation Helmet

item_44204.Description: A resilient piece of history! Perfect for the dwarf fetishist in your life. Or you could wear it in battle, if that's what you're into.
item_44204.Name: Dwarven Soldier Helm

item_44205.Description: This was once a Winter Court helm that was repurposed. Instead of twisting the mind, it protects against such things.
item_44205.Name: Helm of the Summer Court

item_44206.Description: Designed by a spiteful necromancer bent on conquering a city, this hood seethes with hatred. And it turns out that pure hatred is pretty warm, providing mild protection against the cold.
item_44206.Name: Hood of Hateful Comeuppance

item_44207.Description: Fae blacksmiths have infused the metal of this helm with the essence of eternity, meaning that this helm has never not existed. Don't think about it too much.
item_44207.Name: Indestructible Fae Knight's Helm

item_44208.Description: When thousands of Rakshasa warriors arrived on Alharth, they wore suits of armor like this, designed to accommodate all environments. The secret to their crafting is lost to the Rakshasa living here now.
item_44208.Name: Ravana Soldier Helm

item_44209.Description: This ugly leather thing is supposed to be worn on the head, apparently.
item_44209.Name: Orcish Gladiator Cap

item_44214.Description: The face of a big snail has been made into a makeshift helmet.
item_44214.Name: Snail Mother's Face

item_44215.Description: It's a tough helmet that was once used by the elite Dwarven Stalwarts. But that was many years ago, and more recent wearers have not been big on armor maintenance. It's still a great helm, but you imagine it was once even more impressive.
item_44215.Name: Stalwart Helmet

item_44216.Description: Worn leather with metal meticulously inserted into it. Whoever made this lacked skill in leatherworking, but made up for it with time and attention to detail.
item_44216.Name: Desert Vagabond Cap

item_44217.Description: This is the latest masterpiece of rakshasa leatherworking, designed to replace the old Ravana armor they can no longer create. In many ways, this surpasses anything from their homeworld, a testament to rakshasa skill... and the toughness of beasts in Alharth.
item_44217.Name: Rakshasian Elite Helm

item_44218.Description: Thick matted hair combined with spider silk. The silk gets all in your hair and eyes and is rather uncomfortable, but it's really warm.
item_44218.Name: Yeti Mask

item_44220.Description: The isolated elf colony of Sedgewick Forest prefers armor of this type because it reminds them of their home in Verta. It's been explained to them that nobody in Verta dresses this way anymore, but they don't seem to care.
item_44220.Name: Thentree Helmet

item_44221.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. The sinews were not properly cured and stink beyond comprehension.
item_44221.Name: Decent Snail Helm

item_44222.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. Only somewhat stinky.
item_44222.Name: Nice Snail Helm

item_44223.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_44223.Name: Quality Snail Helm

item_44224.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_44224.Name: Great Snail Helm

item_44225.Description: Made of snail shells, sinews, and animal claws.
item_44225.Name: Amazing Snail Helm

item_44241.Description: Hammered together from simple materials, for a simple battle cow.
item_44241.Name: Decent Cow Champron

item_44242.Description: A better-made helmet for a better-made bovine.
item_44242.Name: Nice Cow Champron

item_44243.Description: Hammered and polished and ready for battle.
item_44243.Name: Quality Cow Champron

item_44244.Description: Hammered and polished and ready for battle.
item_44244.Name: Great Cow Champron

item_44245.Description: Hammered and polished and ready for battle.
item_44245.Name: Amazing Cow Champron

item_44261.Description: It's metal. It fits on a werewolf. These are the only positive attributes.
item_44261.Name: Shoddy Werewolf Champron

item_44262.Description: It's metal. It fits on a werewolf. These are the only positive attributes.
item_44262.Name: Rough Werewolf Champron

item_44263.Description: It's metal. It fits on a werewolf. These are the only positive attributes.
item_44263.Name: Crude Werewolf Champron

item_44264.Description: A reasonable-looking metal helm for a werewolf.
item_44264.Name: Decent Werewolf Champron

item_44282.Description: A cowl of the quality that a peasant farmer might wear.
item_44282.Name: Rough Cloth Cowl

item_44283.Description: A tough head covering. Ugly, but practical.
item_44283.Name: Crude Cloth Cowl

item_44284.Description: A head covering that begins to combine fashion sense with survival sense.
item_44284.Name: Decent Cloth Cowl

item_44286.Description: A cowl that makes the wearer seem more mysterious and aloof.
item_44286.Name: Quality Cloth Cowl

item_44287.Description: A cowl that makes the wearer seem more mysterious and aloof.
item_44287.Name: Great Cloth Cowl

item_44288.Description: A cowl that makes the wearer seem more mysterious and aloof.
item_44288.Name: Amazing Cloth Cowl

item_44289.Description: A cowl that makes the wearer seem more mysterious and aloof.
item_44289.Name: Astounding Cloth Cowl

item_44301.Description: This bizarre helmet affects the mind of the wearer ever so slightly. Just a touch.
item_44301.Name: Great Helm of the Winter Court

item_44302.Description: A blob of organic sentient tissue that you can kind of fit onto your head!
item_44302.Name: Lobe Hat

item_44303.Description: Used by the typical troops of the Crone Hegemony.
item_44303.Name: Peltast Hat

item_44304.Description: A garnet that floats around your head and emits light. This was obviously made by an apprentice still learning the craft. The enchantment is clumsy and the gem wobbles slightly in its orbit.
item_44304.Name: Orbiting Gem

item_44305.Description: Warm, warm, warm. A little smelly. But warm!
item_44305.Name: Insulated Hood

item_44306.Description: A freakish mask crafted by an unliving malevolence.
item_44306.Name: Empusa's Mask

item_44307.Description: A garnet that floats around your head and emits light. Not especially well-made, but it's still vaguely impressive.
item_44307.Name: Rohina's Mind Gem

item_44308.Description: This magic garnet can float around your head and emit light. It also emanates hard-won wisdom, and can whisper warnings and advice when you're about to do something stupid.
item_44308.Name: Monger's Boon

item_44309.Description: A terrifying visage made of hardened scorpion sinews backed by reflective beetle carapaces.
EffectDescs: You reflect 4% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_44309.Name: Scorpiclaw Mask

item_4431.Description: A versatile knife for skinning or butchering. (Keep it in your inventory and you'll be given the option to skin and/or butcher the corpses of some enemies.)
item_4431.Name: Utility Knife

item_44310.Description: The Onkara leader claimed to wear this mask even when resting, often saying that a true warrior could never be unprepared.
EffectDescs: You reflect 4% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_44310.Name: General Pask's Helm

item_44311.Description: A subpar goblin helm, dented and worn.
item_44311.Name: Cheap Goblin Helmet

item_44312.Description: Perfect for the pig that wishes it were something else. A symbol of Arisetsu has been hidden inside.
item_44312.Name: Pig's Disguise Kit

item_44313.Description: This clever costume is perfect for cows that need to go undercover. A symbol of Arisetsu has been hidden inside.
item_44313.Name: Cow's Disguise Kit

item_44314.Description: Deer can use this handy disguise to appear less conspicuous. A symbol of Arisetsu has been hidden inside.
item_44314.Name: Deer's Disguise Kit

item_44315.Description: A large shell has been lined with sharkskin and netting. It takes some practice to fight with this on!  (Includes random level 35 enchantments.)
item_44315.Name: Seashell Helm

item_44316.Description: A large shell has been lined with sharkskin and netting. It takes some practice to fight with this on!  (Includes random level 40 enchantments.)
item_44316.Name: Fancy Seashell Helm

item_44317.Description: A large shell has been lined with sharkskin and netting. It takes some practice to fight with this on!  (Includes random level 45 enchantments.)
item_44317.Name: Extra-Fancy Seashell Helm

item_44318.Description: This magic garnet can float around your head and emit evil light.
item_44318.Name: Ever-Glaring Jack O' Lantern

item_4432.Description: A versatile knife for skinning, butchering, oyster-opening, or skull extraction. (Keep it in your inventory and you'll be given the option to skin, butcher, shuck, and/or extract the skull of some enemies.)
item_4432.Name: Multipurpose Knife

item_44321.Description: A helmet sized for a large sow, with a simple but extremely durable design. It's hard to fathom why this exists, but it does.
item_44321.Name: Pig Soldier Helm

item_44322.Description: This dwarven-made pig helm was no doubt worn in an illicit pig-fighting competition. The powerful combat runes are carefully hidden on the inside of the band.
item_44322.Name: Pig Horned Helm

item_44323.Description: The horn of a deceased unicorn. Alicorns have many medicinal uses, but in the right hooves, they have formidable combat uses as well. This particular alicorn looks like it would fit on a deer's head quite nicely, bonding to the skull and enhancing their abilities.
item_44323.Name: Alicorn

item_44324.Description: This oversized hat was created by fairy magic for an unknown purpose. It's too large to fit on a human's head, but it would fit a cow's head perfectly.
item_44324.Name: Twee Cow Sun Hat

item_44325.Description: The horn of a unicorn, enhanced with some sort of dark metal. It looks like it would fit on a deer's head, bonding to the skull and enhancing their abilities.
item_44325.Name: Dark Alicorn

item_44327.Description: Sewn by Eveline Rastin for a friend.
item_44327.Name: Eveline's Comfy Cowl

item_44328.Description: Once used by ratkin guerillas, these cowls were later repurposed for cheese-storage, then un-purposed for that and re-repurposed as armor. As a result they smell a lot like cheese, which the ratkin consider a feature.
item_44328.Name: Ratkin Revolutionist Cowl

item_44329.Description: Foul-smelling and poorly-maintained, yet quite dangerous. Like ratkin homes.
item_44329.Name: Ratkin Necromancer Headdress

item_4433.Description: A bulky knife designed to pry oysters open. (Keep in your inventory to allow oyster-opening. Also provides a 7% chance for a bonus pearl.)
item_4433.Name: Oyster Knife

item_44330.Description: After his brother burned to death, Vagreef spent years mastering Fire Magic to create suits of fire-resistance armor. He planned to manufacture these suits for his entire gang of bandits, but he only managed to make one prototype suit before he was murdered. This was his helmet.
item_44330.Name: Vagreef's Anti-Burn Hat

item_44331.Description: This helmet was crafted by orcs, but was intended to be worn by both orcs and humans. The quality is excellent, but the most interesting feature is definitely the custom ear guard: the creators apparently believed that human ears are especially vulnerable, so they provided special removable padding to give them extra security. No-one knows why the orcs felt this was necessary, and the decision is somewhat troubling.
item_44331.Name: Council Pathfinder Helm

item_44332.Description: Apparently intended to be a gift to Ursula's mother, this cowl is very poorly made and offers no real protection. It has been enchanted with an apprentice-level spell that would normally not be very effective, but the enchantment has been repeated thousands of times over many years, and this has somehow cohered into a decent level of magic.
item_44332.Name: Ursula's Ri-Shin Gift

item_44333.Description: Although it would appear to leave the wearer completely blind, the magical helmet allows perfect visibility.
item_44333.Name: Winter Court Battle-Helm

item_44334.Description: This bizarre glowing helmet affects the mind of the wearer ever so slightly. Just a touch.
item_44334.Name: Winter Court Murder-Helm

item_44335.Description: This hat was digested by something unnatural, and now it exists only in the abstract.
item_44335.Name: Soulworm-Bitten Hat

item_44336.Description: Made of fae mollusc shell, a notoriously difficult material to obtain.
item_44336.Name: Mollusc Millinery

item_44337.Description: An ancient alicorn that's been fitted into a harness for a deer to wear. It's adorned with weird citrus-fruit iconography, which contrasts strangely with the extraordinarily sharp horn.
item_44337.Name: Greenberg's Horn

item_44338.Description: Flexible kelp material worn by ranalon. It smells exactly like you'd expect.
item_44338.Name: Kelp Cap

item_44339.Description: Flexible kelp material worn by ranalon. It smells exactly like you'd expect.
item_44339.Name: Tough Kelp Cap

item_4434.Description: A simple skinning knife made of magical ice. (Keep it in your inventory and you'll be given the option to skin the corpses of some enemies.)
item_4434.Name: Ice Skinning Knife

item_44340.Description: Oversized headgear worn by a supernaturally large skeleton. Various runes and a necromancy gem seem to empower it.
item_44340.Name: Betra's Coif

item_44341.Description: A device that floats around the wearer's head and conveys critical information during battle.
item_44341.Name: Fae Navy Communicator

item_44342.Description: The perfect hat for goblin chiefs: it has protection from loud noise, a secret compartment to stash your bribe money, and extra weight to make your headbutts really impressive.
item_44342.Name: Goblin Chief's Cap

item_4435.Description: A multi-tool embossed with the face of a smiling cartoon elf. The skinning and butchering tools seems decent, but the other tools would break if you tried to use them. (Keep in your inventory to allow skinning and butchering of corpses. +3 to your effective skinning/butchering skill.)
item_4435.Name: Pennoc's Penknife

item_44406.Description: It's a high-quality hat, although it seems unlikely that an average cow would appreciate the style.
item_44406.Name: Quality Cow Porkpie Hat

item_44465.Description: Cozy and warm, with lots of fur trim.

This particular control ring allows hares to use ice magic -- as long as the hare has already learned the rituals, of course.

item_44501.Description: Surprisingly clean. Orcs wash their hair more often than most would expect. While orcs don't especially enjoy bathing, they enjoy orc-lice far less.
item_44501.Name: Orcish Military Helm

item_44502.Description: An insulated helmet that is as frightening as it is protective.
item_44502.Name: Snowblood Misery Trooper Helm

item_44503.Description: Worn by orcish mages after they've been promoted to 'Magic Trooper', which is the highest rank they can expect to reach, given mages' glass ceiling in orcish society.
item_44503.Name: Orcish Magic Trooper Cowl

item_44504.Description: This tattered cloak would seem like an ordinary rag except for a thick Necromancy Gem carefully sewn inside.
item_44504.Name: Veil of Twighlight Pain

item_44505.Description: This red-tinted armor is worn by Gazluk City's front-line soldiers, known as "Death Troopers". Their armor enhances their strength and melee prowess.
item_44505.Name: Death Trooper Helm

item_44506.Description: This blue-tinted armor is worn by Gazluk City's support soldiers, known as "Misery Troopers". Their armor is strong while also providing survival protection in harsh weather.
item_44506.Name: Misery Trooper Helm

item_44507.Description: This green-tinted armor is worn by Gazluk City's gadgeteers and tacticians, known as "Treachery Troopers". Their armor protects them from battlefield conditions and enhances their tricky combat techniques.
item_44507.Name: Treachery Trooper Helm

item_44508.Description: This gold-tinted armor is worn by the highest battlefield officers in Gazluk City's army. It is versatile and strong, like its wearer.
item_44508.Name: Gazluk Officer Helm

item_44509.Description: This cloth armor is worn by the few Gazluk wizards who have become officers. It is designed to aid powerful spellcasters.
item_44509.Name: War-Wizard Officer Cowl

item_4451.Description: A large knife for cutting meat and organs out of corpses. (Keep it in your inventory and you'll have the option to butcher the corpses of some enemies.)
item_4451.Name: Butcher Knife

item_44510.Description: The terrifying orcish cult known as the Mutterers wear these garments.
item_44510.Name: Mutterer Necromancer Cowl

item_44511.Description: The terrifying orcish cult known as the Mutterers wear these garments.
item_44511.Name: Mutterer Cabalist Cowl

item_44513.Description: Traditional hat worn by humans during the winter celebration of Ri-Shin, the god of plants and trees. This version is moderately uncomfortable.

item_44522.Description: This variant of the Ri-Shin hat is used by humans to differentiate teams for winter games. Vol-Mu, or Volmue, is a long-deceased god of winter. In the human telling of the myth, Ri-Shin defeated Vol-Mu to allow spring to return to the land.
