item_45001.Description: Well, you wouldn't want to eat off this shield, that's for sure. But why would you eat off a shield? Just strap it on your arm, weirdo.
item_45001.Name: Moldy Ancient Shield

item_45003.Description: This sucker's seen some good times and some bad times. But mostly bad times, from the shield's point of view.
item_45003.Name: Battle-Hardened Shield

item_45004.Description: If this shield is so lucky, why did Marna give it away? Still, it seems pretty sturdy.
item_45004.Name: Marna's Lucky Shield

item_45005.Description: It's wood with some thin metal plating over it. Pretty sturdy, and also lightweight.
item_45005.Name: Sturdy Shield

item_45006.Description: Etchings in the Goblin language roughly translate to "I Bash Really Well". It sounds better in the native tongue.
item_45006.Name: Goblin Shield

item_45007.Description: Etchings in the Goblin language roughly translate to "I Don't Care About Your Feelings". It sounds better in the native tongue.
item_45007.Name: Goblin Shield

item_4501.Description: Perfect for making maps, surveys, wills, poetry, you name it.
item_4501.Name: Simple Parchment

item_45010.Description: "You'll look protected yet stylish with the latest quality shield from Helena's Quality Killsuits."
item_45010.Name: Quality Shield

item_45011.Description: Made from a perfectly preserved Giant Snail shell.
item_45011.Name: Snail Shield

item_45012.Description: This was once owned by a powerful shaman who protected cute woodland animals. A tiny bit of his soul resides in this shield. If you don't use it, you're throwing away his life's work!
item_45012.Name: Defender of the Frail

item_45013.Description: This antique shield once had an insignia, but it's been dented and scratched beyond recognition.
item_45013.Name: Nameless Guardian's Shield

item_45014.Description: "You'll look protected yet stylish with the latest quality shield from Helena's Quality Killsuits."
item_45014.Name: Quality Shield

item_45015.Description: A thick wooden shield, etched with magical runes.
item_45015.Name: Oaken Shield

item_45016.Description: Found stuck to a giant spider, this shield has been scarred and pitted with acid. It looks pretty badass, but it's not really very protective.
item_45016.Name: Acid-Pitted Shield

item_45017.Description: Obtained from a human named Tyler, this shield seems to have been well-maintained.
item_45017.Name: Tyler's Shield

item_45018.Description: It's somewhat melted around the edges, but still pretty sturdy.
item_45018.Name: Tyler's Second-Favorite Shield

item_45019.Description: A mass-produced shield for non-elite orcs.
item_45019.Name: Orcish Targe

item_4502.Description: Perfect for making maps, surveys, wills, poetry, you name it.
item_4502.Name: Basic Parchment

item_45020.Description: Although nothing special by elven standards, other races would kill for the secrets of the protective runes etched into this shield.
item_45020.Name: Elven Shield

item_45021.Description: Robust, like dwarves. Flammable, like dwarves.
item_45021.Name: Dwarven Targe

item_45022.Description: Obtained from a human named Nelson Ballard. It's not in the best condition, but it has been powerfully enchanted.
item_45022.Name: Nelson Ballard's Shield

item_45024.Description: It's wood with some thin metal plating over it. Pretty sturdy, and also lightweight.
item_45024.Name: Sturdy Shield

item_45025.Description: This shield was stuck to a big droach for decades. It apparently absorbed some of the droach's protective power.
item_45025.Name: Old Crusty's Backside

item_45026.Description: The elite Stalwarts used this sort of shield, embossed with protective sigils and a symbol of Arisetsu. It's hard to find fault with the design, except that it's super heavy.
item_45026.Name: Stalwart Targe

item_45027.Description: This is a fake: Ravana soldiers did not wear shields when they arrived on Alharth. This shield is a masterpiece made in the style of their armor.
item_45027.Name: Ravana Soldier Shield

item_45028.Description: Not many yetis use shields, but they aren't terrible. This one is made of super-thick wood that's been reinforced with pounds of spider silk.
item_45028.Name: Yeti Shield

item_4503.Description: Perfect for making maps, surveys, wills, poetry, you name it.
item_4503.Name: Good Parchment

item_45030.Description: The elves of Sedgewick Forest use shields like this for some reason.
item_45030.Name: Thentree Shield

item_45031.Description: This special testing shield grants the wielder immense health.
item_45031.Name: Admin Shield

item_45032.Description: The stock shield used by countless grunts in the Crone Hegemony.
item_45032.Name: Peltast Shield

item_45033.Description: An attractive longshield. The symbols on the back say "Lead Without Fear" in elvish.
item_45033.Name: Leader's Shield

item_45034.Description: Etchings in the Goblin language roughly translate to "I Have My Rights And I Don't Care About Yours". It sounds better in the native tongue.
item_45034.Name: Cheap Goblin Shield

item_45035.Description: A heavy shield with a strange fae magic.
item_45035.Name: Winter Shield

item_45036.Description: A stock shield used by countless orc armies.
item_45036.Name: Orcish Military Shield

item_45038.Description: Etched with weird runes of distraction, this shield is especially useful at attracting opponents.
item_45038.Name: Hypnotic Shield

item_4504.Description: Perfect for making maps, surveys, wills, poetry, you name it.
item_4504.Name: Expert's Parchment

item_45040.Description: Designed by blacksmith-in-hiding Torgan, this absurdly heavy shield can only be used by those with the most intense courage.
item_45040.Name: Torgan's Shield

item_45041.Description: These impressive shields were a gift to the ratkin, designed to be light yet sturdy. The ratkin also use them as plates, hats, and for myriad other things.
item_45041.Name: Ratkin Revolutionist Shield

item_45042.Description: Someone dreamed of this sturdy shield, then lost control of it.
item_45042.Name: Dream-Keeper's Shield

item_45043.Description: Sacrificing defense for maneuverability, this shield is for experts who want to deal more damage with their shield.
item_45043.Name: Finesse Targe

item_45044.Description: Made of the exotic ocean metal Orichalcum, this shield is light, strong, and durable. (Includes random level 35 enchantments.)
item_45044.Name: Shield of the Sea

item_45045.Description: Made of the exotic ocean metal Orichalcum, this shield is light, strong, and durable. (Includes random level 40 enchantments.)
item_45045.Name: Fancy Shield of the Sea

item_45046.Description: Made of the exotic ocean metal Orichalcum, this shield is light, strong, and durable. (Includes random level 45 enchantments.)
item_45046.Name: Extra-Fancy Shield of the Sea

item_45047.Description: It's made of ice! It will eventually melt, but it usually lasts a while.
item_45047.Name: Simple Ice Shield

item_45048.Description: It's made of ice! It will eventually melt, but it usually lasts a while.
item_45048.Name: Thick Ice Shield

item_45049.Description: Fashioned to look like ice, but significantly more protective.
item_45049.Name: Fae Navy Shield

item_4505.Description: Perfect for making maps, surveys, wills, poetry, you name it.
item_4505.Name: Master Parchment

item_4506.Description: Perfect for making maps, surveys, wills, poetry, you name it.
item_4506.Name: Amazing Parchment

item_4507.Description: Perfect for making maps, surveys, wills, poetry, you name it.
item_4507.Name: Astounding Parchment

item_4551.Description: A small glass jar used to hold dye indefinitely. It is not reusable.
item_4551.Name: Dye Pot

item_4552.Description: A clamp and a delicate hammer for turning gems into powder.
item_4552.Name: Gem Crusher

item_45521.Description: A poisoner's blade that's seen better days.
item_45521.Name: Rusty Knife

item_45533.Description: An ugly and not-especially-sharp weapon made of cold iron. Goblins use them when hunting fairies for capture.
item_45533.Name: Cold-Iron Knife

item_45541.Description: This beautiful knife is used in the elvish custom of Surreto Silosi, where young heartbroken elves impale themselves under the oversight of a healer. This rite of passage signals their entrance into the second of three stages of elven maturity. The knife is usually kept as a memento.
item_45541.Name: Lovelorn Blade

item_45553.Description: This is a favorite of goblin healers, who use it as a surgical tool more often than as a weapon. A universal holy symbol attunes it to priests of Saledar, Arisetsu, or Kirad.
item_45553.Name: Goblin Lifekeeper

item_45554.Description: This style of dwarven weapon has been in use for centuries. It makes an excellent stabbing weapon but lacks versatility.
item_45554.Name: Dwarven Gouger

item_45561.Description: A goblin soldier's backup weapon. The hilt guard provides protection at the expense of killing power.
item_45561.Name: Backup Dagger

item_45562.Description: A magically sharp dagger with complex weighting that makes it difficult for neophytes to master. A necromancy gem has been fastened to the handle by its previous owner.
item_45562.Name: Carving Dagger

item_45571.Description: A military dagger used as a close-quarters weapon by some armies in the Crone Hegemony.
item_45571.Name: Soldier's Pugeo

item_45573.Description: Enchanted with cold magic, this weapon is uncomfortable to hold at first, but after a while your hand goes numb and it stops being so bothersome... as long as you don't need to use your hand in combat for anything else.
item_45573.Name: Freezing Blade

item_45581.Description: The signature blade of the human assassin guild called the Shadow Keepers, this weapon design is now found across the continent. Whenever nefarious types scheme, a venomizer is likely at hand.
item_45581.Name: Venomizer

item_45582.Description: These excellent daggers are standard-issue for the Stalwarts, but few dwarves actually use them. They are routinely lost in gambling matches and then reported as stolen, leading to the dwarven idiom "goblins stole your dagger", which is essentially synonymous with "you have a serious gambling problem."
item_45582.Name: Stalwart Dagger

item_45591.Description: An ancient weapon from the War of Froliac, used by elves who were very, very angry. It is etched with an image of the elven begonia, a symbol of trust broken and secrets defiled. Unfortunately, other races don't understand the symbolism and seem to think it's kind of sissy.
item_45591.Name: Elven Dagger

item_45592.Description: Supposedly coated in blood from over 100 different sacrificed creatures, this knife emanates hatred and can lead to unwanted thoughts of murder. A necromancy gem is embedded in the hilt.
item_45592.Name: Controller's Stiletto

item_45601.Description: Made from a giant scorpion tail, this weapon is difficult to use deftly, but poisoners love it.
item_45601.Name: Scorpion's Revenge

item_45602.Description: Supposedly used by the Rakshasa forces that first arrived on Alharth, this weird weapon is definitely not typical.
item_45602.Name: Ravana Soldier Dagger

item_45621.Description: The freakish orcish spellcasters known as Mutterers use these ornate blades to enhance their spells.
item_45621.Name: Mutterer's Blade

item_45622.Description: A small but very sharp blade inlaid with ivory. The craftsmanship is very high.
item_45622.Name: Sirine's Ivory Blade

item_45623.Description: The favored close-quarters weapon of orcish archers.
item_45623.Name: Military Khopis

item_45624.Description: Fashioned after the long knife used by the Executrix of Command, the terrifying head of the Council's personal defenses. This is no match for the real Executrix's knife, but it is still an incredible weapon.
item_45624.Name: Executrix Blade

item_45625.Description: The preferred blade of elvish courtesans in non-elvish lands, this sneaky knife can be concealed almost anywhere. The hilt has symbols of Arisetsu and Errana.
item_45625.Name: Courtesan's Blade

item_45626.Description: An orcish chef used this to chop vegetables... and any drunk orcs that got out of line. Sharpened via an unknown technique, it cleaves through anything with ease.
item_45626.Name: Gut-Ache's Chopper

item_45627.Description: Designed by blacksmith-in-hiding Torgan, this cruel knife rewards the foolish warrior who dares bring a knife to a melee.
item_45627.Name: Torgan's Stiletto

item_45628.Description: A thin and non-descript blade that's been designed to maximize the impact of applied poisons.
item_45628.Name: Rick's Sticker

item_45629.Description: A weapon whose appearance belies the skill of the ratkin crafter. Making a blade this sharp out of junk metal isn't easy.
item_45629.Name: Ratkin Dagger

item_45630.Description: A common backup weapon for many types of fairies.
item_45630.Name: Fairy Dagger

item_45631.Description: A standard Ranalon utility knife that's also a dangerous weapon. (Acts as an Oyster Knife.)
item_45631.Name: Ranalon Dagger

item_45632.Description: A standard Ranalon utility knife that's also a dangerous weapon. (Acts as an Oyster Knife.) (With random level 35 enchantments.)
item_45632.Name: Tough Ranalon Dagger

item_45633.Description: A standard Ranalon utility knife that's also a dangerous weapon. (Acts as an Oyster Knife.) (With random level 40 enchantments.)
item_45633.Name: Fancy Ranalon Dagger

item_45634.Description: A standard Ranalon utility knife that's also a dangerous weapon. (Acts as an Oyster Knife.) (With random level 45 enchantments.)
item_45634.Name: Extra-Fancy Ranalon Dagger

item_45635.Description: This is a favorite of goblin healers, who use it as a surgical tool more often than as a weapon. A universal holy symbol attunes it to priests of Saledar, Arisetsu, or Kirad.
item_45635.Name: Goblin Lifekeeper

item_45637.Description: When held, this weapon seems to freeze the very air around it. A weapon of elite Winter Court troops.
EffectDescs: Knife abilities that normally deal Slashing damage instead deal Cold damage
item_45637.Name: Autofreeze Knife

item_45701.Description: A long knife held in the off-hand.
item_45701.Name: Basic Dirk

item_45702.Description: A long knife held in the off-hand.
item_45702.Name: Basic Dirk

item_45703.Description: A long knife held in the off-hand. It was once very sharp, but now not so much.
item_45703.Name: Rusty Dirk

item_45704.Description: A simple but robust off-hand blade.
item_45704.Name: Sturdy Dirk

item_45705.Description: A simple but robust off-hand blade.
item_45705.Name: Sturdy Dirk

item_45706.Description: A long knife held in the off-hand.
item_45706.Name: Goblin Dirk

item_45707.Description: A simple off-hand knife that's been crafted to exacting standards.
item_45707.Name: Quality Dirk

item_45708.Description: A simple off-hand knife that's been crafted to exacting standards.
item_45708.Name: Quality Dirk

item_45709.Description: An old dwarven tool. While unexceptional by dwarven standards, it's quite impressive to many other races, who use it as an off-hand weapon.
item_45709.Name: Dwarven Maintenance Blade

item_45710.Description: A strangely-weighted off-hand knife that's good for bashing as well as stabbing.
item_45710.Name: Heavy Dirk

item_45712.Description: An off-hand blade favored by some elven fencers, who use it in conjunction with a longsword.
item_45712.Name: Elven Dirk

item_45713.Description: A gimmicky off-hand knife with a spring mechanism to increase thrusting damage. The mechanism gets gunked up a lot, but on the plus side, the knife is VERY sharp.
item_45713.Name: Stabmaster

item_45714.Description: An off-hand knife used as a personal-defense weapon by some mages. It has a tiny warding glyph that diminishes damage.
item_45714.Name: Safety Dirk

item_45715.Description: An off-hand weapon with nasty barbs to cause as much traumatic damage as possible.
item_45715.Name: Bleeder Shiv

item_45716.Description: An ancient dirk that has been altered by dark magic. But don't worry, it's still sharp.
item_45716.Name: Corrupted Blade

item_45717.Description: This dirk has never not existed and will never stop existing. It was removed from the timestream by Romast, the god of Martial Arts, who is ironically long-dead.
item_45717.Name: Timeless Dirk

item_45718.Description: A sneaky ratkin weapon designed for poison use.
item_45718.Name: Ratkin Dirk

item_45719.Description: A common backup weapon for Spring Fairies that's beginning to find popularity among Winter as well.
item_45719.Name: Fairy Dirk

item_45720.Description: An old dwarven tool. While unexceptional by dwarven standards, it's quite impressive to many other races, who use it as an off-hand weapon.
item_45720.Name: Dwarven Maintenance Blade

item_45721.Description: Wielded by the more sinister variety of Winter Court fae assassins, this shiv freezes everything it touches.
EffectDescs: Knife abilities that normally deal Slashing damage instead deal Cold damage
item_45721.Name: Autofreeze Shiv

item_46001.Description: Well, it's still got a pointy end and a handle. It should work fine.
item_46001.Name: Moldy Ancient Sword

item_46002.Description: It's a sword! Looks pretty sharp.
item_46002.Name: Basic Sword

item_46003.Description: The hilt has been worn smooth with use, leaving indentations that make it easier for neophytes to know how to hold it properly.
item_46003.Name: Battle-Hardened Sword

item_46005.Description: This is a basic sword that Joeh custom-modded over the years. It has a unique hilt and "speed stripes" painted on the blade. Joeh had an entire joke routine planned for when someone asked him what the stripes were for, but nobody ever did.
item_46005.Name: Joeh's Old Sword

item_46006.Description: This sword is sharp. Really sharp. As sharp as you can probably get without imbuing it with magic.
item_46006.Name: Quality Sword

item_46007.Description: Forged by the most skilled goblin weaponsmiths in the tri-county area.
item_46007.Name: Goblinblade

item_46008.Description: Crafted by dwarven blacksmith (and notorious druid-hater) Goh Rastuk. It was going to be imbued with anti-nature magic, but Goh didn't get around to it. It's still a nice sword, though.
item_46008.Name: Naturebane

item_4601.Description: A rock for sharpening the blades of tools.
item_4601.Name: Sharpening Stone

item_46010.Description: Stained with blood, ash, and lightning scars, this dark, evil sword is cold to the touch. Which is kind of creepy. But it's surprisingly well-maintained, and wonderfully sharp! A necromancy gem is embedded in the hilt.
item_46010.Name: Blackened Sword

item_46011.Description: An old style of blade, favored by some werewolves but not many others.
item_46011.Name: Wolfbite

item_46012.Description: Silver is a poor metal for making weapons, and this pocked and marred blade shows it. But its effect against lycanthropes is quite pronounced.
EffectDescs: Deals +20 damage to lycanthropes,Dispels lycanthropic regeneration effects
item_46012.Name: Simple Silver Knife

item_46013.Description: An iron sword with a thick coat of silver on top.
EffectDescs: Deals +20 damage to lycanthropes,Dispels lycanthropic regeneration effects
item_46013.Name: Silvered Sword

item_46014.Description: Each orc is given a xiphos upon their attainment of adulthood. Made of cold iron, it has a broad blade that slightly favors strength over finesse.
item_46014.Name: Xiphos

item_46015.Description: It's a sword! Looks pretty sharp.
item_46015.Name: Basic Sword

item_46016.Description: This sword is sharp. Really sharp. As sharp as you can probably get without imbuing it with magic.
item_46016.Name: Quality Sword

item_46017.Description: This sword was stuck to a big spider. It's not really in good shape, but the holes in the blade make a neat whistling sound when you swing it.
item_46017.Name: Acid-Addled Blade

item_46018.Description: The  rune etchings in this blade were made by Elven masters. It is rare to find these so far from Elven homelands.
item_46018.Name: Elven Longsword

item_46019.Description: A very old style of Dwarven sword design.
item_46019.Name: Ancient Dwarven Blade

item_4602.Description: A rock for sharpening the blades of advanced tools or small blades.
item_4602.Name: Whetstone

item_46020.Description: A blade that has been in the Sedgewick family line for generations.
item_46020.Name: Sedgewick's Honor

item_46022.Description: Goblin-made, with a focus on sharpness over all else.
item_46022.Name: Goblin Cutlass

item_46023.Description: Rust has taken its toll on this blade, but it's better than nothing.
item_46023.Name: Rusty Sword

item_46024.Description: It has an inscription: "Ensorcelled by Official Council Battlemages. Not for use by Rakshasa upon penalty of triple-death."
item_46024.Name: Council Trooper Sword

item_46025.Description: This is a really old weapon design! They don't make 'em like this anymore, for better or for worse.
item_46025.Name: Antique Spatha

item_46026.Description: This short sword is fairly terrible for anything except gutting livestock. But it does that really well!
EffectDescs: Melee attacks deal +5 damage to pigs
item_46026.Name: Pig Sticker

item_46027.Description: The hilt has been worn smooth with use, leaving indentations that make it easier for neophytes to know how to hold it properly.
item_46027.Name: Battle-Hardened Sword

item_46028.Description: This goblin-made weapon uses a manticore tail as a powerful injector. It's not a very good sword, but it's a great poisoning tool.
item_46028.Name: Gouging Stiletto

item_46029.Description: Stained with blood, ash, and lightning scars, this dark, evil sword is cold to the touch. Which is kind of creepy. But it's surprisingly well-maintained, and wonderfully sharp! A necromancy gem is embedded in the hilt.
item_46029.Name: Blackened Sword

item_46030.Description: An Elven Longsword that has been customized and modified by an expert. Dozens of little lines have been scratched into the blade, suggesting perhaps that the weapon has been used to kill a great many of something.
item_46030.Name: Janet Lew's Old Longsword

item_46031.Description: A rapier-like weapon that also holds a strong cutting edge, this blade is the invention of Lord ErDrick, who was known for his expertise in defensive swordsmanship.
item_46031.Name: Lord ErDrick's Blade

item_46032.Description: Made for orcish armies by dwarven smiths under an ancient treaty.
item_46032.Name: Orcish Spatha

item_46033.Description: An evil weapon forged in a dark fire. A necromancy gem rests in the hilt like a gaudy bauble.
item_46033.Name: Fiendish Rapier

item_46034.Description: This odd weapon was made specifically for chopping attacks. The weighting makes it difficult to use for piercing.
item_46034.Name: Chopping Sword

item_46036.Description: Used by Gazluk orcs to inspire courage and/or fear.
EffectDescs: Sword Slash, Riposte, Windstrike, and Finishing Blow deal Fire damage
item_46036.Name: Flaming Gazluk Sword

item_46037.Description: Designed by blacksmith-in-hiding Torgan, this heavy blade yearns to spill blood.
item_46037.Name: Torgan's Spatha

item_46038.Description: A weapon design from a far-away land.
item_46038.Name: Aktaari Cutlass

item_46039.Description: A sturdy military weapon made for ratkin. Thanks to impressive magic, it seems undamaged by years of extreme misuse.
item_46039.Name: Ratkin Revolutionist Sword

item_46040.Description: Etched with the symbol of a long-lost elven family.
item_46040.Name: Lordling's Spatha

item_46041.Description: As soon as you wield this blade, you can sense its eagerness: it wants to be your partner in murder! Of course, good partnerships require sacrifice from both partners...
item_46041.Name: Bendith's Blade

item_46042.Description: An Orichalcum blade with a seashell motif. (With random level 35 enchantments.)
item_46042.Name: Shellmaster's Blade

item_46043.Description: An Orichalcum blade with a seashell motif. (With random level 40 enchantments.)
item_46043.Name: Fancy Shellmaster's Blade

item_46044.Description: An Orichalcum blade with a seashell motif. (With random level 45 enchantments.)
item_46044.Name: Extra-Fancy Shellmaster's Blade

item_46045.Description: A strange weapon made by trolls in a distant realm.
EffectDescs: Finishing Blow dispels one fire effect on you (up to 35 damage/tick) and restores 65 health
item_46045.Name: Murdebok's Blade

item_46046.Description: An extraordinarily light weapon. The entire blade weighs less than the gaudy gem in the hilt.
item_46046.Name: Fae Rapier

item_46503.Description: The fretboard is reinforced with steel to keep it from breaking at an inopportune moment.
item_46503.Name: Sturdy Bard Lute

item_46504.Description: The fretboard is reinforced with steel to keep it from breaking at an inopportune moment.
item_46504.Name: Sturdy Bard Lute

item_46505.Description: This once-high-quality Trancelute was left out in the elements. No amount of tuning will make it very effective.
item_46505.Name: Moldy Trancelute

item_46506.Description: This bardic instrument has a lovely, uplifting sound that makes it fun to play.
item_46506.Name: Jolly Lute

item_46507.Description: Mass-produced by competent artisans, there is nothing special -- or especially wrong -- about this lute.
item_46507.Name: Quality Bard Lute

item_46508.Description: Mass-produced by competent artisans, there is nothing special -- or especially wrong -- about this lute.
item_46508.Name: Quality Bard Lute

item_46509.Description: Made for goblins by craftsman slaves. It seems fairly old, and has a nice sound quality.
item_46509.Name: Goblin Lute

item_4651.Description: A customized hammer used by toolsmiths and weaponsmiths.
item_4651.Name: Peening Hammer

item_46510.Description: Augmented with magical sigils that enhance the lute's hypnotic properties. (The magic isn't strong, but it's noticeable.) One of the sigils happens to be a symbol of Arisetsu, enabling priest magic.
item_46510.Name: Trancelute

item_46511.Description: This ancient doomlute was severely damaged and then repaired by an expert. It still holds a bit of its magic.
item_46511.Name: Refurbished Doomlute

item_46512.Description: This is slightly louder than a normal lute, allowing more effective rallying.
item_46512.Name: Leader's Lute

item_46513.Description: Made by an expert craftsman in Rahu. The body is imported hardwood, the strings are high-quality grimalkin gut, and the unusual enchantments give it a deep luxurious sound quality. Not for beginners!
item_46513.Name: Rakshasa Lute

item_46514.Description: The strange symbols etched into this lute seem to represent constellations, but not ones you're immediately familiar with.
item_46514.Name: Starlute

item_46515.Description: Resonance sigils give this bardic weapon a potent boom.
item_46515.Name: Withering Lute

item_46516.Description: An ancient dwarven instrument from a long-lost age.
item_46516.Name: Doomlute

item_46517.Description: A gift from Rappanel, the elven bard. It has something of his signature sound.
item_46517.Name: Daisy

item_46518.Description: Made of wood from a world that you will never see (and if you did, all the trees are extinct anyway). It's a little small, but serviceable.
item_46518.Name: Fairy Lute

item_4652.Description: A customized hammer used by armorsmiths.
item_4652.Name: Dishing Hammer

item_4653.Description: A customized hammer used by smiths.
item_4653.Name: Shaping Hammer

item_4654.Description: A customized hammer used by smiths.
item_4654.Name: Tack Hammer

item_4655.Description: A customized hammer used by smiths.
item_4655.Name: Delicate Tack Hammer

item_4656.Description: A customized hammer used by smiths.
item_4656.Name: Grand Shaping Hammer

item_4657.Description: A customized hammer used by chefs.
item_4657.Name: Meat Tenderizer

item_46701.Description: A simple instrument made of animal horn.
item_46701.Name: Basic Bard Horn

item_46702.Description: A simple instrument made of animal horn.
item_46702.Name: Blowing Horn

item_46703.Description: A musical instrument made of ram's horn.
item_46703.Name: War Shofar

item_46704.Description: Made of a large animal horn and enchanted with magics that enhance its volume.
item_46704.Name: Blast Horn

item_46705.Description: Carved from a ram's horn by an artisan in Statehelm.
item_46705.Name: Quality Ocarina

item_46706.Description: Carved from a ram's horn by an artisan in Statehelm.
item_46706.Name: Quality Ocarina

item_46707.Description: A wooden instrument that was invented by lumberjacks in Sedgewick Forest to ward off treant saplings.
item_46707.Name: Stickhorn

item_46708.Description: Made of stone, this traditional dwarven instrument requires much skill to use.
item_46708.Name: Stonebugle

item_46709.Description: A wooden instrument with terrible and toxic enchantments. Even touching it to your lips causes slight pain.
item_46709.Name: Death Lur

item_4671.Description: A tiny batch of adhesive. It's used by crafters such as carpenters and fletchers.
item_4671.Name: Basic Wood Glue

item_46710.Description: Made from a sea-snail shell, this instrument has an ominous tone.
item_46710.Name: Leader's Conch

item_46711.Description: Made of a secret elven wood (not oak, despite the name), this horn has a warm but somber quality.
item_46711.Name: Oakhorn

item_46712.Description: A simple horn instrument that's been enchanted to make listeners more nimble.
item_46712.Name: Weaver's Ocarina

item_46713.Description: An instrument made of two ram horns, one embedded inside the other. The sound is terrible, so it is exclusively used as a weapon.
item_46713.Name: Echo Horn

item_46714.Description: This horn is made of shell and enchanted with protective runes.
item_46714.Name: Infallible Conch

item_46715.Description: This sort of instrument is said to be used by elves when they go to war. The last elven war is a distant memory, however, so it's unclear who's making these horns.
item_46715.Name: War Ocarina

item_46716.Description: Made from the horn of the extinct Destiny Ram, this instrument is illegal in six countries, including Verta. But it sounds great!
item_46716.Name: Destiny Horn

item_4672.Description: A tiny batch of adhesive. It's used by crafters such as carpenters and fletchers.
item_4672.Name: Advanced Wood Glue

item_4673.Description: A tiny batch of adhesive. It's used by crafters such as carpenters and fletchers.
item_4673.Name: Expert Wood Glue

item_46734.Description: A shell that can make noise.
EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in wind instrument performance.
item_46734.Name: Decent Musical Conch

item_46735.Description: A beautiful shell with a mellow sound.
EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in wind instrument performance.
item_46735.Name: Nice Musical Conch

item_46736.Description: A lovely shell that's perfect for bardic performances.
EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in wind instrument performance.
item_46736.Name: Quality Musical Conch

item_46737.Description: An exceptional instrument that's too complex for amateurs. This shell's intricate fingering is best left to bards.
item_46737.Name: Great Musical Conch

item_46738.Description: An exceptional instrument that's too complex for amateurs. This shell's intricate fingering is best left to bards.
item_46738.Name: Amazing Musical Conch

item_46739.Description: An exceptional instrument that's too complex for amateurs. This shell's intricate fingering is best left to bards.
item_46739.Name: Astounding Musical Conch

item_4674.Description: A tiny batch of adhesive. It's used by crafters such as carpenters and fletchers.
item_4674.Name: Amazing Wood Glue

item_4681.Description: A simple knife designed for beginning knife-throwers. (Used with the Knife combat skill.)
item_4681.Name: Simple Throwing Knife

item_4682.Description: A knife designed for throwing. (Used with the Knife combat skill.)
item_4682.Name: Basic Throwing Knife

item_4683.Description: A well-balanced knife designed for throwing. (Used with the Knife combat skill.)
item_4683.Name: Good Throwing Knife

item_4684.Description: A carefully-made knife designed for expert knife-throwers. (Used with the Knife combat skill.)
item_4684.Name: Expert's Throwing Knife

item_4685.Description: A masterfully-made throwing knife. (Used with the Knife combat skill.)
item_4685.Name: Master's Throwing Knife

item_4686.Description: An exceptionally well-made throwing knife. (Used with the Knife combat skill.)
item_4686.Name: Amazing Throwing Knife

item_4687.Description: An exceptionally well-made throwing knife. (Used with the Knife combat skill.)
item_4687.Name: Astounding Throwing Knife

item_4688.Description: An exceptionally well-made throwing knife. (Used with the Knife combat skill.)
item_4688.Name: Superb Throwing Knife

item_47001.Description: This staff has seen so much. Thankfully it can't talk.
item_47001.Name: Moldy Ancient Staff

item_47003.Description: It's charred and black from tossing hundreds of fireballs over the years, but it's still really comfortable to use.
item_47003.Name: Battle Hardened Staff

item_47004.Description: This was enchanted by a competent apprentice, but it's nothing special.
item_47004.Name: Sturdy Staff

item_47005.Description: An inscription in Elven reads "To my lovely Velkort, thanks for a great evening."
item_47005.Name: Velkort's Hand-Me-Down

item_47006.Description: This was made by an advanced apprentice, perhaps. While not a masterpiece, it avoids all the classic blunders of staff-making.
item_47006.Name: Quality Staff

item_47007.Description: Designed for inquisitive fire mages who like to explore new ways to burn things.
item_47007.Name: Inquisitor's Staff

item_47008.Description: The original Fatestick was created in a bygone age by Jessandra the Cruel, who used it to save an orphanage from frost bees. Afterwards she declared that the staff had somehow tricked her into being kind and discarded it.
item_47008.Name: Fatestick

item_47009.Description: So named because it makes a sort of swishing noise. Nobody said weapons crafters were good at naming things.
item_47009.Name: Swishystick

item_47010.Description: Well-suited for staff-fighting, but a reasonable fire staff as well. Versatility!
item_47010.Name: Balanced Battlestaff

item_47011.Description: Hogan the staff-fighter's masterpiece... Well, a reasonable facsimile.
item_47011.Name: Hogan's Crippler

item_47012.Description: The lich Khyrulek crafted this wand during her centuries as a living corpse. It works better for the undead, but it's still pretty good for living people. (Not suitable for use as a fighting staff. This only works for fire magic.)
item_47012.Name: The Galvanizer

item_47013.Description: Handmade by a fairy, this staff is embarrassingly dainty.
item_47013.Name: Jesina's Staff

item_47015.Description: Very sturdy, but with a hollow core that gives it a strange heft when swung.
item_47015.Name: Goblin Staff

item_47016.Description: Made of burned bones, this staff is great for necromancers or fire mages. Less great for staff fighting, because burned bones aren't exactly quality building material. It's topped with a necromancy gem.
item_47016.Name: Necromancer's Training Staff

item_47017.Description: A plain stick topped with a necromancy gem. Also works for Fire Magic and Staff Fighting.
item_47017.Name: Necromancy Test Staff

item_47018.Description: Elves create these staves when they're feeling old. The feeling usually passes after a few decades, though, and then the elves give them away.
item_47018.Name: Elven Staff

item_47019.Description: Honed to perfection by a staff expert who slowly went mad from Lycanthropy. It's a powerful weapon, though it is marred by long ugly claw marks.
item_47019.Name: Elerimon Staff

item_47020.Description: Infused with arcane protective rituals. While technically usable by fire Fire Mages and Staff Fighters, this weapon is designed to be wielded by those who fancy themselves healers.
item_47020.Name: Yagreet's Staff

item_47021.Description: Infused with arcane protective rituals. While technically usable by fire Fire Mages and Staff Fighters, this weapon is designed to be wielded by those who fancy themselves healers.
item_47021.Name: Yagreet's Staff

item_47022.Description: Given to neophyte druids to help them hone their powers.
item_47022.Name: Druidic Training Stick

item_47023.Description: This was the favored match-stick of a minor flame spirit.
item_47023.Name: Bonfire Summoner

item_47024.Description: This was enchanted by a competent apprentice, but it's nothing special.
item_47024.Name: Sturdy Staff

item_47025.Description: This was made by an advanced apprentice, perhaps. While not a masterpiece, it avoids all the classic blunders of staff-making.
item_47025.Name: Quality Staff

item_47026.Description: Orloaka the goblin sage augmented this staff by filling its hollow core with tears collected from dying unicorns. Unicorns that he burned alive! (They were actually rhinos, not unicorns, though, so the enchantment isn't all that great.)
item_47026.Name: Orloaka's Staff

item_47027.Description: Used by dwarves who must venture onto the battle field to aid fallen comrades.
item_47027.Name: Dwarven Medic Staff

item_47028.Description: This wooden staff is icy cold to the touch.
item_47028.Name: Freezing Staff

item_47029.Description: This seems to be made of enchanted ice. Kind of neat.
item_47029.Name: Staff of Ice

item_47030.Description: It doesn't have any sand magic or anything. It's just been in the sand a long time.
item_47030.Name: Sandy Staff

item_47031.Description: A staff with modest enchantments and modest grip and modest... well, let's just say the whole thing is 'modest'. In a 'not very good' kind of way.
item_47031.Name: Adequate Staff

item_47032.Description: A traditional druidic training staff has been augmented with dozens of arcane sigils and then dipped in ... something waxy. Probably something organic. Best not to contemplate.
item_47032.Name: Druidic Assault Staff

item_47033.Description: It's charred and black from tossing hundreds of fireballs over the years, but it's still really comfortable to use.
item_47033.Name: Battle Hardened Staff

item_47034.Description: It's charred and black from tossing hundreds of fireballs over the years, but it's still really comfortable to use.
item_47034.Name: Battle Hardened Staff

item_47035.Description: Inscribed with ancient rakshasa runes, this staff taps magic from another world, making it quite hot. A recent owner also attuned it to Arisetsu, further heating it to the point that wielding the staff is a bit painful.
item_47035.Name: Sun Warden

item_47036.Description: A customized staff with heavy weights on each end.
item_47036.Name: Roshun's Heavy Hitter

item_47037.Description: Originally popularized by the terrifying harpy mages known as the Winged Witches.
item_47037.Name: Winged Witch Staff

item_47038.Description: A weapon for experienced staff-fighters who wish to get a little more oomph out of their lunges.
item_47038.Name: Lunging Staff

item_47039.Description: This potent battle staff was used by the thaumaturges of Gazluk to train their pet hippogriff.
item_47039.Name: Hippogriff Prod

item_47040.Description:
Used by the elite Gazluk orcish tacticians.

Note: this halberd is considered a Staff, but it cannot be used to cast spells.
EffectDescs: Staff abilities that normally deal Crushing damage instead deal Slashing damage
item_47040.Name: Tactician's Halberd

item_47041.Description: Designed by blacksmith-in-hiding Torgan, this staff is weighted very oddly, rewarding users for truly committing to each attack.
item_47041.Name: Torgan's Staff

item_47042.Description:
The traditional weapon of Ranalon Guardians. This model is pretty basic, but still very effective.
Note: this weapon is considered a Staff.
EffectDescs: Staff abilities that normally deal Crushing damage instead deal Slashing damage
item_47042.Name: Guardian Trident

item_47043.Description: A common ranalon weapon that doubles as a multi-purpose tool. Ranastaves are sturdy enough to dig with and resilient enough to survive earth-magic being cast through them.
item_47043.Name: Ranastaff

item_47044.Description: Used by ratkin summoners to raise the dead and toss the occasional fireball.
item_47044.Name: Ratkin Staff

item_47045.Description: Made of a pretentious fairy wood, this staff is incredibly strong, yet gives in just the right ways.
item_47045.Name: Trueoak Staff

item_47046.Description: This traditional merfolk weapon has useful water enchantments, but unfortunately those same enchantments make it useless for fire magic. (With random level 35 enchantments.)
item_47046.Name: Staff of the Sea

item_47047.Description: This traditional merfolk weapon has useful water enchantments, but unfortunately those same enchantments make it useless for fire magic. (With random level 40 enchantments.)
item_47047.Name: Fancy Staff of the Sea

item_47048.Description: This traditional merfolk weapon has useful water enchantments, but unfortunately those same enchantments make it useless for fire magic. (With random level 45 enchantments.)
item_47048.Name: Extra-Fancy Staff of the Sea

item_47050.Description: A common ranalon weapon that doubles as a multi-purpose tool. Ranastaves are sturdy enough to dig with and resilient enough to survive earth-magic being cast through them.
item_47050.Name: Tough Ranastaff

item_47051.Description:
The traditional weapon of Ranalon Guardians. This model has a great heft and has been augmented with some common ranalon magics.
Note: this weapon is considered a Staff.
EffectDescs: Staff abilities that normally deal Crushing damage instead deal Slashing damage
item_47051.Name: Sacred Guardian Trident

item_47052.Description:
The custom-tailored weapon of a mighty Ranalon Guardian captain.
Note: this weapon is considered a Staff.
EffectDescs: Staff abilities that normally deal Crushing damage instead deal Slashing damage
Headcracker partially blinds the target, causing a 20% Miss Chance for 5 seconds
item_47052.Name: Lusssha's Trident

item_47101.Description: Come on, the bark isn't even fully removed from this stick! But it's pretty thick. (It will work for Staff Fighting but not Fire Magic abilities.)
item_47101.Name: Shoddy Melee Staff

item_47102.Description: Well, the bark has mostly been removed. Mostly. You'll only get a few splinters trying to use this. (It will work for Staff Fighting but not Fire Magic abilities.)
item_47102.Name: Rough Melee Staff

item_47103.Description: Look, someone figured out how to sand down the edges of a stick. Too bad the creator had no idea how to balance its weight. (It will work for Staff Fighting but not Fire Magic abilities.)
item_47103.Name: Crude Melee Staff

item_47104.Description: This staff is what you'd expect from a combat staff. Absolutely nothing special, though. This will work for Staff Fighting but lacks the runes necessary to work for Fire Magic.
item_47104.Name: Decent Melee Staff

item_47105.Description: Someone took a lot of time balancing and testing this staff to make sure it had the perfect weight distribution. This will work well for Staff Fighting, but lacks the runes necessary to work for Fire Magic.
item_47105.Name: Nice Melee Staff

item_47106.Description: Reinforced and quite sturdy. The weight distribution is slightly off because of the added metal, but it's hardly noticeable. This staff will work well for Staff Fighting, but lacks the runes necessary to work for Fire Magic.
item_47106.Name: Quality Melee Staff

item_47107.Description: The creator of this staff obviously had a lot of experience in making these. Largely metal-clad, but just the right amount of give from the wood. (This staff will work well for Staff Fighting, but lacks the runes necessary to work for Fire Magic.)
item_47107.Name: Great Melee Staff

item_47108.Description: This staff has a surprising amount of detail work. Grips at just the right places, metal tips, and a reduction of weight without adversely affecting durability. (It will work for Staff Fighting but not Fire Magic abilities.)
item_47108.Name: Amazing Melee Staff

item_47109.Description: This has all the relevant features that a staff fighter could want: durable, flexible, perfectly weighted, and makes a cool whistling sound when swung. (This will work for Staff Fighting but not Fire Magic abilities.)
item_47109.Name: Astounding Melee Staff

item_47121.Description: Come on, the bark isn't even fully removed from this stick! But it's pretty thick. Very basic Fire Magic runes have been crudely etched into the bark.
item_47121.Name: Shoddy Combat Staff

item_47122.Description: Well, the bark has mostly been removed. Mostly. You'll only get a few splinters trying to use this. The crude Fire Magic runes bear the mark of an amateur, but should work.
item_47122.Name: Rough Combat Staff

item_47123.Description: Look, someone figured out how to sand down the edges of a stick. Too bad the creator had no idea how to balance its weight. The Fire Magic runes look a little less haphazard, though.
item_47123.Name: Crude Combat Staff

item_47124.Description: This staff is what you'd expect from a combat staff. Absolutely nothing special, though. The standard Fire Magic runes have been etched into the wood.
item_47124.Name: Decent Combat Staff

item_47125.Description: Someone took a lot of time balancing and testing this staff to make sure it had the perfect weight distribution. Then Fire Magic runes were carefully sculpted into the wood.
item_47125.Name: Nice Combat Staff

item_47126.Description: Reinforced and quite sturdy. The weight distribution is slightly off because of the added metal, but it's hardly noticeable. The Fire Magic runes were burned through the metal, creating a neat tactile sensation.
item_47126.Name: Quality Combat Staff

item_47127.Description: The creator of this staff obviously had a lot of experience in making these. Largely metal-clad, but just the right amount of give from the wood. The Fire Magic Runes were burned in, and glow with comforting warmth when used.
item_47127.Name: Great Combat Staff

item_47128.Description: This staff has a surprising amount of detail work. Grips at just the right places, metal tips, and a reduction of weight without adversely affecting durability. The Fire Magic runes are elegant but understated.
item_47128.Name: Amazing Combat Staff

item_47129.Description: This has all the relevant features that a staff fighter or fire mage could want: durable, flexible, perfectly weighted, fire-spewing, and makes a cool whistling sound when swung.
item_47129.Name: Astounding Combat Staff

item_47141.Description: A symbol of Arisetsu has been crudely carved into this crude staff.
item_47141.Name: Shoddy Priest Staff

item_47142.Description: A symbol of Arisetsu has been etched into this inelegant staff. Functional but unimpressive.
item_47142.Name: Rough Priest Staff

item_47143.Description: A symbol of Arisetsu adorns this otherwise-uninteresting staff.
item_47143.Name: Crude Priest Staff

item_47144.Description: A professional-looking staff with fire magic and priestly runes etched into it.
item_47144.Name: Decent Priest Staff

item_47145.Description: All three common symbols of Arisetsu are inscribed in Elvish into this nice staff.
item_47145.Name: Nice Priest Staff

item_47146.Description: The Six Names of Arisetsu are etched in Elvish into this lovely wooden staff.
item_47146.Name: Quality Priest Staff

item_47147.Description: An excellent and versatile staff. All eight Suns of Arisetsu are etched into this staff, hidden amongst the arcane runes.
item_47147.Name: Great Priest Staff

item_47148.Description: Perfect weighting, professional sigiling, and understated holy symbols combine in this exquisite and versatile staff.
item_47148.Name: Amazing Priest Staff

item_47149.Description: This masterpiece includes the Six Names of Arisetsu, the Eight Suns of Arisetsu, the Four Priestly Runes, and dozens of other icons.
item_47149.Name: Astounding Priest Staff

item_4725.Description: A handful of magical ice from the fairy dimension.
item_4725.Name: Crystal Ice

item_4726.Description: A handful of magical essence from the fairy dimension. It is used in many fairy creation techniques and can also be consumed directly to restore health and wing luster. (Note: fairy dust is extremely toxic to mortals and should never be consumed by non-fae!)
item_4726.Name: Fairy Dust

item_47401.Description: Crafted by expert Winter Court ice mages for use in the eternal struggle of the seasons. (Although it's made of incredibly strong ice, it's not suitable for use as a melee weapon.)
item_47401.Name: Grand Fae Wand of Cold

item_47402.Description: Crafted out of magical ice that doesn't melt. (Not suitable for use as a melee weapon.)
item_47402.Name: Basic Fae Wand of Cold

item_47403.Description: Crafted out of magical ice that doesn't melt. (Not suitable for use as a melee weapon.)
item_47403.Name: Basic Fae Wand of Cold

item_4751.Description: A metal tube with a closeable valve. Used on alcohol barrels to make them easier to use. It is not reusable.
item_4751.Name: Keg Tap

item_4771.Description: A flimsy set of tools for picking locks. They'll break when used.
item_4771.Name: Lockpicks

item_4781.Description:
Powdered skull dust for use in consecrating items or places. Harukita, the god of Hate, and Kajich, the god of Fear, both appreciate this sort of thing.

(You can turn this special bone-meal into ordinary bone-meal by right-clicking the item.)
item_4781.Name: Simple Skull Ritual-Powder

item_4782.Description:
Powdered skull dust for use in consecrating items or places. Harukita, the god of Hate, and Kajich, the god of Fear, both appreciate this sort of thing.

(You can turn this special bone-meal into ordinary bone-meal by right-clicking the item.)
item_4782.Name: Basic Skull Ritual-Powder

item_4783.Description:
Powdered skull dust for use in consecrating items or places. Harukita, the god of Hate, and Kajich, the god of Fear, both appreciate this sort of thing.

(You can turn this special bone-meal into ordinary bone-meal by right-clicking the item.)
item_4783.Name: Good Skull Ritual-Powder

item_48004.Description: Shaped like a tiny pair of longswords.
item_48004.Name: Amulet of Competent Swording

item_48005.Description: A tiny metal fist on a chain.
item_48005.Name: Amulet of Unarmed Fighting

item_48006.Description: A tiny metal foot on a chain.
item_48006.Name: Amulet of Competent Unarmed Fighting

item_48007.Description: A figurine of a tiny metal fireball on a chain.
item_48007.Name: Amulet of Fire Magic

item_48008.Description: A figurine of two tiny metal fireballs on a chain.
item_48008.Name: Amulet of Competent Fire Magic

item_48010.Description: A figurine of a heart with many smaller little hearts attached to it. Eerie.
item_48010.Name: Amulet of Max Health +10

item_48011.Description: A figurine of two hearts combined. Weird.
item_48011.Name: Amulet of Max Health +15

item_48012.Description: A figurine of two hearts with little hearts coming off of them, as if they were in love. Creepy.
item_48012.Name: Amulet of Max Health +20

item_48013.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48013.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +5

item_48014.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48014.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +10

item_48015.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48015.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +15

item_48016.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48016.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +20

item_48017.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48017.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +25

item_48018.Description: A figurine of two wolves killing a deer together. So tiny and yet so detailed!
item_48018.Name: Amulet of the Pack

item_48019.Description: This is just some weird elven runes on a chain.
item_48019.Name: Eraphylle

item_48020.Description: This is just some weird elven runes on a chain.
item_48020.Name: Yyllastra

item_48021.Description: This is just some weird elven runes on a chain.
item_48021.Name: Eynophille

item_48022.Description: A tiny metal fist squeezing a man, who seems unperturbed. That's craftsmanship!
item_48022.Name: Amulet of Crushing Mitigation 1

item_48023.Description: A tiny metal fist squeezing a man, who seems unperturbed. That's craftsmanship!
item_48023.Name: Amulet of Crushing Mitigation 2

item_48024.Description: A tiny metal fist squeezing a man, who seems unperturbed. That's craftsmanship!

item_48025.Description: A tiny metal fist squeezing a man, who seems unperturbed. That's craftsmanship!

item_48026.Description: A tiny metal fist squeezing a man, who seems unperturbed. That's craftsmanship!
item_48026.Name: Amulet of Crushing Mitigation 5

item_48027.Description: A figurine of a tiny man with a sword in his skull, who seems to be unperturbed.
item_48027.Name: Amulet of Slashing Mitigation 1

item_48028.Description: A figurine of a tiny man with a sword in his skull, who seems to be unperturbed.
item_48028.Name: Amulet of Slashing Mitigation 2

item_48029.Description: A figurine of a tiny man with a sword in his skull, who seems to be unperturbed.

item_48031.Description: A figurine of a tiny man with a sword in his skull, who seems to be unperturbed.
item_48031.Name: Amulet of Slashing Mitigation 5

item_48032.Description: A figurine of a man with an arrow in his back, who seems to be grinning.
item_48032.Name: Amulet of Piercing Mitigation 1

item_48033.Description: A figurine of a man with an arrow in his back, who seems to be grinning.
item_48033.Name: Amulet of Piercing Mitigation 2

item_48034.Description: A figurine of a man with an arrow in his back, who seems to be grinning.

item_48036.Description: A figurine of a man with an arrow in his back, who seems to be grinning.
item_48036.Name: Amulet of Piercing Mitigation 5

item_48037.Description: A figurine of a woman with hearts glued to every surface of her body. Very disturbing.
item_48037.Name: Amulet of Max Health +25

item_48038.Description: An elegant opal on a thin gold chain. Tasteful.
item_48038.Name: Rita's Charm

item_48039.Description: Hand-made from a leftover snail shell, and infused with simple magic by Sie's fairy friends.
item_48039.Name: Sie Antry's Talisman

item_48040.Description: A figurine of a smiling man with ice-entombed feet.
item_48040.Name: Amulet of Cold Mitigation 1

item_48041.Description: A medallion with an abstract design. Perhaps it is mantis claws raised in victory. Or in pain.
item_48041.Name: Elzehatl's Insignia

item_48042.Description: A figurine of a grinning skull. But, of course, all skulls grin. A necromancy gem is in the eye socket.
item_48042.Name: Necromancy Test Medallion

item_48043.Description: Made of blackened metal and etched with demonic runes.
item_48043.Name: Tidal's Circlet

item_48044.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48044.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +30

item_48045.Description: A figurine of a man holding a heart in his hands. The tiny heart pulses with its own rhythm.
item_48045.Name: Amulet of Max Health +30

item_48046.Description: Blackened as if from fire, this metal glyph emanates controlled rage. A soot-covered Necromancy Gem is still affixed on the back.
item_48046.Name: Symbol of Hate Made Manifest

item_48048.Description: A string covered in weird little beads and shells.
item_48048.Name: Fae Bead Necklace

item_48049.Description: Used by goblin necromancers. A necromancy gem has been embedded in a case made of bone shards.
item_48049.Name: Goblin Necromancy Focus

item_48050.Description: Used by the goblin necromancer Jumjab. It contains two different necromancy gems, in case one gets shattered in combat.
item_48050.Name: Jumjab's Compelling Augment

item_48051.Description: A weird elven rune on a chain. Unlike most elven rune amulets, this one was mass-produced in Verta for export to other lands. Not exactly a triumph of art, but its protective magic is undeniable.
item_48051.Name: Ulnaphylle

item_48052.Description: An expensive necklace with a well-cut magic tourmaline. This type of necklace is often used by people who fear they are in danger of having a psychotic break, although it can only hold off the inevitable for a little while.
item_48052.Name: Soothing Medallion

item_48053.Description: A figurine of a muscular human with a huge pack on his back.
item_48053.Name: Amulet of the Rugged Traveler

item_48054.Description: This is just some weird elven runes on a chain.
item_48054.Name: Alamyneth

item_48056.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48056.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +50

item_48057.Description: A mirror on a chain with a subtle illusion. Enemies briefly see you as being far more beautiful than you are, then suddenly perceive you as being far uglier than reality. It's pretty unnerving.
item_48057.Name: Indicator of False Beauty

item_48058.Description: A tiny enchanted saw on a chain. But it's not just an amulet: upon command, the tiny saw can cut lumber at high speed! (This item acts as a handsaw.)
item_48058.Name: Cutting Blade Necklace

item_48059.Description: Foxes are beloved wizard familiars because they channel tremendous Power. This little metal image of a fox does too.
item_48059.Name: Fox Glyph

item_48060.Description: A fad item by the master of trend magic, Rea Shuloth. Rea's spell compelled everyone to love these necklaces, but even magic can't control fashion for long, and now these are seen as incredibly gauche.
item_48060.Name: Hexagonal Trendsetter

item_48061.Description: This bit of magical rhino horn can be worn as a makeshift necklace.
item_48061.Name: Rhino Necklace

item_48062.Description: A very old locket with a portrait of a human woman painted inside. The artistic quality is quite high. It is engraved, "Don't cry, but don't forget. Love always, Caroline."
item_48062.Name: Lord Serbule's Pendant

item_48063.Description: A small bag of something tied with a cord. You can't tell what's in the bag because it's frozen completely solid, and it seems impervious to any form of heat.
item_48063.Name: Claudia's Pouch

item_48065.Description: A figurine of a tiny brain.
item_48065.Name: Amulet of Max Power +30

item_48066.Description: Designed to let you drink longer without unfortunate gastrointestinal issues.
item_48066.Name: Gutsaver Medallion

item_48067.Description: Created by the famed elven jeweler Sharra, this necklace supposedly reflects the wearer's treatment of the poor. It doesn't seem to do anything like that, but nobody has been brave enough to ask Sharra what's up.
item_48067.Name: 'Treatment of The Poor'

item_48068.Description: A magical prize given to the first-place horse in the decennial Jamurra Derby.
item_48068.Name: Jamurra Derby Ribbon

item_48069.Description: This thin chain features an onyx figurine of an orc on a horse. Orcish rituals have attuned it to several gods, including Tast, Arisetsu, and Akhisa.
item_48069.Name: Tast Pendant

item_48070.Description: A jeweled collar given to a hippogriff by its orcish caretaker.
item_48070.Name: Beakhorse's Collar

item_48071.Description: A tasteful silver-and-pyrite chain with an opal pendant.
item_48071.Name: Gasu'um's Old Necklace

item_48072.Description: An elegant, but simple, medallion on a chain.
item_48072.Name: Gasu'um's Practice Amulet

item_48073.Description: A tacky necklace that calls upon Harukita, the God of Hate, to grant the wearer power. This power is typically used in pretty hateful ways. This necklace also acts as a necromancy gem.
item_48073.Name: Shoddy Harukita Talisman

item_48074.Description: A tacky necklace that calls upon Harukita, the God of Hate, to grant the wearer power. This power is typically used in pretty hateful ways. This necklace also acts as a necromancy gem.
item_48074.Name: Rough Harukita Talisman

item_48077.Name: Nice Harukita Talisman

item_48078.Name: Quality Harukita Talisman

item_48079.Name: Great Harukita Talisman

item_48080.Name: Amazing Harukita Talisman

item_48083.Description: A gaudy necklace worn by those that venerate Kajich, the God of Fear. It allows you to invoke his visage to strike fear in your foes.
EffectDescs: Equipping this allows you to use the ability Visage of Kajich 1
item_48083.Name: Shoddy Kajich Medallion

item_48084.Description: A gaudy necklace worn by those that venerate Kajich, the God of Fear. It allows you to invoke his visage to strike fear in your foes.
EffectDescs: Equipping this allows you to use the ability Visage of Kajich 2

item_5001.Description: This is a small amount of salt.

item_50011.Name: Tail Ring of Defiance

item_50012.Name: Nose Ring of The Seductive Cow

item_50013.Description: Designed to be worn at the base of a deer's tail, this brass ring is very cute.
item_50013.Name: White-Tail Ring

item_50014.Description: Designed to be worn at the base of a deer's tail, this brass ring enhances ferocity.
item_50014.Name: Black-Tail Ring

item_50015.Name: Nose Ring of Destructive Tendencies

item_50018.Name: Rattail-Ring of Screeching

item_50019.Description: Designed for a ratkin's tail but also usable by rakshasa, this small yellow ring smells like... cheese? Well, anyway, it stinks.
item_50019.Name: Rattail-Ring of Digestion

item_50020.Description: Designed for a ratkin's nose, but perhaps also wearable by a cow or pig.
item_50020.Name: Nose Ring of Foulness Protection

item_50022.Description: Designed to be clipped to a fairy's wings, these tassels exude a pheromone that makes many types of bees and wasps non-aggressive (unless attacked).
