item_50024.Description: Designed to be clipped to a fairy's wings, these enchanted tassels make a fairy fly slightly faster.
item_50024.Name: Wing Tassels of Swift Wings

item_50025.Description: A wooden ring designed to be worn at the base of a fox's tail.
item_50025.Name: Foxtail Ring of Pouncing

item_50026.Description: A wooden ring designed to be worn at the base of a fox's tail.
item_50026.Name: Foxtail Ring of Flow

item_5004.Description: This bottle is full of sugary water.
item_5004.Name: Bottle of Sugar Water

item_5005.Description: A really big, eerily preserved strawberry
item_5005.Name: Large Strawberry

item_5006.Description: A chunk of raw deer meat.
item_5006.Name: Venison

item_5007.Description: A chunk of raw pig meat.
item_5007.Name: Pork Shoulder

item_5008.Description: Crusty goblin bread that stays edible and nutritious for months, though it should be noted that it never tastes good, even when fresh.
item_5008.Name: Goblin Wheatbread

item_5009.Description:
A white-mold cheese with a pasty and nutty flavor.

Cheese Type: White
item_5009.Name: Mogyar Cheese

item_5010.Description: This bottle is full of cow's milk. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_5010.Name: Bottle of Milk

item_50101.Description: Designed to be worn in humans' pierced ears, these earrings help protect against the sickness that comes from being too close to glowy yellow crystals.
item_50101.Name: Earrings of Glowy Crystal Resistance

item_50102.Description: Designed to be worn in an elf's pierced navel, this ring helps protect against the sickness that comes from being too close to glowy yellow crystals.
item_50102.Name: Navel Ring of Glowy Crystal Resistance

item_50103.Description: Designed to be worn at the base of a rakshasa's tail, but also able to fit on the tail of a wolf or deer, this ring helps protect against the sickness that comes from being too close to glowy yellow crystals.
item_50103.Name: Tail Ring of Glowy Crystal Resistance

item_50104.Description: Designed to be worn in a cow or pig's nose, this ring helps protect against the sickness that comes from being too close to glowy yellow crystals.
item_50104.Name: Nose Ring of Glowy Crystal Resistance

item_50105.Description: Designed to be worn in the wings of a fairy or giant bat, these rings help protect against the sickness that comes from being too close to glowy yellow crystals.
item_50105.Name: Wing Rings of Glowy Crystal Resistance

item_50106.Description: Designed to be slathered onto the mandibles of a giant spider, this reusable paint helps protect against the sickness that comes from being too close to glowy yellow crystals.
item_50106.Name: Mandible Dye of Glowy Crystal Resistance

item_5012.Description:
A very basic mild cheddar cheese.

Cheese Type: Semi-Hard (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_5012.Name: Mild Cheddar Cheese

item_5013.Description: Smooth, luscious yellow butter with a strong sweet undercurrent. Perfect for elven pastries!
item_5013.Name: Sweet Butter

item_5015.Description: A bottle of disgusting stuff used in making cheese.
item_5015.Name: Basic Rennet

item_5016.Description: A bottle of disgusting stuff used in making cheese.
item_5016.Name: Strong Rennet

item_5017.Description: A bottle of disgusting stuff used in making cheese.
item_5017.Name: Pungent Rennet

item_5018.Description: This bottle contains the acidic runoff of the cheese-making process.
item_5018.Name: Bottle of Whey

item_5019.Description: This bottle contains the sweet runoff of the cheese-making process.
item_5019.Name: Bottle of Sweet Whey

item_5021.Description: A sour milk product that's useful in many recipes.
item_5021.Name: Sour Cream

item_5024.Description:
A cut of meat from a wild creature that's not normally used for food. The meat is low-quality but still useful in many dishes.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5024.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5024.Name: Cheap Meat (Legacy)

item_5026.Description: A big chunk of cow meat.
item_5026.Name: Steak

item_5027.Description: Dried "sticks" of cinnamon, perfect for spicing many dishes.
item_5027.Name: Cinnamon

item_5028.Description: Freshly-squeezed liquid out of a cactus.
item_5028.Name: Cactus Juice

item_5029.Description: Chicken meat that causes mild paralysis when eaten. An extremely exotic ingredient in food, but a common ingredient in poisons.
item_5029.Name: Raw Paralytic Chicken

item_5030.Description:
This cat meat might be fresh. Or it might not be. It's so gross that it'd be hard to tell the difference.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5030.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5030.Name: Sinewy Cat Meat

item_5031.Description:
Someone gutted a mangy cat.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5031.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5031.Name: Stringy Cat Meat

item_5032.Description:
Cat meat is never particularly tasty, but this is ... edible.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5032.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5032.Name: Cat Meat

item_5033.Description:
If cat meat tasted good, this would taste good.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5033.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5033.Name: Robust Cat Meat

item_5034.Description:
An unimpressive dog-like creature yielded this unimpressive "meat".

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5034.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5034.Name: Sinewy Dog Meat

item_5035.Description:
Well, someone's gone and chopped up a mangy dog.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5035.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5035.Name: Stringy Dog Meat

item_5036.Description:
It's dog meat, but at least the dog was probably healthy.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5036.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5036.Name: Dog Meat

item_5037.Description:
Dog meat is an acquired taste, but at least this particular cut looks fresh and juicy.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5037.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5037.Name: Robust Dog Meat

item_5038.Description:
A small and unimpressive dinosaur yielded this gross thing.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5038.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5038.Name: Sinewy Dinosaur Meat

item_5039.Description:
An uninviting dinosaur flank.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5039.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5039.Name: Stringy Dinosaur Meat

item_5040.Description:
It looks... edible. Huh.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5040.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5040.Name: Dinosaur Meat

item_5041.Description:
A hardy beast yielded this reasonably-appetizing-looking cut.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5041.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5041.Name: Robust Dinosaur Meat

item_5042.Description:
A mangy, possibly-diseased beast yielded this mangy, possibly-diseased meat. Mmm.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5042.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5042.Name: Sinewy Beast Meat

item_5043.Description:
Some sort of beast was used for this cut. You'd want to tenderize this. A lot.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5043.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5043.Name: Stringy Beast Meat

item_5044.Description:
This is a well-cut piece of crappy meat.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5044.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5044.Name: Beast Meat

item_5045.Description:
A large and bloody cut from a dangerous beast. Pity the meat doesn't look especially tasty.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5045.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5045.Name: Robust Beast Meat

item_5046.Description:
This might technically be edible, but the stench is almost unbearable.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5046.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5046.Name: Sinewy Insect Meat

item_5047.Description:
Stinky and stringy, but if you boiled it and hammered it... it'd still be gross.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5047.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5047.Name: Stringy Insect Meat

item_5048.Description:
This would be presentable if you were very clever with the presentation.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5048.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5048.Name: Insect Meat

item_5049.Description:
A hardy slab of insect meat. Good for dishes where the meat isn't the centerpiece.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5049.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5049.Name: Robust Insect Meat

item_5051.Description: A large odd egg. Edible if properly prepared.
item_5051.Name: Weird Egg

item_5052.Description: The meat of a large-sized rabbit. (Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5052.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5052.Name: Rabbit Meat

item_5053.Description: An exceptional piece of meat from a rabbit or hare.
item_5053.Name: Great Rabbit Meat

item_5054.Description: Sugar that's supernaturally sweet. A favorite of fairies.
item_5054.Name: Pixie Sugar

item_5056.Description: A bunch of seaweed, edible if properly dried and prepared.
item_5056.Name: Seaweed

item_5057.Description: Very basic vinegar used in simple dishes.
item_5057.Name: Basic Vinegar

item_5058.Description: Vinegar infused with a secret blend of spices.
item_5058.Name: Fancy Vinegar

item_5059.Description: This vinegar infusion is only needed in the fanciest of dishes.
item_5059.Name: Expert's Vinegar

item_5062.Description: The green flowers of the hop plant. Used in beer brewing.
item_5062.Name: Hops

item_5063.Description: Sweet sugarcane molasses, useful for cooking or making alcohol.
item_5063.Name: Molasses

item_5064.Description: An exceptional piece of meat from a deer.
item_5064.Name: Great Venison

item_5065.Description: An exceptional piece of meat from a cow or bull.
item_5065.Name: Great Steak

item_5066.Description: An exceptional piece of meat from a deer.
item_5066.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5066.Name: Amazing Venison

item_5067.Description: An exceptional piece of meat from a cow or bull. (Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5067.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5067.Name: Amazing Steak

item_5068.Description: An exceptional piece of meat from a rabbit or hare. (Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5068.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5068.Name: Amazing Rabbit Meat

item_5069.Description: A chunk of raw boar meat from an impressive animal.
item_5069.Name: Great Pork Shoulder

item_5070.Description: An especially flavorful chicken, ready for cooking.
item_5070.Name: Raw Great Chicken

item_5071.Description: Food-quality vegetable oil. It burns easily so is only suitable for certain dishes.
item_5071.Name: Vegetable Oil

item_5072.Description: Food-quality vegetable oil with a high burn point and a neutral taste. Good for many dishes.
item_5072.Name: Olive Oil

item_5073.Description: Food-quality vegetable oil with a high burn point and a pleasant taste. Extremely versatile.
item_5073.Name: Dwarfnut Oil

item_5074.Description: An edible plant with a spicy and slightly bitter flavor.
item_5074.Name: Watercress

item_5075.Description: This bottle contains salty water made via a secret ranalon technique. It's used as a marinade and pickling agent.
item_5075.Name: Bottle of Brine

item_5076.Description: A large biting beetle. There are probably ways to prepare this for cooking.
item_5076.Name: Beetle

item_5077.Description: A bunch of greens that grow in swamps and sewers. Edible if properly dried and prepared.
item_5077.Name: Swampweed

item_5078.Description: A spice with a bitter, fennely taste.
item_5078.Name: Dill

item_5079.Description: A chalky root with a flowery smell. Chewed by ratkin as a snack, and features heavily in ratkin cuisine.
item_5079.Name: Rattus Root

item_5080.Description: This bottle is full of goat's milk. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_5080.Name: Bottle of Goat Milk

item_5081.Description: A bottle of fairy honey, said to be more delicious than mortals can bear to taste. That's just hyperbole, but it's definitely an extremely rich and complex flavor.
item_5081.Name: Fairy Honey

item_5082.Description: The fibrous and smelly heart of a spriggan plant.
item_5082.Name: Spriggan Nut

item_5083.Description: Like chicken meat, but larger, and with a more pronounced flavor.
item_5083.Name: Raw Turkey

item_5084.Description:
A small, freshly-killed rodent.

(Use in Cheap Meat recipes.)
item_5084.DynamicCraftingSummary: This can be used in Cooking recipes that call for 'Cheap Meat.' In those recipes, all Cheap Meat behaves the same way, so use whatever you have handy.
item_5084.Name: Dead Vole

item_5085.Description: The fin of a large shark. It's supposedly edible.
item_5085.Name: Shark Fin

item_5086.Description: Not edible by themselves, but useful in recipes.
item_5086.Name: Coffee Beans

item_51.Description: WARNING! This spittle is contaminated with the Lycanthropy disease. Drinking it will make you a werewolf instantly and forever! There is NO cure.
item_51.Name: Werewolf Spit

item_51001.Description: Good for flinging small amounts of chemicals all around you. Held in the main hand.
item_51001.Name: Basic Combat Beaker

item_51002.Description: An extraordinary staff with an alchemical beaker on the end. You can use this for staff fighting or battle chemistry. It's not suitable for fire magic, though.
item_51002.Name: Hogan's Flingin' Stick

item_51003.Description: An unusual staff with an alchemical beaker on the end. Not suitable for casting Fire Magic.
item_51003.Name: Beaker-Stick

item_51004.Description: A beaker for flinging chemicals in combat. Held in the main hand.
item_51004.Name: Acid Beaker

item_51005.Description: A beaker for flinging chemicals in combat. Held in the main hand.
item_51005.Name: Splash Beaker

item_51006.Description: This beaker has been carefully constructed to keep healing chemicals at a lower temperature, slightly improving their effects. Held in the main hand.
item_51006.Name: Recuperative Beaker

item_51007.Description: This beaker is one of Xegatis' early failed attempts at restoring flesh to Nightmare Creatures. A crude Necromancy Gem is embedded in the bottom.
item_51007.Name: Beaker of Xegatis

item_51008.Description: The story goes that a crazed elf spent a hundred years splashing himself with different acid beakers to find the one that hurt the most. This is that beaker.
item_51008.Name: Maiming Beaker

item_51009.Description: This old beaker is perfectly shaped for gulping down quick-brewed healing concoctions.
item_51009.Name: Chugging Beaker

item_51010.Description: Good for flinging small amounts of chemicals all around you. Held in the main hand.
item_51010.Name: Basic Combat Beaker

item_51011.Description: Good for flinging small amounts of chemicals all around you. Held in the off hand.
item_51011.Name: Basic Combat Flask

item_51012.Description: A flask for flinging chemicals in combat. Held in the off hand.
item_51012.Name: Acid Flask

item_51013.Description: A flask for flinging chemicals in combat. Held in the off hand.
item_51013.Name: Splash Flask

item_51014.Description: This flask has been carefully constructed to keep healing chemicals at a lower temperature, slightly improving their effects. Held in the off hand.
item_51014.Name: Recuperative Flask

item_51015.Description: The great alchemists of yore supposedly used flasks like this when they fought in wars. Or perhaps that's just a tale invented to sell flasks.
item_51015.Name: War Flask

item_51016.Description: This old flask is perfectly shaped for gulping down quick-brewed healing concoctions.
item_51016.Name: Chugging Flask

item_51017.Description: Good for flinging small amounts of chemicals all around you. Held in the off hand.
item_51017.Name: Basic Combat Flask

item_51018.Description: While dwarves are mostly known for brewing alcohol, those same techniques can also be used to brew potent offensive chemicals.
item_51018.Name: Dwarven Brewer Flask

item_51019.Description: The creator of this beaker designed it around what he thought dwarves would use in combat. He was utterly wrong in every way, but the beaker is still pretty powerful.
item_51019.Name: Dwarf-Inspired Beaker

item_51020.Description: A beaker for exploding stuff. Held in the main hand.
item_51020.Name: Bombing Beaker

item_51021.Description: This cunningly made flask is slightly askew, causing chemicals to spray everywhere. Only experts can hope to use it in combat.
item_51021.Name: Lopsided Flask

item_51022.Description: The sneaky crone Anhinda made this flask after decades of trial and error.
item_51022.Name: Anhinda's Flask

item_51023.Description: Not great for splashing people, but pretty good for delivering healing concoctions.
item_51023.Name: Spillproof Flask

item_51024.Description: Shaped like a snake for some reason.
item_51024.Name: Serpent Flask

item_51025.Description: An ordinary-looking glass flask that's cold to the touch, even in hot environments.
item_51025.Name: Flask of Chills

item_51026.Description: The invention of a rakshasa alchemist who loved her pet. This flask's magic helps to alert pets when their owner is in danger.
item_51026.Name: Rathla's Flask

item_51027.Description: Some aberrant chemical reaction has burned off most of the crimson, but it's otherwise in good shape.
item_51027.Name: Crimson Flask

item_5106.Description: A raw fish. So-called because of its vaguely bluish skin, the grapefish is actually fairly bland.
item_5106.Name: Grapefish

item_51061.Description: A beaker full of a very, very stinky substance.
item_51061.Name: Fish Beaker

item_51062.Description: It has a splash-lip as well as a drinking lip, as if you'd be so foolish as to drink potions out of the same beaker you splash acids from!
item_51062.Name: Multipurpose Beaker

item_51063.Description: A mage's staff with a splash-beaker at the top, perfect for blasting and splashing at the same time.
item_51063.Name: Tricky Sage Beaker

item_51064.Description: This beaker has been coated in many layers of deadly chemicals. Wash your hands after touching it!
item_51064.Name: Tolmar's Beaker

item_51065.Description: A potent chemistry tool -- or weapon. Yeah, let's go with weapon.
item_51065.Name: Jar of Explosions

item_51066.Description: After barely losing the annual Statehelm archery contest, Tamoko gained fame when he returned the following year and used his newly-invented beaker to win the grand prize. The beaker design has since been replicated with his blessing, delighting archery fans but causing a terrible schism in the archery-contest establishment, many of whom consider battle chemistry to be "like cheating".
item_51066.Name: Tamoko's Beaker

item_51067.Description: Made of utterly unbreakable glass mined from the heart of a dying star, this is no measuring tool: it is a deadly weapon of war! (Because the measurement marks rubbed off long ago.)
item_51067.Name: Beaker of Formless Toxin

item_5107.Description: A raw fish. Found in caves throughout the world, these blind fish are normally tiny, but can grow to surprising size in nature-magic-rich environments.
item_5107.Name: Cavefish

item_5108.Description: A raw fish. Also known as Orcish Labyrinth Fish, these fish are surprisingly tasty when correctly prepared, but should not be eaten raw.
item_5108.Name: Green Vexfish

item_5109.Description: A raw fish. These strange fish originate in the distant continent of Fosulf. They require expert handling before they can be eaten safely, and few fishermen in Alharth know the technique.
item_5109.Name: Lungfish

item_5110.Description: A raw fish. These hideous creatures are surprisingly tasty.
item_5110.Name: Flounder

item_5111.Description: A raw fish. Also called a yellowfin, these mid-sized ocean fish are delicious.
item_5111.Name: Amberjack

item_5112.Description: A raw hideous blood-sucking parasite fish.
item_5112.Name: Lamprey

item_5113.Description: A lump of gummy meat. It's supposedly edible, but only expert gourmands can stomach its squishy grossness.
item_5113.Name: Raw Oyster

item_5114.Description: A big raw shrimp. It needs to be de-veined and cleaned before eating.
item_5114.Name: Shrimp

item_52.Description: Test potion transforms you into a pig. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_52.Name: Pig Juice

item_52001.Description: Once a fine weapon, this bow has been mistreated for a very long time. It still shoots arrows, though.
item_52001.Name: Old Worn Bow

item_52002.Description: A mass-produced longbow made for infantrymen to use in a bind. Nothing special.
item_52002.Name: Stock Bow

item_52003.Description: An Elven bow made by someone with a lot of time on their hands. (An Elf, in other words.)
item_52003.Name: Hunting Bow

item_52004.Description: An Elven bow that's been enhanced with Goblin magic.
item_52004.Name: Goblinized Bow

item_52005.Description: Although technically Orcish, these bows are made by Dwarven conscripts.
item_52005.Name: Un-Tal Bow

item_52006.Description: Hand-made by a bored bowyer of middling skill.
item_52006.Name: Basic Bow

item_52007.Description: Apparently once used by Lawara, an elf you met in on an island. It's high-quality, and has a custom hand plate that provides a bit of shielding.
item_52007.Name: Lawara's Bow

item_52008.Description: Tremor the Myconian took this bow from a pesky elf. Myconians can't use bows, but Tremor liked plucking the string to make a 'twang' sound. It really irritated other myconians, and Tremor liked that.
item_52008.Name: Tremor's Bow

item_52009.Description: Practically oozing with enchantment, this masterpiece is rarely seen outside of Elven lands.
item_52009.Name: Elven Master Bow

item_5201.Description: A cleaned fish, ready for cooking.
item_5201.Name: Clownfish Fillet

item_52010.Description: Dwarves aren't really great at making bows with decent range. But this bow is very sturdy!
item_52010.Name: Dwarven Bashbow

item_52011.Description: A light bow designed for precision over power.
item_52011.Name: Eltibule Bow

item_52012.Description: Crafted by goblin slaves under the watchful eye of Gyrumpa, the legendary bowyer. He hated fun, and made sure his bows were especially taxing to use.
item_52012.Name: Goblinic Piercer

item_52013.Description: Tremor the Myconian took this bow from a pesky elf. Myconians can't use bows, but Tremor liked plucking the string to make a 'twang' sound. It really irritated other myconians, and Tremor liked that.
item_52013.Name: Tremor's Enhanced Bow

item_52014.Description: The Stalwarts, like all dwarves, had to work hard overcome their prejudice against ranged weapons. They developed this bludgeoning bow which acknowledges the value of archery while still insisting that hammers are better.
item_52014.Name: Stalwart Bow

item_52015.Description: A rakshasa craftsman named Malgath once used this to demonstrate his skill at crafting.
item_52015.Name: Malgath's Demo Bow

item_52016.Description: A longbow optimized for long-distance targets.
item_52016.Name: Bow of Range

item_52017.Description: A longbow optimized for quick shots.
item_52017.Name: Fastbow

item_52018.Description: A fairly-new item made in the Rakshasa manner, but probably not by a Rakshasa. Still not terrible.
item_52018.Name: Replica Rakshasa Bow

item_52019.Description: A competent and accurate weapon made by the elves of Sedgewick Forest.
item_52019.Name: Thentree Bow

item_5202.Description: A cleaned fish, ready for cooking.
item_5202.Name: Perch Fillet

item_52020.Description: A scarred and twisted bow, barely able to be strung. A hum of darkness can be felt from within. A tiny necromancy gem is embedded in the top.
item_52020.Name: Blackened Bow

item_52021.Description: These lightweight bows aren't actually used by the Peltasts of the Crone Hegemony, but by their support archers.
item_52021.Name: Peltast Bow

item_52022.Description: An Elven bow that's been enhanced with shoddy Goblin magic.
item_52022.Name: Cheap Goblinized Bow

item_52023.Description: A standard bow design used by orcish archers throughout the world. It's resilient yet accurate.
item_52023.Name: Orcish Military Bow

item_52024.Description: A bow designed to channel lightning. And also arrows.
item_52024.Name: Shockbow

item_52025.Description: This thick-handled bow gives tiny psychic cues to the owner, helping it aim perfectly. Some inherently psychic individuals can further take advantage of this mental amplification.
item_52025.Name: Prescient Bow

item_52026.Description: Commissioned by Arianna Fangblade for a close personal friend.
item_52026.Name: Fangblade Jr.

item_52027.Description: A deadly masterpiece that has been disguised to look like a simple sapling bow.
item_52027.Name: Fairy Bow

item_52028.Description: An otherworldly device that can fire energy projectiles. It can also fire regular arrows.
EffectDescs: Equipping this allows you to use the abilities "Basic Shot 7 (Energy Bow)", "Aimed Shot 7 (Energy Bow)", and "Blitz Shot 6 (Energy Bow)", assuming you already know and meet the requirements for the non-energy versions of those abilities.
item_52028.Name: Floxie's Faebow

item_52029.Description: A simple bow that can pack a lot of punch for its size.
item_52029.Name: Quality Bow

item_5203.Description: A cleaned fish, ready for cooking.
item_5203.Name: Eel Fillet

item_52030.Description: An otherworldly device that can fire energy projectiles. It can also fire regular arrows.
EffectDescs: Equipping this allows you to use the abilities "Basic Shot 7 (Energy Bow)", "Aimed Shot 7 (Energy Bow)", and "Blitz Shot 6 (Energy Bow)", assuming you already know and meet the requirements for the non-energy versions of those abilities.
item_52030.Name: Faebow

item_52031.Description: An Elven bow that's been enhanced with Goblin magic and lots of sharp bits.
item_52031.Name: Overgoblinized Bow

item_5210.Name: Flounder Fillet

item_5211.Name: Amberjack Fillet

item_5214.Description: A peeled and de-veined shrimp, ready for cooking. It's also delicious raw.
item_5214.Name: Cleaned Shrimp

item_52602.Description: A simple crossbow with nothing fancy about it.
item_52602.Name: Stock Crossbow

item_52603.Description: A simple crossbow with nothing fancy about it.
item_52603.Name: Stock Crossbow

item_52604.Description: Designed for use by orcish healers, this crossbow comes equipped with a vicious blade for self-defense and a series of holy symbols to allow healing.
item_52604.Name: Cutting Crossbow

item_52605.Description: This mean-looking weapon has a necromancy gem embedded in it.
item_52605.Name: Dark Crossbow

item_52606.Description: The two bolt grooves on this crossbow allow for somewhat-faster firing, but it's hardly "speedy".
item_52606.Name: Speed Crossbow

item_52607.Description: This unassuming-looking weapon hides a series of fire runes on the inside of the flight groove.
item_52607.Name: Crossbow of Flames

item_52608.Description: This crossbow is not actually demonic; it's just designed to look intimidating. The embedded necromancy gem was probably not intended for actual use, but it does work.
item_52608.Name: Demonic Crossbow

item_52609.Description: A simple but robust crossbow that handles well and can be easily restrung.
item_52609.Name: Hunting Crossbow

item_52610.Description: An over-engineered dwarven weapon. It requires a lot of maintenance, but most users find the accelerated reload-time worth it.
item_52610.Name: Double Crossbow

item_52611.Description: This seems like a simple evil crossbow, but in actuality is far more complex, with bizarre otherworldly magic.
EffectDescs: Equipping this allows you to use the ability "Shoot Darkness Bolt", assuming you already know and meet the requirements for Shoot Crossbow 9.
item_52611.Name: Darkcaster

item_53001.Description: Made by an amateur, this punching weapon barely fits onto your hand. But sometimes an ugly, stupid-looking weapon can inspire more fear than a good weapon. Not really. But keep thinking that while you wear these.
item_53001.Name: Shoddy Brass Knuckles

item_53002.Description: They've turned all green and gross. But they'll still work to make your punches more painful.
item_53002.Name: Corroded Brass Knuckles

item_53003.Description: These fit over your knuckles to make your punches hurt more. Now with real faux-brass coating!
item_53003.Name: Basic Brass Knuckles

item_53004.Description: Designed to fit over leather gloves, these brass knuckles have nasty bumps to make your punches cause extra injury.
item_53004.Name: Protruding Knuckles

item_53005.Description: It's sturdy, but it's so simple that it'd be hard not to be sturdy. But it's not false advertising, anyway.
item_53005.Name: Sturdy Cestus

item_53006.Description: This simple fist weapon was fitted for a goblin's hand, but you can make it work. (Cestuses count as an empty hand for purposes of Unarmed attacks.)
item_53006.Name: Goblin Cestus

item_53007.Description: This simple fist weapon will make your punches hurt more.
item_53007.Name: Quality Cestus

item_53008.Description: This simple fist weapon will make your punches hurt more.
item_53008.Name: Quality Cestus

item_53009.Description: Preferred by orcish martial artists, this black-iron fist weapon is intimidatingly heavy in the hand.
item_53009.Name: Orcish Katar

item_53011.Description: This grim fist weapon was clearly inspired by the Human legend of the Green Man, a druid who supposedly wanders the forests and punches wayword teens to death if they're out past curfew.
item_53011.Name: Fist of the Green Man

item_53012.Description: It was found in the gut of a giant spider. That's really the only spider-related thing going on here.
item_53012.Name: Spider Cestus

item_53013.Description: The preferred punching thingy of elven bullies.
item_53013.Name: Elven Cestus

item_53014.Description: It's a bit cramped for larger races, but this Dwarven unarmed weapon feels impressively heavy.
item_53014.Name: Dwarven Pugilfist

item_53015.Description: A piece of arm machinery from a large ancient golem.
item_53015.Name: Golem Fist

item_53016.Description: This punching weapon has a little mechanical serpent head on it which can be used to inject poison deep into a target.
item_53016.Name: Serpent Sting

item_53017.Description: This is just a piece of metal, but it's been covered in strange substances that help protect the hand of the puncher.
item_53017.Name: Yeti Knuckleduster

item_53018.Description: Someone has carved a fist weapon out of glasstone, a rock known for its supernatural lightness. The glasstone market is in shambles now that glasstone jewelry has fallen out of fashion among humans, so new uses are becoming affordable.
item_53018.Name: Glasstone Fist

item_53020.Description: This strangely-weighted punching weapon requires skill to use, but is quite deadly in the right hand.
item_53020.Name: Pounding Cestus

item_53021.Description: The creepy orcish mages known as Mutterers sometimes use weapons like this, designed to bleed the enemy.
item_53021.Name: Mutterer's Katar

item_53022.Description: A piece of arm machinery from a large ancient golem.
item_53022.Name: War Golem Fist

item_53023.Description: Designed by blacksmith-in-hiding Torgan, this weapon was weighted by a master. It requires quite a strong arm, though.
item_53023.Name: Torgan's Katar

item_53024.Description: A weapon made by ratkin martial artists. Ratkins are renowned for their use of poison.
item_53024.Name: Ratkin Katar

item_53025.Description: The weighting of this weapon is awkward for non-fairies, but it works after you get used to it.
item_53025.Name: Fairy Cestus

item_53026.Description: Used by ranalon martial artists to great effect.
item_53026.Name: Frog Punch

item_5306.Description: This head of broccoli looks a lot like a little green tree.
item_5306.Name: Broccoli

item_5307.Description: Orange and pointy. Yup, it's a carrot.
item_5307.Name: Carrot

item_5308.Description: A useful spice for cooking. It has an aromatic, warm and slightly bitter taste.
item_5308.Name: Oregano

item_5310.Description: A big bunch of purple grapes.
item_5310.Name: Grapes

item_5313.Description: This banana is in good shape - no brown spots yet.
item_5313.Name: Banana

item_5315.Description: A nice round gourd full of mushy stuff.
item_5315.Name: Pumpkin

item_5320.Description: A bunch of fresh barley grass.
item_5320.Name: Barley

item_5321.Description: A bunch of sugarcane stalks. Sugarcane can be cooked into molasses and sugar.
item_5321.Name: Sugarcane

item_5322.Description: Not really berries at all, these are actually seed cones with some bitter mushy stuff on the end. Useful as a spice and flavoring in brewing.
item_5322.Name: Juniper Berries

item_5323.Description: A fresh uncooked ear of corn. Corn is a bit of a delicacy in the Council Lands, although it's extremely common elsewhere.
item_5323.Name: Corn

item_5324.Description: Tart and sweet. A delicacy to some, but not as versatile for cooking as red apples.
item_5324.Name: Green Apple

item_5325.Description: Fruit from a strange plant that grows in the fae realm. While delicious, sprigganberries are incredibly poisonous unless the tiny seeds are carefully removed. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
EffectDescs: Food Poisoning: Heavy poison damage over time masks beneficial effect
item_5325.Name: Sprigganberries

item_5327.Description: A strong but pleasant-smelling herb used in cooking.
item_5327.Name: Basil

item_5328.Description: A large sweet fruit. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_5328.Name: Cantaloupe

item_5329.Description: Fresh green peas, ready for cooking.
item_5329.Name: Peas

item_5330.Description: Some fresh cranberries. Too bitter to be eaten raw, but useful in cooking.
item_5330.Name: Cranberries

item_53501.Description: Some bones strapped to a handle make this off-hand martial weapon look as stupid as it feels.
item_53501.Name: Shoddy Fighting Claw

item_53502.Description: Sharpened bone "blades" protrude from this off-hand martial weapon. It's silly looking, but dangerous!
item_53502.Name: Primitive Fighting Claw

item_53503.Description: This martial artist's glove is adorned with small sharpened metal protrusions. It smells like soup.
item_53503.Name: Goblin Claw

item_53504.Description: Fashionable, but a little uncomfortable to wear unless you're a Rakshasa.
item_53504.Name: Sturdy Claw

item_53505.Description: A skilled metalsmith put this left-handed fighting claw together. It's a little uncomfortable to wear, though.
item_53505.Name: Quality Claw

item_53506.Description: A skilled metalsmith put this left-handed fighting claw together. It's a little uncomfortable to wear, though.
item_53506.Name: Quality Claw

item_53507.Description: The Rakshasa martial artist handed this weapon down to a promising pupil.
item_53507.Name: Furlak's Claw

item_53508.Description: Long, deadly blades jut out from this glove-like weapon. It only fits the left hand.
item_53508.Name: Basic War Claw

item_53509.Description: When the Council demanded that the Rakshasa provide renumeration for every human that was injured at the Battle of Rahu, outraged Rakshasa tore up the treaty and killed the messengers, leading to the Sand War. The Rakshasa won the war with claws like this, fashioned after weapons from their home world.
item_53509.Name: Sand War Claw

item_53510.Description: Made of Cold Iron, this weapon is used in fae civil wars. Fairies who wield it are in constant pain from the metal... but not as much pain as their victims.
item_53510.Name: Fae Claw

item_53512.Description: Few of the legendary Dwarven Stalwarts used unarmed weapons, but the ones that did wore claws like this.
item_53512.Name: Stalwart Claw

item_53513.Description: The Rakshasa outcasts in the Ilmari Desert enchant these claws with life-saving protection from the desert elements.
item_53513.Name: Resistant Claw

item_53514.Description: A claw enchanted specifically for making horrible scars.
item_53514.Name: Torturer's Claw

item_53515.Description: A claw tailored specifically for the Claw Barrage maneuver.
item_53515.Name: Claw-Barrager

item_53516.Description: A claw with ugly tassels dangling from it. Being hit by this stupid-looking weapon is especially infuriating.
item_53516.Name: Ridiculer's Claw

item_53517.Description: Another public-relations disaster by the famous Veilmoor clan of human smiths, these claws are each imbued with the soul of a kitten who would otherwise have been euthanized. While it's not technically illegal to use such small souls in enchanting, the 'save the kittens forever' campaign was not appreciated by the weapon-buying public. But as is typical with Veilmoor products, the weapon is so good that nothing else matters too much.
item_53517.Name: Tragic Kitten Claw

item_53518.Description: Carefully designed to avoid hurting you while sprinting.
item_53518.Name: Running Claw

item_53519.Description: Designed by blacksmith-in-hiding Torgan, this wicked weapon features hooked talons to rip into flesh.
item_53519.Name: Torgan's Claw

item_53520.Description: A weapon made by a ratkin martial artist. It fits poorly to other races' hands, but it's nothing a little adhesive can't fix.
item_53520.Name: Ratkin Claw

item_53521.Description: Used by some troll martial-artists that you definitely do not want to meet.
item_53521.Name: Troll Claw

item_54.Description: Test potion transforms you into a deer. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_54.Name: Deer Juice

item_54001.Description: A well-made but simple lute, perfect for beginners.
EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in stringed instrument performance.
item_54001.Name: Classic Lute

EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in percussion instrument performance.
item_54002.Name: Hand Drum

item_54003.Description: An ocarina made of horn. This instrument is especially easy to learn.
EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in wind instrument performance.
item_54003.Name: Gemshorn

item_54004.Description: A brass horn of dwarven design.
EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in its use, assuming you already have mastery of the ocarina.
item_54004.Name: Blatterhorn

EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in its use, assuming you already have mastery of the drum.
item_54005.Name: Mini-Dulcimer

item_54006.Description: A tiny harp. Sounds pretty good.
EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in its use, assuming you already have mastery of the lute.
item_54006.Name: Harp

item_54007.Description: Found within a sentient weather phenomenon, this bizarre horn gives off an eerie glow.
EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in wind instrument performance.
item_54007.Name: Fog Horn

item_54008.Description: A set of enchanted chimes that can be both plucked and strummed.
EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in its use, assuming you already have mastery of the dulcimer AND the harp.
item_54008.Name: Fairy Chimes

item_5550.Description:
A brined cheese with a clean, slightly sour taste.

Cheese Type: Brine (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_5550.Name: Feta Cheese

item_55503.Description: It's a lumpy stick, but it's had the splinters removed.
item_55503.Name: Primitive Club

item_55504.Description: A lumpy stick with protruding thorns around the outside.
item_55504.Name: Vicious Club

item_55505.Description: The Flower Child liked to lovingly poke people with this dainty stick.
item_55505.Name: The Flower Child's Prodder

item_55506.Description: A very nasty very heavy stick.
item_55506.Name: Cruel Club

item_55507.Description: Agrashab used this club for a while before he found a better one.
item_55507.Name: Agrashab's Club

item_55508.Description: Gulagra, the spirit of discord, usually takes the form of a mountain-sized worm, and would have no use for this club. But somebody named it after him anyway.
item_55508.Name: Gulagra's Club

item_55509.Description: This legendary anti-troll device is imbued with magic flame that can never be quenched. There are rumors that sometimes the club's wielder gets a tiny bit incinerated when the fire gets out of control... but what are you, a baby?
EffectDescs: All Hammer attacks have a 25% chance to ignite the target, causing 50 damage over 20 seconds
item_55509.Name: Flame Basher

item_5551.Description:
A nutty, and quite hard, cheese.

Cheese Type: Hard (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_5551.Name: Gouda Cheese

item_55510.Description: This huge club has been used to kill so many drakeworms that some of their strange magic has rubbed off on it.
item_55510.Name: Deworming Club

item_55511.Description: Archtroll merchants in the fae realm sell these clubs as souvenirs to rich magical tourists. Very few tourists realize the exceptional quality they're purchasing, and most are thrown away as junk a few years later.
item_55511.Name: Archcudgel

item_55513.Description: A stick that's good for crushing.
item_55513.Name: Crushing Club

item_55515.Description: Otis the Ogre once used this in an epic arena battle. But he gave it away after he found a better one.
item_55515.Name: Otis's Gift Club

item_55516.Description: Only the best trollish crafters can claim the title of Archtroll and create Archcudgels. These weapons are deadly works of art.
item_55516.Name: Shattering Archcudgel

item_55517.Description: A dense stick that packs a punch.
item_55517.Name: Weighty Club

item_5552.Description:
A blue cheese with a luxurious taste and a horrific odor.

Cheese Type: Blue
item_5552.Name: Stilton Cheese

item_55561.Description: A big tree branch with most of the leaves removed.
item_55561.Name: Shoddy Club

item_55562.Description: A big tree branch with some of the bark removed to make a hand-hold.
item_55562.Name: Rough Club

item_55563.Description: A big tree branch with all the bark removed.
item_55563.Name: Crude Club

item_55564.Description: A big stick that's weighted so that the heavy part is at the hitting end.
item_55564.Name: Decent Club

item_55565.Description: It's pretty good for hitting things.
item_55565.Name: Nice Club

item_55566.Description: Polished and weighted with care and attention to detail.
item_55566.Name: Quality Club

item_55567.Description: As simple as clubs are, it's still surprisingly easy to screw them up. This one isn't screwed up!
item_55567.Name: Great Club

item_55568.Description: This club makes it seem effortless to swing a massive weight around.
item_55568.Name: Amazing Club

item_55569.Description: This club is bizarrely light for being so heavy.
item_55569.Name: Astounding Club

item_55602.Description: Thick and awkward, but basically indestructible.
item_55602.Name: Dwarven Hammer

item_55603.Description: This hammer has little rivulets carved into it to guide any blood away from the wielder's hand. Craftsmanship!
item_55603.Name: Battle Hammer

item_55604.Description: Perfect for hitting enemies and then shooting them with lightning. Much less practical for construction work.
item_55604.Name: Blasting Hammer

item_55605.Description: Covered in weird runes. Probably just graffiti.
item_55605.Name: Hammer of the Five Truths

item_55606.Description: Standard issue for the ancient Dwarven Stalwarts. They don't make them like this anymore.
item_55606.Name: Stalwart Hammer

item_55607.Description: This ungainly hammer has an inscription: 'Not even their bones must survive. - Ku Turla'
item_55607.Name: Mallet of Obliteration

item_55608.Description: A huge weighted hammer that can only be wielded by mighty warriors. It is said that a minotaur may not criticize their elders until they can wield this hammer -- a task that requires years of training even for that gigantic race.
item_55608.Name: Minotaur Hammer

item_55609.Description: Asterion the minotaur customized this ridiculously heavy hammer to be even heavier. A phrase is inscribed on the shaft in common tongue: "If you cannot lift my hammer, I shall lift it for you."
item_55609.Name: Asterion's Hammer

item_55610.Description: Made of stone that's been immersed in sadness -- literal, liquid sadness -- for years. It requires a strong mind to wield.
item_55610.Name: Devastating Hammer

item_55611.Description: Used by the strongest of the legendary orcish Misery Troopers.
item_55611.Name: Misery Trooper Hammer

item_55612.Description: Designed by blacksmith-in-hiding Torgan, this hammer is insanely, ridiculously, heavy.
item_55612.Name: Torgan's Hammer

item_55613.Description: A hefty tool that doubles as a deadly weapon.
EffectDescs: Pound, Pound to Slag, Leaping Smash, Rib Shatter, Reckless Slam, and Seismic Impact deal Piercing damage
item_55613.Name: Ratkin Mining Pick

item_55614.Description: A huge weighted warhammer that can only be wielded by mighty warriors. It is said that a minotaur may not criticize their elders until they can wield this hammer -- a task that requires years of training even for that gigantic race.
item_55614.Name: Minotaur Warhammer

item_56.Description: Use this wolf whistle on the teleportation platform north of Serbule Keep.
item_56.Name: Wolf Whistle

item_5601.Description:
A brined cheese that tastes weirdly floral. Ratkin use this cheese as sustenance in lean times.

Cheese Type: Brine (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_5601.Name: Ratkin Survival Cheese

item_59.Description: A primer on Combat Psychology. (Raises your skill to 1 if you don't know Combat Psychology.)
item_59.Name: Fighting with Psychology

item_60.Description: A chisel with a magical tip designed to chip away magical crystal.
item_60.Name: Geomancy Awl

item_6008.Description: An unfolding bloom of fried onion. Dipping sauce optional.
item_6008.Name: Onion Blossom

item_6009.Description: Boiled cabbage with salt and butter to taste. Not as bad as it sounds!
item_6009.Name: Boiled Cabbage

item_6010.Description: Voted the most under-rated vegetable dish by 4 out of 5 elven gourmands.
item_6010.Name: Baked Beets

item_6012.Description: A heaping head of broccoli with the *perfect* amount of salt and butter.
item_6012.Name: Broccoli Florets

item_6014.Description: Stuffed with what? Venison, of course!
item_6014.Name: Stuffed Squash

item_6015.Description: This muffin might sound strange but it is actually quite sweet. Disgusting, but sweet.
item_6015.Name: Guava Beet Muffin

item_6017.Description: Apples and strawberries in sweet syrup. A little monotonous.
item_6017.Name: Boring Fruit Cocktail

item_6018.Description: Apples, strawberries, grapes and oranges in sweet syrup.
item_6018.Name: Fruit Cocktail

item_6019.Description: Apples, grapes, oranges and guava in sweet syrup. Who puts guava in fruit cocktail?
item_6019.Name: Weird Fruit Cocktail

item_6020.Description: A loaf of warm, moist banana bread.
item_6020.Name: Banana Bread

item_6022.Description: Unlike most food, this does not give a long-term regeneration effect. Bacon is an instant pick-me-up any time!
item_6022.Name: Bacon

item_6023.Description: Tough and dry, but good for gnawing. This provides a quick instant pick-me-up.
item_6023.Name: Venison Jerky

item_6025.Description: Just like roast beef - except not.
item_6025.Name: Venison Roast

item_6026.Description: Tasty pork and venison sausage. Just don't ask to see how it's made ...
item_6026.Name: Sausage

item_6029.Description: There are worse things to stuff in a mushroom than meat from a mantis claw. Probably.
item_6029.Name: Mantis-Stuffed Mushroom

item_6030.Description: A perfectly edible fish dish, if a bit uninspired.
item_6030.Name: Fried Clownfish

item_6031.Description: Tasty fish sticks with the heartburny flavor of fried onions.
item_6031.Name: Breaded Perch with Onions

item_6033.Description: These leftover bits of a Super Fishy Surprise have been mixed together to get an ... "interesting" and "unusual" flavor.
item_6033.Name: Bonus Fishy Surprise

item_6034.Description: Boiled crab meat. Butter is optional.
item_6034.Name: Boiled Crab

item_6037.Description: A seasoned shark steak with a wood-fired sweet smoky flavor.
item_6037.Name: Maple-Smoked Shark

item_6038.Description: Smoked perch with a sweet orange glaze.
item_6038.Name: Orange Perch

item_6039.Description: Three skewers of seafood and vegetables.
item_6039.Name: Shark and Crab Kebabs

item_6040.Description: A baked potato with delicious melted cheese.
item_6040.Name: Cheesy Baked Potato

item_6041.Description: A baked potato topped with fresh butter.
item_6041.Name: Buttered Baked Potato

item_6042.Description: Baked beets in a succulent, simple glaze.
item_6042.Name: Glazed Beets

item_6043.Description: Thin, runny, and smelly. Mmm! Salt is a key ingredient.
item_6043.Name: Cabbage Soup

item_6044.Description: Choice parts of a pig infused with ancient spirits of evil. An instant pick-me-up! Warning: if Ur-Bacon speaks to you, do not speak back. Never follow instructions you receive from evil food of any kind.
item_6044.Name: Ur-Bacon

item_6046.Description: A bowl of oats and milk. Warm and bland. You should eat a bowl immediately! Food boosts your health and power regeneration rates, and makes combat much easier.
item_6046.Name: Plain Porridge

item_6048.Description: Comes with its own handle! An instant fill-up for the not-particularly-discerning bar patron.
item_6048.Name: Chicken Drumstick

item_6050.Description: Stir-fried chicken with broccoli and other vegetables.
item_6050.Name: Chicken and Broccoli

item_6051.Description: Baked with a delicate lemon glaze. Delicious!
item_6051.Name: Lemon-Glazed Chicken

item_6052.Description: Baked chicken in a complex dish. This one was cooked just right and has a variety of textures.
item_6052.Name: Chicken Casserole

item_6053.Description: A disgusting concoction created by someone who doesn't understand certain important concepts. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6053.Name: Beginner's Buttermilk

item_6054.Description:
Some damp biscuits. Not appetizing, but much better than starving!

(For an hour after you eat food, you'll regenerate health and power between fights. And better food than this can regenerate you DURING combat, too!)
item_6054.Name: Hardtack

item_6055.Description: An odorous dish said to be palatable to psychic mantises.
item_6055.Name: Venison Psi-Mantis Style

item_6056.Description: It smells bad, but... it doesn't taste too bad, actually.
item_6056.Name: Chicken Psi-Mantis Style

item_6057.Description: An improvement over basic hash browns. Greasy and salty, in a good way!
item_6057.Name: Venison Hash

item_6058.Description: Apple Juice! (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6058.Name: Apple Juice

item_6059.Description: A baked potato that has been rotated at a perfect consistency for hours. As far as plain ungarnished potatoes go, this is great...
item_6059.Name: Perfectly Baked Potato

item_6060.Description: Small dried vegetable chunks, magically puffed with air and then filled with sugar and cheese. It's... interesting.
item_6060.Name: Fairy Puffs

item_6061.Description: This poisonous muffin smells of wood and herbs. It can be used as a test for lycanthropy, as the muffins tend to kill werewolves, while only maiming others.
item_6061.Name: Wolfsbane Muffin

item_6062.Description: A delicious treat: a banana shallow-fried in sugary butter. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6062.Name: Fried Banana

item_6063.Description: A deceptively simple dish of beets, fish, and meat, somehow made tasty together.
item_6063.Name: Beets 'n Meats

item_6064.Description: A blend of baked vegetables in a hearty cheese sauce.
item_6064.Name: Cheesy Veggie Delight

item_6065.Description: Laura's Neth's melt-in-your-mouth cheese biscuits are to die for. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6065.Name: Laura's Cheese Biscuits

item_6066.Description: They may look like a light snack at first glance, but these biscuits are meaty and filling enough for a hearty meal.
item_6066.Name: Laura's Crab Biscuits

item_6068.Description: An orcish staple, famous for its lingering effect. It's... an acquired taste.
item_6068.Name: Black Soup

item_6069.Description: A very potent Elvish brew. Bitter as can be, but it warms you right up. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6069.Name: Bitter-Mint Tea

item_6070.Description: Mmm, battered and deep-fried. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6070.Name: Fried Crab

item_6071.Description: Unleavened bread. Not super tasty by itself, but good in sandwiches. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6071.Name: Flatbread

item_6072.Description: Tasty crabmeat in a makeshift bun. Lemony!
item_6072.Name: Crab Roll

item_6073.Description: Made with whatever meat is available and seasoned within an inch of its life. Most races find the smell pleasant, but the taste much too salty. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6073.Name: Goblin Stew

item_6074.Description: A mushy fruit paste that can be eaten as a snack. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6074.Name: Guava Bowl

item_6075.Description: A true masterpiece of potato-making. Well, actually, the potato itself is a little soggy. But the toppings are masterful!
item_6075.Name: Loaded Baked Potato

item_6076.Description: A tasty baked dish with mutton and veggies.
item_6076.Name: Shepherd's Pie

item_6077.Description: A tasty baked dish with beef and veggies.
item_6077.Name: Cottage Pie

item_6078.Description: A pleasant baked dish with odds and ends.
item_6078.Name: Peasant's Pie

item_6079.Description: Dried meat from unusual creatures. Salted beyond reckoning. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6079.Name: Mystery Jerky

item_6080.Description: Warm crusty bread, perfect for a cold day. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6080.Name: Snacking Bread

item_6081.Description: Cured pig meat with a touch of sugar and a hint of cloves.
item_6081.Name: Juicy Ham

item_6082.Description: A cup of heated mushroom blend with a pinch of spices. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6082.Name: Myconutmeg

item_6083.Description: A simple, tasty beverage. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6083.Name: Orange Juice

item_6084.Description: A delicious blended fruit drink. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6084.Name: Fruity Mushy

item_6085.Description: A delicious cold beverage. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6085.Name: Lemonade

item_6086.Description: A delicious cold beverage. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6086.Name: Hiral's Citrus Blend

item_6087.Description: A pleasant cold beverage. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6087.Name: Sun Vale Tea

item_6088.Description: A thick seasonal drink. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6088.Name: Pumpkin Smoothie

item_6090.Description: A delicious, if basic, pumpkin pie. It's missing fancy spices! And maybe something to top it with.
item_6090.Name: Basic Pumpkin Pie

item_6092.Description: Gretchen Salas has a way with a potato. These rolls are really good! You can't even taste the potato.
item_6092.Name: Gretchen's Potato Rolls

item_6093.Description: An elvish drink. Not quite tea, and not quite fruit juice, but something in between. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6093.Name: Leafwater

item_6094.Description: An elvish invention. A single fist-sized cube of this will keep you from being hungry all day. It tastes like fruitcake.
item_6094.Name: Lembas Brick

item_6095.Description: A bell pepper full of steak! Mm. Meaty.
item_6095.Name: Stuffed Bell Pepper

item_6096.Description: A stir-fried vegetarian dish with more than a hint of spice.
item_6096.Name: Vegetable Masterpiece

item_6097.Description: Supposedly a favorite of mountain-dwelling orcs. Fresh mutton topped with cheese and peppers.
item_6097.Name: Mountain Mutton

item_6098.Description: A tough but highly portable snack consisting of chewy shark meat in a fried pepper husk. It's an acquired taste.
item_6098.Name: Shark Chew

item_6099.Description: A heady mixture of edible mushrooms in a green pepper "bowl".
item_6099.Name: Shroom Feast

item_61.Description: Dear player, thank you for completing this quest. If this were a complete MMO, you would have received a fun reward now. Maybe next time! - Eric
item_61.Name: I.O.U. Quest Reward

item_6100.Description: An advanced preparation of the humble bird. Delicious!
item_6100.Name: Aromatic Chicken

item_6101.Description: A very spicy version of Aromatic Chicken. Not for the faint of heart.
item_6101.Name: Spicy Chicken

item_6102.Description: A stew which is definitely better than the sum of its ingredients.
item_6102.Name: Basic Pepperpot

item_6103.Description: An exotic meal that uses a rare fish found only in the deepest of caves. The fish is delicious, but has a slightly bitter aftertaste that has to be drowned out by tons of lemon.
item_6103.Name: Spicy Cavefish

item_6104.Description: A bizarre snack that uses a rare fish found only in the deepest of caves. You eat it scales and all. It takes some getting used to.
item_6104.Name: Cavefish Sticks

item_6105.Description: An unexpectedly refreshing drink. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6105.Name: Beachside Blend

item_6106.Description: The perfect refreshment after desert exertion. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6106.Name: Chuma's Agave Secret

item_6107.Description: An unusual tea with a strong kick. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6107.Name: Desert Tea

item_6108.Description: This drink has a not-too-great flavor, but it's very good at rehydrating tired bodies. The preferred desert beverage of people who are too rich to drink water. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6108.Name: Hydration Punch

item_6109.Description: Venison fried in butter and coated in fresh-cracked pepper. A restorative treat!
item_6109.Name: Pepper Venison

item_6110.Description: A delicious snack food. It's ... some sort of meat... drenched in a sweet sauce and wrapped in dough. Selaxi refuses to part with the recipe. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6110.Name: Selaxi's Scorpion Stinger

item_6111.Description: A tasty beverage of cactus juice and some sweet ingredient Selaxi refuses to share. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6111.Name: Selaxi's Cactus Mixer

item_6112.Description: An invention of the yeti people, this kabob-like snack is best eaten before you learn the ingredients. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6112.Name: Yeti Stick

item_6113.Description: A yeti invention of boiled mutton in matted fur. The stench is impressive. The taste is unique, and not as bad as you'd expect.
item_6113.Name: Furpot

item_6114.Description: A delicious seasonal tea. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6114.Name: Pumpkin Spice Tea

item_6115.Description: A pie so good that it would be foolish to eat it as just a dessert. Eat it as a meal.
item_6115.Name: Fancy Pumpkin Pie

item_6116.Description: Hard on the outside, runny liquid on the inside. Mmm...
item_6116.Name: Soft-Boiled Egg

item_6117.Description: Runny and hot and covered in salt and pepper. Ideal with some bread.
item_6117.Name: Poached Egg

item_6118.Description: This is just some raw eggs in a glass, blended with a little milk. Gross. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6118.Name: Raw Egg Blend

item_6119.Description: Somebody wove some long bacon strips into a sort of bowl. And then put chunks of fried meat into the bowl. Weird. Salty.
item_6119.Name: Bacon Basket

item_6120.Description: It's a scrambled egg, beloved breakfast of nearly every sentient race.
item_6120.Name: Scrambled Egg

item_6121.Description: It's... a clownfish. Dried and salted. Snack-sized. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6121.Name: Dried Clownfish

item_6123.Description: A well-preserved and salted fish, perfect for snacking. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6123.Name: Dried Grapefish

item_6124.Description: A well-preserved and salted fish. This makes an amazing snack! (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6124.Name: Dried Perch

item_6127.Description: A well-preserved and salted fish. An ... interesting... snack. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6127.Name: Dried Cave Fish

item_6128.Description: Low-quality pieces of cat meat have been sliced extraordinarily thin, tenderized, and then buried in salt. The result is a cup of hot stew that tastes ... salty. But not horrible. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6128.Name: Cat Stew Cup

item_6129.Description: Cat meat coated in a thick orange sauce. Surprisingly not terrible.
item_6129.Name: Orange Cat

item_6130.Description: The perfect seasonings make cat meat not just palatable, but actually tasty.
item_6130.Name: Spicy Lemon Cat

item_6131.Description: Dried meat and fish in a secret blend of spices. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6131.Name: Nishika's Travel Snack

item_6132.Description: Made from the tender tentacles of young kraken, this meal is quite the delicacy.
item_6132.Name: Kraken Calamari

item_6133.Description: It stinks! And it tastes vinegary. But it's... it's edible.
item_6133.Name: Pickled Fish

item_6134.Description: Picked beets in a secret alpha-development sauce. (This item cannot be crafted. It provides benefits equivalent to a level 25 Meal item, but it has no Gourmand requirement. A normal level 25 Meal requires Gourmand level 10+.)
item_6134.Name: Alpha Beets

item_6135.Description: Fried cat-meat in a house blend of spices and lightly breaded.
item_6135.Name: House Cat

item_6136.Description: Shaved ice flavored with apple. This treat should be eaten quickly before it melts! (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6136.Name: Apple Shaved Ice

item_6137.Description: Shaved ice flavored with strawberries. This treat should be eaten quickly before it melts! (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6137.Name: Strawberry Shaved Ice

item_6138.Description: Shaved ice flavored with grapes. This treat should be eaten quickly before it melts! (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6138.Name: Grape Shaved Ice

item_6139.Description: Shaved ice flavored with orange juice. This treat should be eaten quickly before it melts! (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6139.Name: Orange Shaved Ice

item_6140.Description: Shaved ice flavored with guava. This treat should be eaten quickly before it melts! (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6140.Name: Guava Shaved Ice

item_6141.Description: Shaved ice flavored with pureed banana. This treat should be eaten quickly before it melts! (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6141.Name: Banana Shaved Ice

item_6142.Description: Shaved ice flavored with lemon juice. This treat should be eaten quickly before it melts! (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6142.Name: Lemon Shaved Ice

item_6143.Description: Fresh, cold, and delicious. Eat it before it melts! (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6143.Name: Mint Ice Cream

item_6144.Description: A well-made omelet is an attractive and delicious meal. This one's full of ham and cheese.
item_6144.Name: Basic Ham Omelet

item_6146.Description: Fresh, cold, and delicious. Eat it before it melts! (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6146.Name: Strawberry Ice Cream

item_6147.Description: Delicious long-grain rice, as prepared in Rahu.
item_6147.Name: Rahu Rice

item_6148.Description: Raw clownfish on a ball of delicious rice.
item_6148.Name: Clownfish Nigiri

item_6149.Description: Raw crab meat on a ball of delicious rice.
item_6149.Name: Crab Nigiri

item_6150.Description: Raw grapefish on a ball of delicious rice.
item_6150.Name: Grapefish Nigiri

item_6151.Description: Raw perch on a ball of delicious rice.
item_6151.Name: Perch Nigiri

item_6352.Description: Sorry! Please accept this cake as a token of our apology. - Sincerely, the Project: Gorgon team
item_6352.Name: Apology Cake

item_6353.Description: A slice of mouth-watering honey cake! It's slightly cold to the touch, and it looks somewhat translucent, but it tastes delicious. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6353.Name: Fairy Cake

item_6354.Description: A cold stew that seems warm to the touch. And it smells amazing. What's your favorite food? Why, it smells exactly like that, and tastes even better!
item_6354.Name: Fairy Stew

item_6355.Description: The captain of the Wintertide's secret recipe. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6355.Name: Tiramisu of Delights

item_6356.Description: A little bit of Etana cooked up in a vegetable stew. A taste of when the cook gets cooked!
item_6356.Name: Apprentice Surprise

item_6357.Description: A potent drink that's popular among poor humans of the Crone Hegemony. (Actual Crones drink much higher-quality stuff.) This can warm you up on a cold day! (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6357.Name: Crone Coffee

item_6358.Description: A horrible "candy" that is technically poisonous: that numb feeling on your tonue? That's the poison. But it's also technically food... (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6358.Name: Meat Candy

item_6359.Description: A seasonal drink with an intoxicating aroma and a surprising kick. (This is a snack. Snacks stack with meal foods; you can eat one of each and get the benefits of both.)
item_6359.Name: Pumpkin Spice Coffee

item_6360.Description: A cake to celebrate 3 years of Project: Gorgon on Steam! Thanks for playing and supporting us!
item_6360.Name: 3-Year Steamed Cake

item_64.Description: Teaches you the basics of Archery. (Raises your skill to 1 if it isn't already.)
item_64.Name: Archery For Imbeciles

item_6401.Description: Baked beets in a succulent, simple glaze.
item_6401.Name: Glazed Beets

item_6402.Description: A loaf of warm, moist banana bread.
item_6402.Name: Banana Bread

item_6405.Description: A delicious treat: a banana shallow-fried in sugary butter.
item_6405.Name: Fried Banana

item_6406.Description: A blend of baked vegetables in a hearty cheese sauce.
item_6406.Name: Cheesy Veggie Delight

item_6407.Description: Tasty crabmeat in a makeshift bun. Lemony!
item_6407.Name: Crab Roll

item_6451.Description: This is an incredibly unappealing piece of rotten meat.
EffectDescs: Food Poisoning: Heavy poison damage over time masks beneficial effect
item_6451.Name: Maggoty Ham

item_6452.Description: This is an incredibly unappealing piece of rotten meat.
EffectDescs: Food Poisoning: Heavy poison damage over time masks beneficial effect
item_6452.Name: Rotten Meat

item_6453.Description: Even though this food was designed to last a very long time, it's still been too long.
EffectDescs: Food Poisoning: Heavy poison damage over time masks beneficial effect
item_6453.Name: Spoiled Rations

item_65.Description: Teaches you the basics of Fletching. (Raises your skill to 1 if it isn't already.)
item_65.Name: I'd Rather Be Fletching

item_66.Description: Teaches you how to performed Unarmed kicks. Only useful if you somehow managed to get turned into an animal before learning the Unarmed Kick ability. (Raises your Unarmed skill to 1 if it isn't already.)
item_66.Name: Kicking Your Way To Murder

item_69.Description: Test potion transforms you into a spider. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_69.Name: Spider Juice

item_71.Description: Teaches you the Myconian language. (This is a testing aid and will not be available for long; please use this to test the Myconian dungeon, which can be accessed via random brown mushrooms in Serbule.)
item_71.Name: Myconian Primer

item_72.Description: Lets you fly for 30 minutes (press the Move Up key to begin). You'll take no damage from falls while the effect lasts.
item_72.Name: Flight Potion

item_73.Description: You become a raven. Use the Move Up key to fly. Your attacks will do negligible damage. But you can fly, so that's something.
item_73.Name: Raven Potion

item_74.Description: Teaches you how to survey, find minerals, and mine ore. (Raises your skill in Surveying, Geology, and Mining to 1 if they aren't already.)
item_74.Name: Surveying Book

item_75.Description: Test potion transforms you into a cow. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_75.Name: Cow Juice

item_77.Description: It's a note labeled "To my dear friend."
item_77.Name: Note from Yurra

item_79.Description: Turns off PvP caused by PvP Juice test-potions.
item_79.Name: Un-PvP Juice

item_80.Description: Makes you PvP-flagged for a half hour. You can attack other players who are also PvP-flagged.
item_80.Name: PvP Juice (30 minutes)

item_81.Description: Makes you PvP for an hour.
item_81.Name: PvP Juice (60 minutes)

item_82.Description: Strange weeds that supposedly bring the dead back to life.
item_82.Name: Eternal Greens

item_83.Description: Makes you PvP against ALL players -- even ones who don't want to PvP! Used for live events only! Use UnPvPJuice to turn it off.
item_83.Name: Special PK Juice

item_84.Description: Potion transforms you into a GIGANTIC spider. Permanent until dispelled via UnspiderJuice. For live events only!
item_84.Name: Superspider Juice

item_85.Description: Teaches you how to create visual arts. (Raises your skill to 1 if it isn't already.)
item_85.Name: How To Be An Artist

item_86.Description: Test potion transforms you into a giant bat. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_86.Name: Bat Juice

item_88.Description: When you aren't in combat, hold down Shift to run very, very fast. You also take no damage from falls. Lasts 5 minutes.
item_88.Name: Super Speed Potion

item_89.Description: Gives you a blank appearance. Consume a minor panacea to return to normal.
item_89.Name: Admin Invisibility Potion

item_90.Description: Transforms you into a rabbit. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_90.Name: Bunny Juice

item_92.Description: Transforms you into a spirit fox. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_92.Name: Fox Juice

item_94.Description: Transforms you into a skeleton. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_94.Name: Skeleton Juice
